Value: any structural anomaly of the cavity in each of the cerebral hemispheres derived from the cavity of the embryonic neural tube; they are separated from each other by the septum pellucidum, and each communicates with the third ventricle by the foramen of Monro, through which also the choroid plexuses of the lateral ventricles become continuous with that of the third ventricle

Subject: dilated lateral ventricles [MP:0000825]
Value: the luminal space of the lateral ventricles is increased in volume or area, usually with an increase in contained fluid, in the cavity in each of the cerebral hemispheres derived from the cavity of the embryonic neural tube; they are separated from each other by the septum pellucidum, and each communicates with the third ventricle by the foramen of Monro, through which also the choroid plexuses of the lateral ventricles become continuous with that of the third ventricle

Subject: abnormal third ventricle morphology [MP:0000826]
Value: any structural anomaly of the narrow cleft inferior to the corpus callosum, within the diencephalon, between the paired thalami; its floor is formed by the hypothalamus, its anterior wall by the lamina terminalis, and its roof by ependyma; it communicates with the fourth ventricle by the cerebral aqueduct, and with the lateral ventricles by the interventricular foramina

Subject: dilated third ventricle [MP:0000827]
Value: the luminal space of the third ventricle is increased in volume or area, usually with an increase in contained fluid, in the narrow cleft inferior to the corpus callosum, within the diencephalon, between the paired thalami; its floor is formed by the hypothalamus, its anterior wall by the lamina terminalis, and its roof by ependyma; it communicates with the fourth ventricle by the cerebral aqueduct, and with the lateral ventricles by the interventricular foramina

Subject: abnormal fourth ventricle morphology [MP:0000828]
Value: any structural anomaly of the irregularly shaped cavity in the rhombencephalon, between the medulla oblongata, the pons, and the isthmus in front, and the cerebellum behind; it is continuous with the central canal of the cord below and with the cerebral aqueduct above, and through its lateral and median apertures it communicates with the subarachnoid space

Subject: dilated fourth ventricle [MP:0000829]
Value: the luminal space of the fourth ventricle is increased in volume or area, usually with an increase in contained fluid, in the irregularly shaped cavity in the rhombencephalon, between the medulla oblongata, the pons, and the isthmus in front, and the cerebellum behind; it is continuous with the central canal of the cord below and with the cerebral aqueduct above, and through its lateral and median apertures it communicates with the subarachnoid space

Subject: abnormal diencephalon morphology [MP:0000830]
Value: any structural anomaly of the paired caudal parts of the prosencephalon from which the thalamus, hypothalamus, epithalamus and subthalamus are derived; these regions regulate autonomic, visceral and endocrine function, and process information directed to the cerebral cortex

Subject: diencephalon hyperplasia [MP:0000831]
Value: overdevelopment or increased size, usually due an increased number of cells in the rostral portion of the brain stem

Subject: abnormal thalamus morphology [MP:0000832]
Value: any structural anomaly of the large ovoid mass of paired bodies containing mostly grey matter and forming part of the lateral wall of the third ventricle of the brain

Subject: thalamus hyperplasia [MP:0000833]
Value: overdevelopment or increased size, usually due an increased number of cells in the thalamus

Subject: abnormal subthalamus morphology [MP:0000834]
Value: any structural anomaly of the anterior part of the diencephalon that lies between the thalamus, hypothalamus, and tegmentum of the mesencephalon, including subthalamic nucleus, zona incerta, the fields of Forel, and the nucleus of ansa lenticularis

Subject: abnormal subthalamic nucleus morphology [MP:0000835]
Value: any structural anomaly of the lens-shaped nucleus located in the ventral part of the subthalamus on the inner aspect of the internal capsule that is concerned with the integration of somatic motor function

Subject: abnormal substantia nigra morphology [MP:0000836]
Value: any structural anomaly of the layer of grey substance that separates the posterior parts of the cerebral peduncles (tegmentum mesencephali) from the anterior parts; it normally includes a posterior compact part with many pigmented cells (pars compacta) and an anterior reticular part whose cells contain little pigment (pars reticularis)

Subject: abnormal hypothalamus morphology [MP:0000837]
Value: any structural anomaly of the ventral part of the diencephalon extending from the region of the optic chiasm to the caudal border of the mammillary bodies and forming the inferior and lateral walls of the third ventricle; this region regulates the autonomic nervous system via hormone production and release

Subject: hypothalamus hyperplasia [MP:0000839]
Value: overdevelopment or increased size, usually due an increased number of cells in the hypothalamus

Subject: abnormal epithalamus morphology [MP:0000840]
Value: any structural anomaly of the small dorsomedial area of the thalamus including the habenular nuclei and associated fiber bundles, the pineal body, and the epithelial roof of the third ventricle

Subject: abnormal hindbrain morphology [MP:0000841]
Value: any structural anomaly of the part of the brain developed from the posterior of the three primary brain vesicles of the embryonic neural tube from which the metencephalon and myelencephalon are derived; the metencephalon (anterior part of the embryonic hindbrain), gives rise to the cerebellum and pons while the myelencephalon (posterior portion of the embryonic hindbrain) gives rise to the medulla oblongata

Subject: absent superior olivary complex [MP:0000842]
Value: missing nucleus of neurons on the dorsal part of the lateral surface of the pons; it normally receives projection fibers from the cochlear nuclei and is prominently involved in spatial localization of sound

Subject: absent facial nuclei [MP:0000843]
Value: missing nucleus of neurons in the hindbrain; receives fibers from the facial muscles, stapedus muscle and stylohyoid muscle

Subject: abnormal pontine flexure morphology [MP:0000844]
Value: any structural anomaly of the dorsally concave bend of the embryonic rhombencephalon that produces a thinning of the roof of the pons and medulla oblongata and defines the boundary between the metencephalon and myelencephalon in the embryo

Subject: abnormal medulla oblongata morphology [MP:0000846]
Value: any structural anomaly in the most caudal region of the brainstem that lies directly rostral to the spinal cord; includes regions responsible for autonomic functions such as digestion, breathing and control of heart rate

Subject: abnormal metencephalon morphology [MP:0000847]
Value: any structural anomaly of the anterior part of the developing vertebrate hindbrain or the corresponding part of the adult brain composed of the cerebellum and the pons Varolii

Subject: abnormal pons morphology [MP:0000848]
Value: any structural anomaly of the band of nerve fibers in the brain connecting the medulla oblongata and the mesencephalon; this region conveys information about movement from the cerebral hemisphere to the cerebellum

Subject: abnormal cerebellum morphology [MP:0000849]
Value: any structural anomaly of the part of the metencephalon that lies in the posterior cranial fossa dorsal to the pons and medulla that is concerned with the coordination of movement and learning of motor skills

Subject: absent cerebellum [MP:0000850]
Value: missing the part of the metencephalon that lies in the posterior cranial fossa dorsal to the pons and medulla that is concerned with the coordination of movement

Subject: cerebellum hypoplasia [MP:0000851]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced cell number, in the cerebellum

Subject: small cerebellum [MP:0000852]
Value: reduced size of cerebellum

Subject: absent cerebellar foliation [MP:0000853]
Value: missing small branches of the cerebellar lobules

Subject: abnormal cerebellum development [MP:0000854]
Value: aberrant or incomplete differentiation of the part of the metencephalon that lies dorsal to the pons and medulla behind the brain stem and controls balance for walking and standing, modulates the force and range of movement and is involved in the learning of motor skills

Subject: accelerated formation of intralobular fissures [MP:0000855]
Value: formation of the major fissures of the cerebellum earlier in development than normal

Subject: abnormal cerebellar plate morphology [MP:0000856]
Value: any structural anomaly of the embryonic pseudostratified epithelium of the fourth cerebellar ventricle that eventually forms the vermis and ventral neuroepithelium

Subject: abnormal cerebellar foliation [MP:0000857]
Value: any anomaly of the pattern of the ten cerebellar lobules; in mammals, the vermis portion of the cerebellum has a foliation pattern along the AP axis that is distinct from the lateral cerebellar hemispheres and the intermediate zone that separates the vermis from the lateral hemispheres; in addition, each of the ten basic lobules can be subdivided into sublobules but strain and species differences are reported

Subject: altered metastatic potential [MP:0000858]
Value: altered likelihood of a tumor cell spreading from the site of the initial tumor formation and forming a secondary tumor at another site not directly connected with it

Subject: abnormal somatosensory cortex morphology [MP:0000859]
Value: any structural anomaly of the area of the parietal lobe that lies posterior to the central sulcus and is concerned with receiving and processing general sensations from the body surface

Subject: abnormal primary somatosensory cortex morphology [MP:0000860]
Value: any structural anomaly of the area of the postcentral gyrus and central sulcus that is involved in somatic sensation

Subject: disorganized barrel cortex [MP:0000861]
Value: derangement of the pattern of the discrete functional units of the somatosensory cortex that processes tactile information derived from the vibrissae

Subject: absent barrels in primary somatosensory cortex [MP:0000862]
Value: missing pattern of the discrete functional units of the somatosensory cortex that processes tactile information derived from the vibrissae

Subject: abnormal secondary somatosensory cortex morphology [MP:0000863]
Value: any structural anomaly of the area of the upper bank of the lateral sulcus that is involved in somatic sensation

Subject: abnormal cerebellum vermis morphology [MP:0000864]
Value: any structural anomaly of the narrow medial zone between the two hemispheres of the cerebellum that is delimited by two longitudinal furrows; it may be continuous with the cerebellar hemispheres in some areas of the cerebellum, e.g., dorsally, or separated by deeper fissues in others (e.g., ventrally); it receives inputs from the spinocerebellar tracts which carry to the vermis information on the position and balance of the torso, and it sends projections to the fastigial nucleus of the cerebellum, which then sends output to the vestibular nuclei

Subject: absent cerebellum vermis [MP:0000865]
Value: missing narrow middle zone between the two hemispheres of the cerebellum

Subject: cerebellum vermis hypoplasia [MP:0000866]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, in the vermis

Subject: abnormal cerebellum anterior vermis morphology [MP:0000867]
Value: any structural anomaly of the anterior portion of the narrow middle zone between the two hemispheres of the cerebellum that is located anterior to the primary fissure

Subject: decreased anterior vermis size [MP:0000868]
Value: smaller appearance of the narrow middle zone between the two hemispheres of the anterior lobe of the cerebellum

Subject: abnormal cerebellum posterior vermis morphology [MP:0000869]
Value: any structural anomaly of the posterior portion of the narrow middle zone between the two hemispheres of the cerebellum that is located posterior to the primary fissure

Subject: absent cerebellum vermis lobule VIII [MP:0000870]
Value: missing part of the inferior vermis of the cerebellum (vermis lobule VIII)

Subject: absent cerebellum vermis lobule IX [MP:0000871]
Value: missing triangular elevation on the vermis of the cerebellum

Subject: abnormal cerebellum external granule cell layer morphology [MP:0000872]
Value: any structural anomaly of the transient layer of the cerebellar cortex present during development which is composed of the dividing and migrating granule cells

Subject: thin external granule cell layer [MP:0000873]
Value: reduced thickness of the transient layer of the cerebellar cortex present during development which is composed of dividing and migrating granule cells

Subject: irregular external granule cell layer thickness [MP:0000874]
Value: uneven thickness of the transient layer of the cerebellar cortex present during development which is composed of dividing and migrating granule cells

Subject: abnormal cerebellar Purkinje cell layer [MP:0000875]
Value: any structural anomaly of the cell layer that lies just underneath the molecular layer of the cerebellar cortex; it contains the neuronal cell bodies of the Purkinje cells that are arranged side by side in a single layer, and candelabrum interneurons are vertically oriented between the Purkinje cells

Subject: Purkinje cell degeneration [MP:0000876]
Value: a retrogressive impairment of function or destruction of the large neurons located at the interface of the molecular and internal granule layers of the cerebellar cortex

Subject: abnormal Purkinje cell morphology [MP:0000877]
Value: any structural anomaly of the neurons located at the interface of the molecular and internal granule layers of the cerebellar cortex; these inhibitory neurons provide the output of the cerebellar cortex through axons that project into the white matter, and extensive dendritic trees from the Purkinje cells extend upward in a single plane into the molecular layer where they synapse with parallel fibers of granule cells

Subject: abnormal Purkinje cell number [MP:0000878]
Value: different from average number of neuronal cells that are located in the interface of the molecular and granular layers of the cerebellar cortex

Subject: increased Purkinje cell number [MP:0000879]
Value: greater than normal number of neuronal cells that are located in the interface of the molecular and granular layers of the cerebellar cortex

Subject: decreased Purkinje cell number [MP:0000880]
Value: fewer than normal neuronal cells that are located in the interface of the molecular and granular layers of the cerebellar cortex

Subject: delaminated Purkinje cell layer [MP:0000884]
Value: splitting or disorganization of the layer of large neuron cell bodies between the molecular and granular layers of the cerebellum

Subject: abnormal cerebellar granule layer morphology [MP:0000886]
Value: any structural anomaly of the innermost cortical layer of the cerebellum; contains densely packed small neurons, mostly granule cells with some Golgi cells are found at the outer border

Subject: delaminated cerebellar granule layer [MP:0000887]
Value: splitting or disorganization of the deepest of the three layers of the cerebellum that contains granule cells

Subject: absent cerebellar granule layer [MP:0000888]
Value: absence of the innermost cortical layer of the cerebellum; contains densely packed small neurons, mostly granule cells with some Golgi cells are found at the outer border

Subject: abnormal cerebellar molecular layer [MP:0000889]
Value: any structural anomaly of the outermost layer of the cerebral cortex that contains the parallel fibers of the granule cells, interneurons such as stellate and basket cells, and the dendrites of the underlying Purkinje cells

Subject: thin cerebellar molecular layer [MP:0000890]
Value: reduced width of the outermost layer of the cerebral cortex that contains the parallel fibers of the granule cells, interneurons such as stellate and basket cells, and the dendrites of the underlying Purkinje cells

Subject: abnormal midbrain morphology [MP:0000897]
Value: any structural anomaly associated with the brain region derived from the middle of the three cerebral vesicles of the embryo; this region controls sensory and motor functions in the adult, including eye movement and coordination of auditory and visual reflexes

Subject: midbrain hyperplasia [MP:0000898]
Value: overdevelopment or increased size, usually due an increased number of cells associated with the brain region derived from the middle of the three cerebral vesicles of the embryo; this region controls sensory and motor functions in the adult, including eye movement and coordination of auditory and visual reflexes

Subject: abnormal corpora quadrigemina morphology [MP:0000899]
Value: any structural anomaly of the inferior and superior colliculus

Subject: decreased colliculi size [MP:0000900]
Value: smaller inferior and superior colliculus

Subject: altered position of colliculi [MP:0000901]
Value: positional abnormality of the inferior and superior colliculus

Subject: abnormal superior colliculus morphology [MP:0000904]
Value: any structural anomaly of the paired superior eminence of the mesencephalic tectum that is involved in auditory processing

Subject: increased superior colliculus size [MP:0000905]
Value: enlargement of the paired superior eminence of the mesencephalic tectum

Subject: abnormal trigeminal V mesencephalic nucleus morphology [MP:0000906]
Value: any structural anomaly of the group of sensory neurons residing in a long, narrow plate in the midbrain; axons pass with the trigeminal nerve

Subject: small mesencephalic trigeminal nucleus [MP:0000907]
Value: reduced size of the group of sensory neurons residing in a long, narrow plate in the midbrain; axons pass with the trigeminal nerve

Subject: absent mesencephalic trigeminal nucleus [MP:0000908]
Value: missing group of sensory neurons residing in a long, narrow plate in the midbrain; axons pass with the trigeminal nerve

Subject: abnormal facial motor nucleus morphology [MP:0000909]
Value: any structural anomaly of the group of motor neurons residing in the pons that innervate the muscles of facial expression

Subject: small facial motor nucleus [MP:0000910]
Value: reduced size of the group of motor neurons residing in the pons that innervate the muscles of facial expression

Subject: abnormal trigeminal motor nucleus morphology [MP:0000911]
Value: any structural anomaly of the group of motor neurons innervating the muscles of mastication

Subject: small trigeminal motor nucleus [MP:0000912]
Value: reduced size of the group of motor neurons innervating the muscles of mastication

Subject: abnormal brain development [MP:0000913]
Value: aberrant or incomplete differentiation of the brain

Subject: exencephaly [MP:0000914]
Value: neurocranial defects resulting in exposure or extrusion of the brain

Subject: obstructive hydrocephaly [MP:0000917]
Value: hydrocephaly due to a block in cerebrospinal fluid flow in the ventricular system

Subject: cranioschisis [MP:0000919]
Value: incomplete closure of the skull, usually congenital

Subject: abnormal myelination [MP:0000920]
Value: any anomaly in the process by which myelin sheaths are formed and maintained around neurons; oligodendrocytes in the brain and spinal cord and Schwann cells in the peripheral nervous system wrap axons with compact layers of their plasma membrane

Subject: demyelination [MP:0000921]
Value: a partial absence or patchy, incomplete area of a myelin sheath over all or part of an axon or fiber tract due to degeneration or destruction of the myelin sheath

Subject: abnormal roof plate morphology [MP:0000923]
Value: any structural anomaly of the single row of specialized glial cells that occupies the dorsal midline of the developing neural tube along the entire anterior-posterior axis; the roof plate serves as a critical embryonic signaling center for the organization of dorsal neuronal cell types, and acts as a barrier preventing axons and cells migrating across the dorsal midline

Subject: absent roof plate [MP:0000924]
Value: absence of the single row of specialized glial cells that occupies the dorsal midline of the developing neural tube along the entire anterior-posterior axis; the roof plate serves as a critical embryonic signaling center for the organization of dorsal neuronal cell types, and acts as a barrier preventing axons and cells migrating across the dorsal midline

Subject: abnormal floor plate morphology [MP:0000925]
Value: any structural anomaly of the specialized glial structure (non-neuronal cells) situated at the ventral midline of the embryonic neural tube; this structure spans the anteroposterior axis from the midbrain to the tail regions, separating the left and right basal plates of the developing neural tube, and serves as an organizer to ventralize tissues in the embryo as well as to guide neuronal positioning and differentiation along the dorsoventral axis of the neural tube

Subject: absent floor plate [MP:0000926]
Value: absence of the specialized glial structure (non-neuronal cells) situated at the ventral midline of the embryonic neural tube; this structure spans the anteroposterior axis from the midbrain to the tail regions, separating the left and right basal plates of the developing neural tube, and serves as an organizer to ventralize tissues in the embryo as well as to guide neuronal positioning and differentiation along the dorsoventral axis of the neural tube

Subject: small floor plate [MP:0000927]
Value: reduced size of the specialized glial structure (non-neuronal cells) situated at the ventral midline of the embryonic neural tube; this structure spans the anteroposterior axis from the midbrain to the tail regions, separating the left and right basal plates of the developing neural tube, and serves as an organizer to ventralize tissues in the embryo as well as to guide neuronal positioning and differentiation along the dorsoventral axis of the neural tube

Subject: incomplete rostral neuropore closure [MP:0000928]
Value: arrest of the fusion of the cephalic neural folds

Subject: open neural tube [MP:0000929]
Value: failure of completion of the last step in the formation of the neural tube, where the paired neural folds are brought together and fuse at the dorsal midline

Subject: wavy neural tube [MP:0000930]
Value: undulations in the embryonic neural tube

Subject: absent notochord [MP:0000932]
Value: missing axial fibrocellular cord in embryos around which develops the vertebral primordia

Subject: abnormal rhombomere morphology [MP:0000933]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the transiently divided segments of the developing neural tube of vertebrate embryos found within the hindbrain region in the area that will eventually become the rhombencephalon; the rhombomeres appear as a series of slightly constricted swellings in the neural tube, caudal to the cephalic flexure

Subject: abnormal telencephalon development [MP:0000934]
Value: anomaly in the progression of the enlarged anteriolateral part of the brain; consists of the paired cerebral hemispheres and olfactory bulbs, the basal ganglia and the connecting structures, and is considered to be the seat of conscious mental processes; it develops from the anterior-most embryological division of the brain that develops from the prosencephalon

Subject: abnormal folding of telencephalic vesicles [MP:0000935]
Value: malformation of the stereotypic invaginations forming the paired diverticula of the telencephalon

Subject: small embryonic telencephalon [MP:0000936]
Value: reduced size of the paired diverticula of the embryonic telencephalon, from which the forebrain develops

Subject: abnormal motor neuron morphology [MP:0000937]
Value: any structural anomaly of cells that innervate an effector (muscle or glandular) tissue and are responsible for transmission of motor impulses

Subject: motor neuron degeneration [MP:0000938]
Value: retrogressive impairment of function or destruction of the cells that innervate an effector (muscle or glandular) tissue and are responsible for transmission of motor impulses

Subject: decreased motor neuron number [MP:0000939]
Value: fewer than normal numbers of cells that innervate an effector (muscle or glandular) tissue and are responsible for transmission of motor impulses

Subject: abnormal motor neuron innervation pattern [MP:0000940]
Value: any changes in the placement, morphology or number of motor nerve fibers to an effector motor tissue, or failure of refinement of neuronal connections during development

Subject: convulsive seizures [MP:0000947]
Value: seizures characterized by uncontrolled motor activity

Subject: nonconvulsive seizures [MP:0000948]
Value: seizures without uncontrolled motor activity, but with impairment of consciousness

Subject: abnormal seizure response to pharmacological agent [MP:0000950]
Value: anomaly in the seizure activity response that is brought about by treatment with pharmacological agents

Subject: sporadic seizures [MP:0000951]
Value: occasional seizures occurring at irregular intervals

Subject: abnormal CNS glial cell morphology [MP:0000952]
Value: any structural anomaly of non-neuronal cells of the central nervous system that form the myelin insulation of nervous pathways, guide neuronal migration during development, and exchange metabolites with neurons

Subject: abnormal oligodendrocyte morphology [MP:0000953]
Value: any structural anomaly of the neuroglia of the central nervous system that form the insulating myelin sheath of axons in the CNS

Subject: decreased oligodendrocyte progenitor number [MP:0000954]
Value: fewer cells that differentiate into a type of glial cell in the central nervous system

Subject: abnormal spinal cord morphology [MP:0000955]
Value: any structural anomaly of the cylindrical tissue of the vertebral canal that extends from the medulla oblongata to the conus medullaris

Subject: decreased spinal cord size [MP:0000956]
Value: smaller appearance of the spinal cord

Subject: peripheral nervous system degeneration [MP:0000958]
Value: a retrogressive impairment of function or destruction of the ganglia and peripheral nerves that lie outside the brain and spinal cord

Subject: abnormal somatic sensory system morphology [MP:0000959]
Value: any structural anomaly of the neural tissue involved in the transmission of sensory signals

Subject: abnormal sensory ganglion morphology [MP:0000960]
Value: any structural anomaly of the clusters of neurons in the somatic peripheral nervous system which contain the cell bodies of sensory nerve axons, interneurons and non-neuronal supporting cells

Subject: abnormal dorsal root ganglion morphology [MP:0000961]
Value: any structural anomaly of a group of sensory nerve cell bodies located on the dorsal spinal roots within the vertebral column

Subject: disorganized dorsal root ganglion [MP:0000962]
Value: loss of segmentation pattern of dorsal root ganglia or loss of regular spacing between the ganglia

Subject: fused dorsal root ganglion [MP:0000963]
Value: loss of DRG spacing pattern and the appearance of two or more ganglia as one

Subject: small dorsal root ganglion [MP:0000964]
Value: reduced size a group of sensory nerve cell bodies located on the dorsal spinal roots within the vertebral column

Subject: abnormal sensory neuron morphology [MP:0000965]
Value: any structural anomaly of cells that innervate an effector (muscle or glandular) tissue and are responsible for transmission of sensory impulses

Subject: decreased sensory neuron number [MP:0000966]
Value: fewer than normal numbers of cells that innervate an effector (muscle or glandular) tissue and are responsible for transmission of sensory impulses

Subject: abnormal sensory neuron innervation pattern [MP:0000968]
Value: any changes in the placement, morphology or number of sensory nerve fibers to sensory termini or to spinal cord

Subject: abnormal nociceptor morphology [MP:0000969]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the peripheral receptors for pain, including receptors sensitive to painful mechanical stimuli, extreme heat or cold, and chemical stimuli

Subject: abnormal polymodal receptor morphology [MP:0000970]
Value: anomaly in a sensory receptor that may be stimulated by mechanical, thermal or chemical means

Subject: abnormal thermoreceptor morphology [MP:0000971]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the cellular receptors that mediate the sense of temperature; in vertebrates, these are most often located under the skin

Subject: abnormal mechanoreceptor morphology [MP:0000972]
Value: anomaly in the receptors of the body, usually nerve termini, that respond to mechanical pressure or distortion

Subject: abnormal cutaneous/subcutaneous mechanoreceptor morphology [MP:0000973]
Value: any structural anomaly of the neuronal receptors that respond to mechanical pressure or distortion in the skin

Subject: abnormal hair guard neuron morphology [MP:0000974]
Value: anomaly of the subcutaneous mechanoreceptors that innervate hair follicles of guard hairs, and are involved in the amplification of slow-moving and/or light touch stimuli signals

Subject: absent hair guard neurons [MP:0000975]
Value: absence of the subcutaneous mechanoreceptors that innervate hair follicles of guard hairs, and are involved in the amplification of slow-moving and/or light touch stimuli signals

Subject: hyperinnervation of hair guard cells [MP:0000976]
Value: more robust innervation of the subcutaneous mechanoreceptors that innervate hair follicles of guard hairs, and are involved in the amplification of slow-moving and/or light touch stimuli signals

Subject: abnormal hair-tylotrich neuron morphology [MP:0000977]
Value: anomaly of the subcutaneous mechanoreceptors that innervate tylotrich hair follicles

Subject: hyperinnervation of hair-tylotrich cells [MP:0000978]
Value: more robust innervation of the hair tylotrich cells

Subject: abnormal hair-down neuron morphology [MP:0000979]

Subject: absent hair-down neurons [MP:0000980]

Subject: hyperinnervation of hair-down cells [MP:0000981]
Value: more robust innervation of the subcutaneous mechanosensitive D-hair (down-hair) neurons, which innervate hair follicles, and are characterized by a large-amplitude Cav3.2 T-current involved in the amplification of slow-moving and/or light touch stimuli

Subject: abnormal Meissner\'s corpuscle morphology [MP:0000982]

Subject: enlarged Meissner\'s corpuscles [MP:0000983]

Subject: hyperinnervation of Meissner\'s corpuscle [MP:0000984]

Subject: abnormal Merkel\'s receptor morphology [MP:0000985]

Subject: increased Merkel\'s receptor number [MP:0000986]
Value: greater than the normal number of the modified epidermal cells located in the stratum basale and found mostly in areas where sensory perception is acute

Subject: hyperinnervation of Merkel\'s receptor [MP:0000987]

Subject: abnormal pacinian corpuscle morphology [MP:0000988]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the rapidly adapting mechanoreceptors found in subcutaneous tissue beneath both hairy and glabrous skin, and which normally contain an afferent nerve fiber surrounded by a capsule with multiple concentric layers; trasmit signals generated by vibrations when grasping an object

Subject: abnormal Ruffini\'s corpuscle morphology [MP:0000989]
Value: any structural anomaly in the sensory cells in the subcutaneous tissue of the digits specialized to transduce mechanical stimuli, skin stretch, direction of object motion, hand shape and finger position

Subject: abnormal skeletal muscle mechanoreceptor morphology [MP:0000990]
Value: any structural anomaly of the receptors that respond to mechanical pressure or distortion in the skeletal muscle

Subject: abnormal primary muscle spindle morphology [MP:0000991]
Value: any structural anomaly of the sensory organ in muscle; involved in the stretch reflex and sensitive to stretch velocity

Subject: absent primary muscle spindle [MP:0000992]

Subject: partial loss of primary muscle spindle [MP:0000993]

Subject: abnormal secondary muscle spindle morphology [MP:0000994]

Subject: absent secondary muscle spindle [MP:0000995]

Subject: partial loss of secondary muscle spindle [MP:0000996]
Value: missing a portion of the sensory organ in muscle; involved in the stretch reflex and is not sensitive to stretch velocity

Subject: abnormal synovial joint capsule morphology [MP:0000997]

Subject: absent synovial joint capsule [MP:0000998]

Subject: abnormal golgi tendon organ morphology [MP:0000999]

Subject: absent golgi tendon organ [MP:0001000]

Subject: abnormal chemoreceptor morphology [MP:0001001]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the cells specialized to detect chemical substances and relay that information centrally in the nervous system

Subject: abnormal taste bud morphology [MP:0001002]

Subject: abnormal olfactory receptor morphology [MP:0001003]

Subject: abnormal retinal photoreceptor morphology [MP:0001004]
Value: any structural anomaly of a cell specialized to detect and transduce light, including rods and cones of the retina

Subject: abnormal retinal rod cell morphology [MP:0001005]

Value: increased measure of the head and trunk (head, thorax and abdomen) in the rostral-caudal direction

Subject: decreased body length [MP:0001258]
Value: decreased measure of the head and trunk (head, thorax and abdomen) in the rostral-caudal direction

Subject: abnormal body weight [MP:0001259]
Value: anomaly in average weight compared to controls

Subject: increased body weight [MP:0001260]
Value: greater than normal average weight

Subject: obese [MP:0001261]

Subject: decreased body weight [MP:0001262]
Value: lower than normal average weight

Subject: weight loss [MP:0001263]
Value: progressive reduction of body weight below normal average for age

Subject: increased body size [MP:0001264]
Value: larger than average body weight, height and/or length of an organism compared to controls

Subject: decreased body size [MP:0001265]
Value: smaller than average body weight, height and/or length of an organism compared to controls

Subject: enlarged chest [MP:0001267]
Value: wider diameter, or distended chest cavity

Subject: barrel chest [MP:0001268]
Value: distended circumference of the thoracic and abdominal areas

Subject: distended abdomen [MP:0001270]

Subject: increased metastatic potential [MP:0001272]

Subject: decreased metastatic potential [MP:0001273]
Value: reduced likelihood of a tumor cell spreading from the site of the initial tumor formation and forming a secondary tumor at another site not directly connected with it

Subject: curly vibrissae [MP:0001274]
Value: coiled or spiral shape of the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors

Subject: tangled vibrissae [MP:0001277]
Value: snarled or intertwined stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors

Subject: kinked vibrissae [MP:0001278]
Value: sharp bends in the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors

Subject: wavy vibrissae [MP:0001279]

Subject: loss of vibrissae [MP:0001280]
Value: inability to retain the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors

Subject: increased vibrissae length [MP:0001281]
Value: longer average length of the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors

Subject: short vibrissae [MP:0001282]
Value: decreased length of the stiff hairs projecting from the face around the nose of most mammals which act as touch receptors

Subject: sparse vibrissae [MP:0001283]
Value: few and widely spaced stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors

Subject: absent vibrissae [MP:0001284]
Value: absence of the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors

Subject: abnormal eye development [MP:0001286]
Value: malformation or arrest of differentiation of the visual organ

Subject: abnormal lens induction [MP:0001288]
Value: any anomaly in the signaling at short range between the head ectoderm and the optic vesicle that results in the head ectoderm forming a lens

Subject: persistence of hyaloid vascular system [MP:0001289]
Value: failure of the degeneration of the transient vascular system of the eye during development, that normally nourishes the retina, immature lens and primary vitreous of the developing eye

Subject: delayed eyelid opening [MP:0001290]
Value: late average time for the first postnatal eye opening

Subject: abnormal lens vesicle development [MP:0001292]
Value: malformation or abnormal patterning of the ectodermal invagination that forms opposite the optic cup in the primordium of the lens of the eye

Subject: anophthalmia [MP:0001293]
Value: absence of the globe and ocular tissue from the orbit, with or without the presence of ocular adnexa (eyelids, conjunctiva, and lacrimal apparatus); remnants of the globe sometimes appear in ectopic locations

Subject: macrophthalmia [MP:0001296]
Value: increased average size of the eyes

Subject: microphthalmia [MP:0001297]
Value: reduced average size of the eyes; generally refers to a congenital defect

Subject: abnormal eye distance/ position [MP:0001299]
Value: abnormal placement of the eyes in relation to each other or in relation to other craniofacial structures

Subject: ocular hypertelorism [MP:0001300]
Value: increased interpupillary distance, i.e. increased distance between the center of the pupils of the two eyes

Subject: eyelids open at birth [MP:0001302]
Value: open eyes instead of closed at perinatal stage; failure of the upper and lower thin folds of skin and muscle that cover the exposed portion of the eye to fuse completely together during development and an individual is born with the eye(s) uncovered leading to degrees of injury and blindness

Subject: abnormal lens morphology [MP:0001303]
Value: any structural anomaly of the transparent structure of the eye responsible for focusing light rays

Subject: cataract [MP:0001304]
Value: complete or partial opacity of the lens

Subject: enlarged lens [MP:0001305]
Value: increased size of the transparent structure of the eye responsible for focusing light rays

Subject: small lens [MP:0001306]
Value: reduced size of the transparent structure of the eye responsible for focusing light rays

Subject: fused cornea and lens [MP:0001307]
Value: condition in which the transparent anterior portion of the fibrous coat of the eye is joined to the transparent biconvex cellular refractive structure lying between the iris and vitreous humor of the eye

Subject: abnormal lens polarity [MP:0001308]
Value: failure of normal orientation of the lens during development

Subject: hydropic eye lens fibers [MP:0001309]
Value: swollen cortical fibers of the eye lens

Subject: abnormal conjunctiva morphology [MP:0001310]
Value: any structural anomaly of the mucous membrane that lines the inner surface of the eyelids and the front of the eyeball

Subject: abnormal cornea morphology [MP:0001312]
Value: any structural anomaly of the transparent anterior portion of the fibrous coat of the eye that covers the iris, pupil, and anterior chamber; together with the lens, the cornea refracts light

Subject: increased incidence of corneal inflammation [MP:0001313]
Value: greater than average occurrence and/or persistence of the local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in the cornea

Subject: corneal opacity [MP:0001314]
Value: complete or partial clouding of the cornea

Subject: corneal scarring [MP:0001316]
Value: appearance of fibrous tissue on the cornea after healing in response to injury

Subject: abnormal pupil morphology [MP:0001317]
Value: any structural anomaly of the central circular aperture of the iris through which light rays enter the eye

Subject: pupil opacity [MP:0001318]
Value: milky or cloudy appearance of the central circular aperture of the iris through which light rays normally enter the eye

Subject: irregularly shaped pupil [MP:0001319]
Value: shape defects in the aperture of the iris through which light rays enter the eye, usually circular

Subject: small pupils [MP:0001320]
Value: smaller than normal size of the central circular aperture of the iris through which light rays enter the eye

Subject: abnormal iris morphology [MP:0001322]
Value: any structural anomaly of the adjustable membrane, composed of the stroma and pigmented epithelium, located just in front of the crystalline lens within the eye

Subject: abnormal eye pigmentation [MP:0001324]
Value: change in the normal pigmentation of the eye to another color, or lack of color

Subject: abnormal retina morphology [MP:0001325]
Value: any structural anomaly of the thin layer of neural tissue lining the back of the eyeball which contains visual receptors

Subject: retinal degeneration [MP:0001326]
Value: retrogressive pathological change in the thin layer of neural tissue lining the back of the eyeball, which contains visual receptors and can result in the impairment or cessation of retinal neural function

Subject: decreased retinal photoreceptor cell number [MP:0001327]
Value: fewer than the expected number of rods and/or cones

Subject: disorganized retinal layers [MP:0001328]
Value: derangement of the pattern of the sheets of cells comprising the optic part of the retina

Subject: retina hyperplasia [MP:0001329]
Value: overdevelopment or increased size, usually due an increased number of cells in the thin layer of neural tissue lining the back of the eyeball which contains visual receptors

Subject: abnormal optic nerve morphology [MP:0001330]
Value: any structural anomaly of the second cranial nerve which is responsible for conveying visual information from the retina to the brain; it extends from the retina to the optic chiasma where part of its fibers become the optic tract and cross to the opposite side and pass to the geniculate bodies

Subject: abnormal optic nerve innervation [MP:0001332]
Value: misprojection or aberrant target finding of the second cranial nerve which is responsible for conveying visual information from the retina to the brain

Subject: absent optic nerve [MP:0001333]
Value: absence of the second cranial nerve which is responsible for conveying visual information from the retina to the brain

Subject: absent optic tract [MP:0001334]
Value: absence of the band of the paired bands of optic nerve fibers running from the optic chiasma mostly to the lateral geniculate body, with a smaller number of fibers terminating in the superior colliculus and the pretectal region

Subject: dry eyes [MP:0001337]
Value: absence of natural or normal moisture in the eye

Subject: abnormal eyelid morphology [MP:0001340]
Value: any structural anomaly of the skin folds covering the front of the eyeball

Subject: absent eyelids [MP:0001341]
Value: missing skin folds covering the front of the eyeball when closed

Subject: pronounced eyelids [MP:0001343]
Value: strongly protruding eyelids

Subject: blepharoptosis [MP:0001344]
Value: ptosis, drooping eyelids

Subject: Meibomian gland atrophy [MP:0001345]
Value: acquired diminution of the size of the sebaceous glands embedded in the tarsal plate of each eyelid, associated with wasting as from death and reabsorbtion of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes

Subject: abnormal lacrimal gland morphology [MP:0001346]
Value: any structural anomaly of the glands that secrete tears

Subject: absent lacrimal glands [MP:0001347]
Value: missing the glands that secrete tears

Subject: abnormal lacrimal gland physiology [MP:0001348]
Value: any functional anomaly of the glands that secrete tears

Subject: excessive tearing [MP:0001349]
Value: an unusually high amount of fluid in the eye, either oversecreted by the lacrimal glands, or due to imperfect drainage by the tear conducting passages, often resulting in overflow of fluid from the eye onto the cheek

Subject: increased aggression towards mice [MP:0001353]
Value: when compared to controls, subjects exhibit greater than the normal level of domineering, assaultive posture and/or hostile physical action toward other mice

Subject: increased aggression towards males [MP:0001354]
Value: when compared to controls, subjects exhibit greater than the normal level of domineering, assaultive posture and/or hostile physical action toward male mice

Subject: submission towards male mice [MP:0001355]
Value: no domineering, assault posture nor hostile physical action toward male mice

Subject: increased aggression towards females [MP:0001356]
Value: when compared to controls, subjects exhibit greater than the normal level of domineering, assaultive posture and/or hostile physical action toward female mice

Subject: increased aggression towards humans [MP:0001357]
Value: when compared to controls, subjects exhibit greater than the normal level of domineering, assaultive posture and/or hostile physical action toward humans

Subject: aggression towards inanimate objects [MP:0001358]
Value: a domineering, assault posture and/or hostile physical action toward inanimate objects

Subject: abnormal social investigation [MP:0001360]
Value: altered behavior of animals to approach and examine other animals

Subject: social withdrawal [MP:0001361]
Value: reclusive behavior; the tendency to refrain from participating in social situations and to seek isolation

Subject: abnormal anxiety-related response [MP:0001362]
Value: altered emotional response related to anticipation of a non-specific threat

Subject: increased anxiety-related response [MP:0001363]
Value: when compared to controls, subjects exhibit more responses thought to be indicative of anxiety in behavioral tests

Subject: decreased anxiety-related response [MP:0001364]
Value: when compared to controls, subjects exhibit fewer responses thought to be indicative of anxiety in behavioral tests

Subject: abnormal mating preference [MP:0001375]
Value: any change from the common preference of an initiating organism to initiate sexual contact with a receptive partner; in rodents, this usually refers to males that attempts to initiate sexual behavior with males and females indiscriminately

Subject: abnormal mating receptivity [MP:0001376]
Value: deviation from the normal cycle or inability of females to respond favorably to males that initiate sexual behavior

Subject: abnormal mating frequency [MP:0001377]
Value: increased, reduced or absent attempt of sexual behavioral contact between an initiating organism and a receptive partner

Subject: abnormal ejaculation [MP:0001378]
Value: anomalies in the ability to propulse semen from the genital ducts and the urethra to the exterior

Subject: abnormal penile erection [MP:0001379]
Value: altered ability to achieve a rigid state of the penis obtained in the condition in which the erectile tissue is filled with blood

Subject: reduced male mating frequency [MP:0001380]
Value: males do not as frequently initiate sexual behavior (as scored by the presence of copulation plugs in rodents, not due to infertility)

Subject: abnormal nursing [MP:0001382]
Value: females show anomlies in the feeding of offspring from mammary glands, or do not nurse offspring, or nurse offspring infrequently

Subject: abnormal pup retrieval [MP:0001384]
Value: any anomaly in the ability of a nesting female to retrieve stray pups to the nest or a delay in retrieving stray pups

Subject: pup cannibalization [MP:0001385]
Value: the killing and eating of newborn mice by the mother; however, this can be a normal response if the mother does not recognize the pups as her own

Subject: abnormal maternal nurturing [MP:0001386]
Value: anomaly in the behaviors related to a female tending to young

Subject: abnormal stationary movement [MP:0001388]
Value: altered ability or inability to change body posture or shift a body part

Subject: abnormal eye movement [MP:0001389]
Value: deviation from the normal motility of the visual organs

Subject: abnormal tail movements [MP:0001391]
Value: a change from the normal manner of moving the tail

Subject: abnormal locomotor behavior [MP:0001392]
Value: altered ability or inability to move from place to place in response to stimuli

Subject: ataxia [MP:0001393]
Value: inability to coordinate voluntary muscular movements

Subject: circling [MP:0001394]
Value: repeated movement in a circle; often associated with inner ear defects

Subject: bidirectional circling [MP:0001395]
Value: circling behavior exhibited in both clockwise and counterclockwise directions

Subject: unidirectional circling [MP:0001396]
Value: circling behavior in one direction only, either clockwise or counterclockwise

Subject: hyperactivity [MP:0001399]
Value: general restlessness or excessive movement; more frequent movement from one place to another or having an increased state of activity

Subject: hyperresponsive [MP:0001400]
Value: increased reaction to touch

Subject: jumpy [MP:0001401]
Value: marked by fitful, jerky movements

Subject: hypoactivity [MP:0001402]
Value: general reduced locomotor activity; reduced movement from one place to another or having a decreased state of activity

Subject: no spontaneous movement [MP:0001404]
Value: failure of neonates or embryos to initiate any voluntary or spontaneous change in position or posture, with or without external stimulus

Subject: impaired coordination [MP:0001405]
Value: reduced ability to execute integrated movements of muscle

Subject: abnormal gait [MP:0001406]
Value: abnormal pattern of movement of the limbs of animals, characterized by elements of progression, stability, speed and length over the ground

Subject: short stride length [MP:0001407]
Value: reduced average distance between steps

Subject: stereotypic behavior [MP:0001408]
Value: repetitive, invariant, perseverative motor patterns that do not appear to be purposeful

Subject: increased stereotypic behavior [MP:0001409]
Value: more frequent incidence of repetitive, invariant, perseverative motor patterns that do not appear to be purposeful

Subject: head bobbing [MP:0001410]
Value: repetitive up and down movement of the head

Subject: spinning [MP:0001411]
Value: repetitive rolling of the body

Subject: excessive scratching [MP:0001412]
Value: compulsive scraping of the skin, usually with the nails

Subject: abnormal response to new environment [MP:0001413]
Value: altered behavioral reaction associated with placing an animal in a new location

Subject: increased exploration in new environment [MP:0001415]
Value: greater amount of time spent investigating new location

Subject: decreased exploration in new environment [MP:0001417]
Value: less amount of time spent investigating a new location

Subject: abnormal drinking behavior [MP:0001422]
Value: an altered pattern of fluid consumption or altered preference for particular fluids

Subject: abnormal liquid preference [MP:0001423]
Value: the desire to drink more or less fluids than average, or to drink unusual fluids

Subject: abnormal alcohol consumption [MP:0001425]
Value: aberrant behavioral-related or physiological-related intake of alcohol into the body

Subject: polydipsia [MP:0001426]
Value: abnormally large intake of fluids by mouth, usually due to excessive thirst that is relatively prolonged

Subject: adipsia [MP:0001428]
Value: failure to drink

Subject: dehydration [MP:0001429]
Value: excessive water loss from the body or from an organ or bodily part

Subject: abnormal eating behavior [MP:0001431]
Value: altered ability to consume foods or atypical consumption pattern

Subject: abnormal food preference [MP:0001432]
Value: the desire to eat more or less food than average, or to eat unusual foods

Subject: polyphagia [MP:0001433]
Value: eating to excess

Subject: absent suckling reflex [MP:0001435]
Value: inability to orient and open/close mouth in sucking pattern in response to external light touching or stroking of the chin

Subject: abnormal suckling behavior [MP:0001436]
Value: reduced ability or inability to exert suction by the mouth, or atypical suckling pattern

Subject: no swallowing reflex [MP:0001437]
Value: inability to pull food through the esophagus to the stomach in response to feeding

Subject: aphagia [MP:0001438]
Value: failure to eat

Subject: abnormal grooming behavior [MP:0001440]
Value: defects in the standard of behavior of cleaning and/or keeping outward appearance tidy (self, mate or offspring)

Subject: increased grooming behavior [MP:0001441]
Value: increased amount of time spent cleaning and/or keeping outward appearance tidy (self, mate or offspring)

Subject: decreased grooming behavior [MP:0001442]
Value: reduced amount of time spent cleaning and/or keeping outward appearance tidy (self, mate or offspring)

Subject: poor grooming [MP:0001443]
Value: below average standard of cleaning and/or keeping outward appearance tidy (self, mate or offspring)

Subject: abnormal whisker trimming behavior [MP:0001446]
Value: anomaly in the behavior of plucking or biting off of the whiskers/vibrissae from other individuals of a cohort

Subject: abnormal nest building behavior [MP:0001447]
Value: deviation from the usual behavior of nesting animals to build sleeping nests out of any available materials, or of nesting animals to build nests to protect offspring

Subject: abnormal huddling behavior [MP:0001448]
Value: deviation from the usual tendency of mice to pile together when sleeping

Subject: abnormal cued conditioning behavior [MP:0001454]
Value: anomaly in the ability of an animal to learn and remember an association between an aversive experience (the unconditioned stimulus (US), usually a shock) and a neutral stimulus (the conditioned stimulus (CS), usually an auditory cue or light flash)

Subject: abnormal object recognition memory [MP:0001458]
Value: anomaly in the ability to recognize objects that the animal has previously encountered; recognition is measured by relative amount of time exploring objects, which should decrease upon subsequent or multiple presentations of the same object when presented with novel objects at the same time

Subject: abnormal olfactory discrimination memory [MP:0001460]
Value: anomaly in the ability to exhibit a differential response to olfactory stimuli that is achieved by the reinforcement of the desired response for each particular olfactory stimulus

Subject: abnormal avoidance learning behavior [MP:0001462]
Value: anomaly in the ability to associate a previously neutral stimulus with an unpleasant or punishing stimuli so that the animal learns to avoid the previously neutral stimulus

Subject: abnormal spatial learning [MP:0001463]
Value: anomaly in the ability to ascertain or acquire spatial location information in order to improve navigation or other behavior using such location cues

Subject: abnormal temporal memory [MP:0001468]
Value: anomaly in the ability to recall temporal events and stimuli

Subject: abnormal contextual conditioning behavior [MP:0001469]
Value: anomaly in the ability of an animal to learn and remember an association between an aversive experience (the unconditioned stimulus (US), usually a shock) and the neutral, unchanging environment (the conditioned stimulus (CS), or the environmental context in this case)

Subject: reduced long term potentiation [MP:0001473]
Value: less than the normal persistent robust synaptic response induced by synchronous stimulation of pre- and postsynaptic cells

Subject: reduced long term depression [MP:0001475]
Value: less than the normal, persistent activity-dependent decrease in synaptic efficacy between neurons, often following slow, weak stimulation of CA1 neurons

Subject: abnormal pinna reflex [MP:0001485]
Value: anomaly in the response to an auditory stimulus by a characteristic ear twitch

Subject: abnormal startle reflex [MP:0001486]
Value: aberrant threshold or reflex response to variable stimuli, often auditory; usually measured by amplitude of whole body flinch

Subject: increased startle reflex [MP:0001488]
Value: reduced threshold or more severe reflex response to variable stimuli, often auditory; usually measured by amplitude of whole body flinch

Subject: decreased startle reflex [MP:0001489]
Value: greater threshold or less severe reflex response to variable stimuli, often auditory; usually measured by amplitude of whole body flinch

Subject: abnormal vibrissae reflex [MP:0001490]
Value: animals do not change position in response to stimulation of the whiskers

Subject: unresponsive to tactile stimuli [MP:0001491]
Value: absence of reflex action normally induced by touch or pain

Subject: abnormal pilomotor reflex [MP:0001492]
Value: anomaly in the involuntary bristling of hairs that occurs when an organism is cold or experiences strong emotions such as fear or awe

Subject: audiogenic seizures [MP:0001496]
Value: a reflex seizure triggered by loud noises

Subject: abnormal kindling response [MP:0001499]
Value: any anomaly in the long-lasting epileptogenic changes normally induced by daily sub threshold electrical brain stimulation, often used as an induced model for epilepsy

Subject: reduced kindling response [MP:0001500]
Value: fewer epileptogenic changes normally induced by daily sub threshold electrical brain stimulation

Subject: abnormal sleep pattern [MP:0001501]
Value: deviation from the normal wake/sleep cycle

Subject: obsolete abnormal circadian rhythm [MP:0001502]
Value: deviation from the normal 24 hour biological activity cycle

Subject: abnormal posture [MP:0001504]
Value: atypical intentionally or habitually assumed position of the limbs or carriage of the body

Subject: hunched posture [MP:0001505]
Value: stooped low with the limbs pulled in close to the body and arched back

Subject: limp posture [MP:0001506]
Value: lack of rigidity of the carriage of the body

Subject: abnormal coat appearance [MP:0001510]
Value: anomaly in the visual aspect of the coat or hair

Subject: disheveled coat [MP:0001511]
Value: coat that looks generally unkempt

Subject: trunk curl [MP:0001512]
Value: posture of the trunk in a curled position

Subject: limb grasping [MP:0001513]
Value: mice clasp front and/or hind feet almost immediately upon being lifted by tail

Subject: abnormal grip strength [MP:0001515]
Value: altered ability to grasp and hold objects, often measured as time spent hanging from an object or wire

Subject: abnormal motor coordination/balance [MP:0001516]
Value: altered ability of an animal to maintain skillful and effective interaction of movements or maintenance of equilibrium

Subject: impaired swimming [MP:0001522]
Value: reduced ability or inability to swim

Subject: impaired righting response [MP:0001523]
Value: reduced ability or greater amount of time needed to recover from an unnatural position to a normal position and/or to resist any force acting to place an organism into a false position

Subject: impaired limb coordination [MP:0001524]
Value: reduced ability to organize limb movements to execute complex maneuvers, such as walking

Subject: impaired balance [MP:0001525]
Value: reduced ability of an animal to maintain equilibrium

Subject: abnormal placing response [MP:0001526]
Value: altered ability to stretch and lift the forelimbs and head to grab a close edge

Subject: athetotic walking movements [MP:0001527]
Value: characterized by slow, writhing involuntary movements of flexion, extension, pronation and supination of the paws and toes

Subject: abnormal vocalization [MP:0001529]
Value: an inability, decreased ability or altered ability to produce sound from the vocal organs; or a general increase or decrease in the production of vocal sound

Subject: abnormal skeleton physiology [MP:0001533]
Value: any functional anomaly of the bony framework of the body

Subject: decreased caudal vertebrae number [MP:0001539]
Value: reduced number of the bony segments of the tail or tail remnant

Subject: abnormal osteoclast physiology [MP:0001541]
Value: any functional anomaly of the specialized phagocytic cells associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue

Subject: abnormal bone strength [MP:0001542]
Value: change in the ability of bone to endure the application of force without yielding or breaking

Subject: abnormal cardiovascular system physiology [MP:0001544]
Value: any functional anomaly of the heart or vascular tissue

Subject: abnormal hematopoietic system physiology [MP:0001545]
Value: any functional anomaly of the fluid and/or its suspended elements that circulate(s) through the heart, arteries, capillaries, and veins

Subject: abnormal lipid level [MP:0001547]
Value: any anomaly in the concentrations of fat-soluble substances (molecules composed of carbon and hydrogen and are characteristically insoluble in water) in the body

Subject: hyperlipidemia [MP:0001548]
Value: abnormally high concentration of lipids in the circulating blood

Subject: increased circulating triglyceride level [MP:0001552]
Value: greater concentration of naturally occurring esters of three fatty acids and glycerol in the blood; triglycerides are widespread in adipose tissue, commonly circulate in the blood in the form of lipoproteins, and are involved in the process of bidirectional transference of adipose fat and blood glucose with the liver

Subject: abnormal circulating free fatty acids level [MP:0001553]
Value: any anomaly in the blood concentrations of the fatty acids which occur in plasma as a result of lipolysis in adipose tissue or when plasma triacyglycerols are taken into tissues

Subject: increased circulating free fatty acid level [MP:0001554]
Value: higher than normal levels of the fatty acids which occur in plasma as a result of lipolysis in adipose tissue or when plasma triacyglycerols are taken into tissues

Subject: increased circulating HDL cholesterol level [MP:0001556]
Value: higher amount in the blood of the small lipoprotein:cholesterol complex that transports cholesterol out of the arteries and to the liver for reprocessing or excretion

Subject: hyperglycemia [MP:0001559]
Value: abnormally high concentration of glucose in the blood; generally refers to a pathological state

Subject: abnormal circulating insulin level [MP:0001560]
Value: any anomaly in the blood concentration of the polypeptide hormone, secreted by beta cells of the pancreas, that promotes glucose utilization, protein synthesis, and the formation and storage of neutral lipids

Subject: abnormal circulating calcium level [MP:0001562]
Value: any anomaly in the concentration of calcium in the blood

Subject: abnormal circulating phosphate level [MP:0001565]
Value: any anomaly in the blood concentrations of the salt or ester of phosphoric acid

Subject: increased circulating phosphate level [MP:0001566]
Value: abnormally high concentrations of phosphates in the circulating blood

Subject: abnormal circulating bilirubin level [MP:0001569]
Value: any anomaly in the concentration in the blood of the bile pigment bilirubin, normally found in the liver and in red blood cells

Subject: abnormal circulating enzyme level [MP:0001570]
Value: aberrant concentration in the blood of any of the proteins that act as catalysts for biological reactions

Subject: abnormal circulating alanine transaminase level [MP:0001573]
Value: aberrant concentration in the blood of the enzyme which transfers amino groups from l-alanine to 2-ketoglutarate, or the reverse (from l-glutamate to pyruvate); serum concentration is increased in viral hepatitis and myocardial infarction

Subject: abnormal oxygen level [MP:0001574]
Value: any anomaly in the concentration of the gaseous element that is essential for animal and plant life

Subject: cyanosis [MP:0001575]
Value: a dark bluish or purple skin discoloration resulting from deficient oxygenation of the blood

Subject: anemia [MP:0001577]
Value: less than normal levels of red blood cells and/or hemoglobin within red blood cells, or volume of packed red blood cells in the bloodstream, resulting in insufficient oxygenation of tissues and organs

Subject: hemolytic anemia [MP:0001585]
Value: deficiency of red cells resulting from an increased rate of erythrocyte destruction

Subject: abnormal erythrocyte cell number [MP:0001586]
Value: altered number of the cells that transport oxygen, red blood cells, per unit

Subject: abnormal hemoglobin [MP:0001588]
Value: defects in the levels or the function of the oxygen-carrying protein of erythrocytes

Subject: abnormal mean corpuscular hemoglobin [MP:0001589]
Value: anomalies in the average levels of hemoglobin contained in an erythrocyte

Subject: hypotension [MP:0001596]
Value: sustained low blood pressure at a level that is likely to result in cardiovascular disease and/or other pathological states

Subject: abnormal blood viscosity [MP:0001598]
Value: anomaly in the resistance to flow of the blood through the vessels

Subject: abnormal blood volume [MP:0001599]
Value: any anomaly in the amount of space occupied by the blood in the vessels

Subject: abnormal myelopoiesis [MP:0001601]
Value: anomaly in the process of, or atypical formation of myeloid cells from the pluripotent hematopoietic stem cells in the bone marrow from myeloid stem cells, including the production of leukocytes in blood, such as monocytes and granulocytes and precursor cells for macrophage and dendritic cells found in the lymphoid tissue

Subject: impaired myelopoiesis [MP:0001602]
Value: atypical process of bone marrow cell formation and/or the formation of bone marrow-derived blood cells with the result of fewer of these cells being formed

Subject: failure of myelopoiesis [MP:0001603]
Value: missing the process of bone marrow cell formation and/or the formation of bone marrow-derived blood cells

Subject: impaired hematopoiesis [MP:0001606]
Value: atypical process of blood cell formation with the result of fewer of these cells being formed

Subject: abnormal vasodilation [MP:0001613]
Value: anomaly in the physiological widening of the lumen of the blood vessels by relaxing the underlying vascular smooth muscle

Subject: abnormal blood vessel morphology [MP:0001614]
Value: any structural anomaly of the network of tubes that carries blood through the body

Subject: abnormal vascular permeability [MP:0001619]
Value: anomaly in the ability of the blood vessels to permit the passage of substances such as fluid, heat, or gases

Subject: abnormal vasculogenesis [MP:0001622]
Value: aberrant process of the initial establishment of the vascular network

Subject: cardiac hypertrophy [MP:0001625]
Value: an increase in size of the cardiac tissue, not due to increased cell number

Subject: abnormal cardiac output [MP:0001627]
Value: anomaly in the blood volume pumped by each ventricle per minute (stroke volume x heart rate)

Subject: abnormal heart rate [MP:0001629]
Value: greater than or fewer than average resting heart beats per minute, usually measured by the number of times the heart ventricles contract per unit of time, usually per minute

Subject: poor circulation [MP:0001633]
Value: insufficient movement of blood throughout the body, often manifesting in cold and/or pale skin

Subject: internal hemorrhage [MP:0001634]
Value: blood loss in the interior of the body due to vessel rupture or dysmorphology

Subject: irregular heartbeat [MP:0001636]
Value: uneven timing of heart contraction

Subject: abnormal apoptosis [MP:0001648]
Value: excessive or absent cell death in a particular tissue or cell type

Subject: abnormal mandibular symphysis morphology [MP:0001649]
Value: any structural anomaly of the fibrocartilagenous union of the two halves of the mandible (embryonic stages)

Subject: abnormal seizure response to electrical stimulation [MP:0001650]

Subject: absent mesoderm [MP:0001683]

Subject: absent vitelline blood vessels [MP:0001719]

Subject: absent visceral yolk sac blood islands [MP:0001721]

Subject: pale yolk sac [MP:0001722]

Subject: disorganized yolk sac vascular plexus [MP:0001723]

Subject: abnormal extraembryonic endoderm formation [MP:0001724]

Subject: abnormal umbilical cord morphology [MP:0001725]

Subject: abnormal allantois morphology [MP:0001726]

Subject: abnormal embryo implantation [MP:0001727]

Subject: impaired embryo implantation [MP:0001729]

Subject: abnormal spermiogenesis [MP:0001932]

Subject: increased litter size [MP:0001934]

Subject: decreased litter size [MP:0001935]

Subject: abnormal sexual maturation [MP:0001937]

Subject: delayed sexual maturation [MP:0001938]

Subject: abnormal lung volume [MP:0001942]

Subject: abnormal respiration [MP:0001943]

Subject: vesicoureteral reflux [MP:0001948]

Subject: abnormal respiratory sounds [MP:0001950]

Subject: abnormal breathing pattern [MP:0001951]

Subject: increased airway responsiveness [MP:0001952]
Value: more easily provoked into bronchoconstriction in bronchial provocation tests

Subject: respiratory failure [MP:0001953]
Value: cessation of or failure to commence breathing

Subject: respiratory distress [MP:0001954]

Subject: hypopnea [MP:0001956]

Subject: apnea [MP:0001957]

Subject: emphysema [MP:0001958]

Subject: abnormal reflex [MP:0001961]
Value: anomaly in an involuntary response to a peripheral stimulus

Subject: abnormal hearing physiology [MP:0001963]

Subject: deafness [MP:0001967]

Subject: abnormal touch/ nociception [MP:0001968]

Subject: abnormal pain threshold [MP:0001970]
