Subject: increased thermal nociceptive threshold [MP:0001973]
Value: a greater than average point at which thermal pain sensation is first detectable

Subject: abnormal chemically-elicited antinociception [MP:0001980]
Value: change in the analgesic effect of chemical substances

Subject: increased chemically-elicited antinociception [MP:0001981]
Value: greater than the normal analgesic effect of chemical substances

Subject: decreased chemically-elicited antinociception [MP:0001982]
Value: less than the normal analgesic effect of chemical substances

Subject: abnormal olfactory system physiology [MP:0001983]
Value: any functional anomaly of the system relating to smell

Subject: abnormal olfaction [MP:0001984]
Value: anomaly in the ability to smell

Subject: abnormal gustatory system physiology [MP:0001985]
Value: any functional anomaly in the perception of taste

Subject: abnormal taste sensitivity [MP:0001986]
Value: changes in the ability to perceive a particular flavor or suggestion of something imparting a flavor by the chemoreceptors of the gustatory system

Subject: alcohol preference [MP:0001987]
Value: predilection to ingest alcohol over other substances

Subject: cocaine preference [MP:0001988]
Value: predilection to ingest cocaine over other substances

Subject: abnormal blinking [MP:0001993]
Value: anomaly in the normal reflex of closing the eyes frequently and rapidly

Subject: increased blinking frequency [MP:0001994]
Value: greater number of occurrences of the normal reflex of closing the eyes frequently and rapidly

Subject: decreased blinking frequency [MP:0001995]
Value: reduced number of occurrences of the normal reflex of closing the eyes frequently and rapidly

Subject: photosensitivity [MP:0001999]
Value: alterations in the response to sunlight or UV irradiation, especially sensitivity of the eyes

Subject: blindness [MP:0002001]
Value: loss of the sense of sight

Subject: miotic pupils [MP:0002003]
Value: contraction of the pupils

Subject: neoplasm [MP:0002006]
Value: the observable morphological and physiological characteristics of  a benign or malignant tissue growth resulting from uncontrolled cell proliferation in a mammalian organism that are manifested through development and lifespan

Subject: increased cellular sensitivity to gamma-irradiation [MP:0002007]
Value: increased incidence of cell death following exposure to gamma-irradiation

Subject: preneoplasia [MP:0002009]
Value: state preceding the pathological process resulting in a neoplasm; does not necessarily imply cancerous development

Subject: increased trichofolliculoma incidence [MP:0002012]
Value: greater than the expected number of dome-shaped hamartoma tumors which contain multiple abortive and/or misaligned hair follicles

Subject: increased pilomatricoma incidence [MP:0002013]
Value: greater than the expected number of neoplasms that arise from hair matrix cells occurring in a specific population in a given time period; pilomatricoma is an encapsulated tumor containing irregularly shaped, lobules of cells separated by fibrovascular connective tissue stroma; two distinct cell populations comprise this tumor, basaloid cells with scant cytoplasm located towards the periphery and the ghost (or shadow) cells occupying the central portion

Subject: increased papilloma incidence [MP:0002014]
Value: greater than the expected number of benign tumors consisting of villous or arborescent outgrowths of fibrovascular stroma covered by neoplastic epithelial cells occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: epithelioid cysts [MP:0002015]
Value: abnormal membranous sacs appearing in an epithelium

Subject: ovary cysts [MP:0002016]
Value: the appearance of fluid-filled sacs within the ovary

Subject: increased malignant tumor incidence [MP:0002018]
Value: higher than normal incidence of locally invasive, destructive and metastatic tumors

Subject: abnormal tumor incidence [MP:0002019]
Value: deviation from the expected number of abnormal growths in a specific population

Subject: increased tumor incidence [MP:0002020]
Value: greater than the expected number of neoplasms in a specific population in a given time period, usually of a specific type

Subject: increased incidence of induced tumors [MP:0002021]
Value: higher than normal frequency of tumor incidence induced by a carcinogen, mutagen or virus

Subject: increased B cell derived lymphoma incidence [MP:0002023]
Value: higher than normal incidence of heterogeneous lymphoid tumors generally expressing one or more B-cell antigens or representing malignant transformations of B-lymphocytes

Subject: increased T cell derived lymphoma incidence [MP:0002024]
Value: higher than normal incidence of a group of heterogeneous lymphoid tumors representing malignant transformations of T-lymphocytes

Subject: increased leukemia incidence [MP:0002026]
Value: higher than normal incidence of a cancer characterized by progressive proliferation of abnormal leukocytes in hematopoietic tissues, organs and blood

Subject: increased lung adenocarcinoma incidence [MP:0002027]
Value: greater than the expected number of a malignant neoplasm of epithelial cells in the lung, usually with a glandular organization, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased neurofibrosarcoma incidence [MP:0002030]
Value: greater than the expected number of a highly aggressive malignant neoplasm arising from the fibrous connective tissue surrounding peripheral nerves, in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased adrenal gland tumor incidence [MP:0002031]
Value: greater than the expected number of neoplams in the adrenal gland occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased sarcoma incidence [MP:0002032]
Value: greater than the expected number of a connective tissue neoplasm associated with the proliferation of embryonically-derived mesodermal cells, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased malignant triton tumor incidence [MP:0002033]
Value: greater than the expected number of a malignant tumor with neurogenic and myogenic differentiation, occurring in a specific population in a given time period; usually arises in tissues of neural crest origin

Subject: increased leiomyosarcoma incidence [MP:0002035]
Value: greater than the expected number of a malignant tumor derived from smooth (nonstriated) muscle, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased rhabdomyosarcoma incidence [MP:0002036]
Value: greater than the expected number of a malignant tumor derived from skeletal (striated) muscle, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased fibrohistocytoma incidence [MP:0002037]
Value: greater than the expected number of slowly growing skin nodules derived from cellular fibrous tissue occurring in a specific population in a given time period; these often surround capillaries

Subject: increased carcinoma incidence [MP:0002038]
Value: greater than the expected number of any of a variety of malignant neoplasms arising from epithelial cells, occurring in a specific population in a given time period; carcinomas are usually glandular or squamous in origin

Subject: increased neuroblastoma incidence [MP:0002039]
Value: greater than the expected number of a malignant neoplasm characterized by immature nerve cells of embryonic type, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased pituitary adenoma incidence [MP:0002041]
Value: greater than the expected number of benign neoplasms of the pituitary, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased colon hamartoma incidence [MP:0002043]
Value: greater than the expected number of benign focal malformations in the colon in a specific population in a given time period; results from faulty colonic development, and is composed of an abnormal mixture of tissue elements, or an abnormal proportion of a single element normally present at that site

Subject: increased colon adenoma incidence [MP:0002044]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign epithelial neoplasm with a glandular organization arising in the colon, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased renal cystadenoma incidence [MP:0002045]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign epithelial neoplasm with a glandular organization and a cyst-like appearance arising in the kidney, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased hepatic hemangioma incidence [MP:0002047]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign tumor characterized by blood-filled spaces lined by benign endothelial cells in the liver, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased lung adenoma incidence [MP:0002048]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign epithelial neoplasm with a glandular organization arising in the lung, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased extremity angiosarcoma incidence [MP:0002049]
Value: higher than normal incidence of malignant neoplasm of soft tissues; thought to arise from endothelial cells of blood vessels

Subject: increased pheochromocytoma incidence [MP:0002050]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign neoplasm derived from adrenal medullary cells, occurring in a specific population in a given time period; usually associated with hypertension

Subject: increased skin papilloma incidence [MP:0002051]
Value: greater than the expected number of a circumscribed, benign epithelial tumor projecting from the surrounding surface, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: decreased tumor incidence [MP:0002052]
Value: less than the expected number of neoplasms in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: decreased incidence of induced tumors [MP:0002053]
Value: reduced frequency of tumor incidence induced by a carcinogen, mutagen or virus

Subject: neonatal lethality [MP:0002058]
Value: death within the neonatal period after birth (Mus: P0)

Subject: abnormal seminal vesicle morphology [MP:0002059]
Value: any structural anomaly of either of the paired sac-like glandular structures situated posterolateral to the urinary bladder in the male and functioning as part of the reproductive system; each sac is pyramidal in shape and convoluted in appearance and at the anterior extremity becomes constricted into a narrow straight duct that joins the ipsilateral vas deferens to form the ejaculatory duct; seminal vesicles secrete seminal fluid and nourish and promote the movement of spermatozoa through the urethra

Subject: abnormal skin morphology [MP:0002060]
Value: any structural anomaly of the membranous protective covering of the body

Subject: abnormal aggression-related behavior [MP:0002061]
Value: domineering, assaultive or forceful physical action

Subject: abnormal associative learning [MP:0002062]
Value: anomaly in the ability to change the frequency or form of a behavior as a result of the influence of the environment

Subject: abnormal learning/memory/conditioning [MP:0002063]
Value: altered ability to receive, store, process or recall informational stimuli

Subject: seizures [MP:0002064]
Value: sudden and often acute manifestation of epileptic attack, sometimes convulsive

Subject: abnormal fear/anxiety-related behavior [MP:0002065]
Value: altered response in tests for fear or anxiety related behaviors

Subject: abnormal motor capabilities/coordination/movement [MP:0002066]
Value: altered ability to coordinate voluntary movement or repetitive, compulsive movements

Subject: abnormal sensory capabilities/reflexes/nociception [MP:0002067]
Value: inability or altered ability to respond to a sensory stimulus

Subject: abnormal parental behavior [MP:0002068]
Value: altered behavior of animals that affects the ability of offspring to survive

Subject: abnormal consumption behavior [MP:0002069]
Value: altered ability or inability to eat or drink, or unusual choice or avoidance of foods or drink

Subject: abnormal hair growth [MP:0002073]
Value: absence or reduced amount of hair or abnormal onset of hair growth cycle or development, or abnormal hair pattern

Subject: abnormal hair texture [MP:0002074]
Value: irregular or unusual appearance of the structure of the hair

Subject: abnormal coat/hair pigmentation [MP:0002075]
Value: irregular or unusual pigmentation of the hair

Subject: abnormal glucose homeostasis [MP:0002078]
Value: anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of glucose in the fluids and tissues

Subject: increased circulating insulin level [MP:0002079]
Value: greater than normal levels of insulin in blood

Subject: prenatal lethality [MP:0002080]
Value: death anytime between fertilization and birth (Mus: approximately E18.5)

Subject: perinatal lethality [MP:0002081]
Value: death anytime within the perinatal period (Mus: E18.5 through postnatal day 1)

Subject: postnatal lethality [MP:0002082]
Value: premature death anytime between the neonatal period and weaning age (Mus: P1 to approximately 3 weeks of age)

Subject: premature death [MP:0002083]
Value: death after weaning age, but before the normal life span (Mus: after 3 weeks of age)

Subject: abnormal developmental patterning [MP:0002084]
Value: abnormal systematic arrangement of the developing body along an axis

Subject: abnormal embryonic tissue morphology [MP:0002085]
Value: any structural anomaly of the embryonic tissue part of the whole embryo

Subject: abnormal extraembryonic tissue morphology [MP:0002086]
Value: any structural anomaly of the membranes involved with embryonic protection and nutrition

Subject: abnormal embryonic growth/weight/body size [MP:0002088]
Value: limited or accelerated growth or development apparent during the embryonic period (sensu Mus: up to E14, or the completion of organogenesis)

Subject: abnormal postnatal growth/weight/body size [MP:0002089]
Value: increased or decreased average body size, weight or growth characteristic abnormalities manifesting after birth

Subject: abnormal vision [MP:0002090]
Value: inability or decreased ability to see

Subject: abnormal eye morphology [MP:0002092]
Value: any structural anomaly of the spheroid organ and optic nerve that serves to detect light

Subject: abnormal skin pigmentation [MP:0002095]
Value: anomaly in the coloration of the skin due to changes in the amount, shape, or distribution of cells producing pigment

Subject: abnormal vibrissa morphology [MP:0002098]
Value: any structural anomaly of the stiff hairs projecting from the face around the nose of most mammals which act as touch receptors

Subject: abnormal tooth morphology [MP:0002100]
Value: any anomaly in the size, shape or structure of the hard or soft tissues of the skeletal element within the mouth that is composed of dentine and used to procure or masticate food

Subject: abnormal ear morphology [MP:0002102]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the structures involved in the ear or vestibular system

Subject: abnormal muscle physiology [MP:0002106]
Value: any functional anomaly of the muscle, not due to an anatomical defect

Subject: abnormal muscle morphology [MP:0002108]
Value: any structural anomaly of the contractile tissue that produces movement in animals

Subject: abnormal limb morphology [MP:0002109]
Value: any structural anomaly of the projecting paired appendages of an animal trunk, used in particular for movement and grasping; usually denotes the arm and/or legs in mammalian species

Subject: abnormal digit morphology [MP:0002110]
Value: any structural anomaly of the fingers or toes

Subject: abnormal tail morphology [MP:0002111]
Value: any structural anomaly of the flexible elongated appendage located at the caudal end of the torso in many species; it is usually continuous with the vertebral column

Subject: abnormal skeleton development [MP:0002113]
Value: any anomaly in the formation of bone tissue

Subject: abnormal axial skeleton morphology [MP:0002114]
Value: any structural anomaly of the articulated bones of the cranium and vertebral column

Subject: abnormal limb bone morphology [MP:0002115]
Value: any structural anomaly of the limb or autopod bones

Subject: abnormal craniofacial bone morphology [MP:0002116]
Value: any structural anomaly of the cranial or facial bones

Subject: abnormal lipid homeostasis [MP:0002118]
Value: anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of lipids in the fluids and tissues

Subject: dipsosis [MP:0002119]
Value: excessive desire to drink, or to drink unusual fluids

Subject: abnormal definitive hematopoiesis [MP:0002123]
Value: abnormal development of blood cells in the fetal and adult organism; in the fetus cells develop in the aorta, genital ridge and mesonephros region and later in the liver; in adults cells normally develop in the bone marrow and lymphatic tissues

Subject: abnormal cardiovascular system morphology [MP:0002127]
Value: any structural anomaly of the heart or vascular tissue

Subject: abnormal blood circulation [MP:0002128]
Value: failure or atypical movement in the flow of blood from the heart to the vasculature and back to the heart

Subject: abnormal respiratory system morphology [MP:0002132]
Value: any structural anomaly of pulmonary tissues

Subject: abnormal respiratory system physiology [MP:0002133]
Value: any functional anomaly of the pulmonary system; inability or reduced ability to intake and exchange oxygen and carbon dioxide with the environment

Subject: abnormal kidney morphology [MP:0002135]
Value: any structural anomaly of either of the two excretory organs that filter wastes (especially urea) from the blood and excrete them and water in urine

Subject: abnormal kidney physiology [MP:0002136]
Value: any functional anomaly and/or activity of either of the two excretory organs that filter wastes (especially urea) from the blood and excrete them and water in urine

Subject: abnormal hepatobiliary system morphology [MP:0002138]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the tissues of the liver or biliary system

Subject: abnormal hepatobiliary system physiology [MP:0002139]
Value: any functional anomaly of the tissues of the liver or biliary system

Subject: abnormal B cell differentiation [MP:0002144]
Value: atypical production of or inability to produce mature B cells, and/or accumulation of B cell precursors

Subject: abnormal T cell differentiation [MP:0002145]
Value: atypical production of or inability to produce mature T cells, and/or accumulation of T cell precursors

Subject: abnormal hypersensitivity reaction [MP:0002148]
Value: immune response that results in tissue injury

Subject: abnormal neural tube morphology [MP:0002151]
Value: any structural anomaly of the hollow epithelial tube found on the dorsal side of the vertebrate embryo that develops into the central nervous system (i.e. brain and spinal cord)

Subject: abnormal brain morphology [MP:0002152]
Value: any structural anomaly of the brain, one of the two components of the central nervous system and the center of thought and emotion; controls coordination, bodily activities and the interpretation of information from the senses (sight, hearing, smell, etc.)

Subject: abnormal reproductive system morphology [MP:0002160]
Value: structural or developmental anomaly of any of the tissues involved in the reproductive system

Subject: abnormal fertility/fecundity [MP:0002161]
Value: anomaly in the reproductive capability of an organism or population to produce live offspring

Subject: abnormal gland morphology [MP:0002163]
Value: any structural anomaly of an organ that functions as a secretory or excretory organ

Subject: abnormal gland physiology [MP:0002164]
Value: any functional anomaly of an organ that functions as a secretory or excretory organ

Subject: altered tumor susceptibility [MP:0002166]
Value: greater than or less than the average number of tumors, usually a specific type, arising in a given organism when compared to controls

Subject: obsolete other aberrant phenotype [MP:0002168]
Value: anomaly or dysmorphology not attributable to any other category

Subject: no abnormal phenotype detected [MP:0002169]
Value: normal viability, fertility, appearance and behavior; reported phenotype is indistinguishable from controls

Subject: abnormal gastrulation movements [MP:0002174]
Value: failure of embryonic cells to migrate, or migrate to the appropriate target during the development and invagination of the primary germ layers

Subject: decreased brain weight [MP:0002175]
Value: lower than average weight of the brain

Subject: increased brain weight [MP:0002176]
Value: greater than average weight of the brain

Subject: abnormal outer ear morphology [MP:0002177]
Value: any structural anomaly of any components of the auricles or external acoustic meatus

Subject: abnormal astrocyte morphology [MP:0002182]
Value: any structural anomaly of the large neuroglial (macroglial) cells in the central nervous system - the largest and most numerous neuroglial cells in the brain and spinal cord; astrocytes are irregularly shaped with many long processes, including those with 'end feet' which form the glial (limiting) membrane and directly and indirectly contribute to the blood-brain barrier; astrocytes regulate the extracellular ionic and chemical environment, and 'reactive astrocytes' (along with microglia) respond to injury

Subject: gliosis [MP:0002183]
Value: increased growth pattern of neuroglia in a damaged area of the brain or spinal cord

Subject: abnormal innervation [MP:0002184]
Value: the malformation, misprojection, abnormal fasciculation or abnormal refinement of the connection, of nerve fibers to a target

Subject: abnormal fibula morphology [MP:0002187]
Value: any structural anomaly of the lateral and smaller bone of the lower limb

Subject: small heart [MP:0002188]
Value: reduced size of the heart relative to average

Subject: abnormal myocardial trabeculae morphology [MP:0002189]
Value: any structural anomaly of the supporting bundles of muscular fibers lining the walls of the heart

Subject: disorganized myocardium [MP:0002190]
Value: derangement of the pattern cardiac muscle layers

Subject: abnormal artery morphology [MP:0002191]
Value: any structural anomaly of the blood vessels that carry blood away from the heart

Subject: hydrops fetalis [MP:0002192]
Value: an abnormal accumulation of serous fluid in fetal tissues

Subject: minimal clonic seizures [MP:0002193]
Value: seizures involving rhythmic face and forelimb clonus including arm movement, and it may include rearing and falling and ventral flexion of the neck; a seizure is scored as minimal when it satisfies the minimal criteria up to or including ventral flexion, but does not include maximal tonic hindlimb extension

Subject: maximal tonic hindlimb extension seizures [MP:0002194]
Value: seizures induced by electrical stimulation of the brainstem; manifesting as a tonic-clonic flexion/extension sequence, starting in tonic extension of the forelimbs and terminating in a full tonic hindlimb extension, which is defined when the angle of the hindlimbs to the torso exceeds 90 degrees (although it is usually 180 degrees)

Subject: psychomotor seizures [MP:0002195]
Value: low frequency, tetanic stimulation used to evoke partial limbic seizures, with currents ranging from 8 mA to 20 mA, depending on the strain and gender; manifesting as rhythmic face movements and extensive forelimb clonus (e.g. shadow-boxing forelimb movements), dorsal flexion of the neck, rearing and falling, and/or transient wobbliness/ataxia; seizure lasts only 10-15 seconds and when antiepileptic drugs are present may last only a few seconds

Subject: absent corpus callosum [MP:0002196]
Value: absence of the commissural plate interconnecting the cortical hemispheres of the brain

Subject: abnormal brain commissure morphology [MP:0002199]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the nerve fiber tracts that span the longitudinal fissure between the cerebral and/or cerebellar hemispheres of the brain

Subject: abnormal brain ventricular system morphology [MP:0002200]
Value: any structural anomaly of the brain ventricles, their associated choroid plexuses or the intercommunicating channels that connect the ventricular system

Subject: abnormal neurotransmitter level [MP:0002204]
Value: anomaly in the amount of endogenous signaling molecules into a synaptic cleft; neurotransmitters are released on excitation from the axon terminal of a presynaptic neuron of the central or peripheral nervous system and travel across the synaptic cleft to either excite or inhibit the target cell

Subject: abnormal CNS synaptic transmission [MP:0002206]
Value: defect in the communication from a neuron to a target across a synapse in the central nervous system

Subject: abnormal long term potentiation [MP:0002207]
Value: alterations in a persistent robust synaptic response induced by synchronous stimulation of pre- and postsynaptic cells

Subject: abnormal germ cell morphology [MP:0002208]
Value: any structural anomaly of the germ cell, that is, any of the reproductive (generative) cells of a multicellular organism, whether they are undifferentiated or fully differentiated

Subject: decreased germ cell number [MP:0002209]
Value: reduced numbers of any of the reproductive (generative) cells of a multicellular organism, whether they are undifferentiated or fully differentiated

Subject: abnormal sex determination [MP:0002210]
Value: anomaly of primary or secondary sexual development or characteristics

Subject: abnormal primary sex determination [MP:0002211]
Value: aberrant gonadal development resulting in either abnormal or absent gonads or the development of gonads inconsistent with the chromosomal sex

Subject: abnormal secondary sex determination [MP:0002212]
Value: gonadal development may or may not be normal, and the phenotype of the animal outside the gonad does not match chromosomal sex or is ambiguous

Subject: true hermaphroditism [MP:0002213]
Value: the presence of both unequivocal ovarian tissue and testicular elements in the same individual regardless of karyotype; these two tissue types may be present in the same gonad (ovotestis) or may be present as separate ovaries and testis tissue elements in the same individual regardless of sex chromosome complement

Subject: streak gonad [MP:0002214]
Value: impairment of genital ridge development; aplasia of gonadal tissue which is sometimes replaced with functionless tissue

Subject: abnormal seminiferous tubule morphology [MP:0002216]
Value: any structural anomaly of the tubules in the testes where spermatogenesis occurs

Subject: small lymph nodes [MP:0002217]
Value: lymph nodes of decreased size

Subject: increased lymph node number [MP:0002218]
Value: greater than the normal number of lymph nodes

Subject: decreased lymph node number [MP:0002219]
Value: fewer than the normal number of lymph nodes

Subject: large lymphoid organs [MP:0002220]
Value: increased size of lymphatic tissues

Subject: abnormal lymph organ size [MP:0002221]
Value: change in the normal size of lymphatic tissues

Subject: lymphoid hypoplasia [MP:0002223]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced cell number, in lymphatic tissue

Subject: abnormal spleen size [MP:0002224]
Value: deviation from the normal spleen size

Subject: abnormal spleen capsule morphology [MP:0002227]
Value: any structural anomaly of the connective tissue that surrounds the spleen

Subject: abnormal spleen trabecular vein morphology [MP:0002228]
Value: any structural anomaly of one of the veins that feed the splenic vein

Subject: neurodegeneration [MP:0002229]
Value: a retrogressive impairment of function or destruction of neural tissue

Subject: abnormal primitive streak formation [MP:0002230]
Value: anomaly in the establishment of the midline ridge of embryonic epiblast that later develops into mesoderm and endoderm

Subject: abnormal primitive streak morphology [MP:0002231]
Value: anomaly in the midline ridge of the embryonic epiblast that later develops into mesoderm and endoderm

Subject: abnormal nose morphology [MP:0002233]
Value: any structural anomaly of the organ that is specialized for smell and is part of the respiratory system

Subject: abnormal pharynx morphology [MP:0002234]
Value: any structural anomaly in the passage between the mouth and the posterior nares and the larynx and esophagus

Subject: abnormal external nares morphology [MP:0002235]
Value: any structural anomaly of the anterior opening to the nasal cavity

Subject: abnormal internal nares morphology [MP:0002236]
Value: any structural anomaly of the portion of the opening of the nasal cavity into the nasal pharynx

Subject: abnormal nasal cavity morphology [MP:0002237]
Value: any structural anomaly of the cavity of the respiratory tract that extends from the nares to the pharynx; the nasal cavity is lined with ciliated mucosa

Subject: abnormal nasal mucosa morphology [MP:0002238]
Value: any structural anomaly of the mucous membrane that lines the nasal cavity

Subject: abnormal nasal septum morphology [MP:0002239]
Value: any structural anomaly of the dividing wall that runs down the midline of the nose separating the two nasal cavities, each of which ends in a nostril; it is formed by the septal nasal cartilage, parts of skull bones (ethmoid bone; vomer), and membranous parts

Subject: abnormal paranasal sinus morphology [MP:0002240]
Value: any structural anomaly of the paired air-filled cavities surrounded by the bones of the face that are lined by mucous membranes and are continuous with the nasal cavity

Subject: abnormal laryngeal mucosa goblet cell morphology [MP:0002241]
Value: any structural anomaly of the epithelial cells lining the larynx, which produce mucins

Subject: abnormal olfactory mucosa morphology [MP:0002242]
Value: any structural anomaly of the portion of the nasal mucosa that contains the olfactory sensory endings

Subject: abnormal vomeronasal organ morphology [MP:0002243]
Value: any structural anomaly of the tubular, crescent-sensory organ with a luminal epithelium that contains chemosensitive receptor cells with microvilli that are thought to detect pheromones and transmit signals to the remainder of the accessory olfactory system; the organ lies at the base the nasal cavity and is split into two, separated by the nasal septum

Subject: abnormal turbinate morphology [MP:0002244]
Value: any structural anomaly of the small curved bones that extends horizontally along the lateral wall of the nasal passage

Subject: abnormal ethmoid sinus morphology [MP:0002245]
Value: any structural anomaly of the evaginations of the mucous membrane of the nasal cavity into the ethmoidal bony labyrinth, forming multiple small paranasal sinuses

Subject: abnormal frontal sinus morphology [MP:0002246]
Value: any structural anomaly of the paired evaginations of the mucous membrane of the nasal cavity into the lower part of the squama of the frontal bones

Subject: abnormal maxillary sinus morphology [MP:0002247]
Value: any structural anomaly of the largest of the paranasal sinuses, a paired pyramid-shaped air sinus located within the maxillary bone which drains via the maxillary ostium into the infundibulum, then through the hiatus semilunaris into the middle meatus of the nose

Subject: abnormal sphenoid sinus morphology [MP:0002248]
Value: any structural anomaly of the most posterior paranasal sinus located in the sphenoid bone near the optic nerve and the pituitary gland on the side of the skull; it drains into the sphenoethmoidal recess superior to the superior concha; the sinus is divided into right and left parts by a bony septum

Subject: abnormal larynx morphology [MP:0002249]

Subject: small vestibular ganglion [MP:0003987]

Subject: disorganized embryonic tissue [MP:0003988]

Subject: abnormal barrel cortex morphology [MP:0003989]
Value: any structural anomaly of the discrete functional units of the somatosensory cortex that processes tactile information derived from the vibrissae

Subject: decreased neurotransmitter release [MP:0003990]

Subject: arteriosclerosis [MP:0003991]
Value: thickening, hardening and/or loss of elasticity of the walls of arteries

Subject: increased mortality induced by ionizing radiation [MP:0003992]

Subject: abnormal ventral spinal root morphology [MP:0003993]

Subject: abnormal dorsal spinal root morphology [MP:0003994]
Value: any structural anomaly of the posterior bundle of nerves emerging from the spinal cord to join with the anterior/ventral nerve bundle at each spinal cord segment to form one of the 31 paired peripheral nerves

Subject: abnormal uterine artery morphology [MP:0003995]
Value: any structural anomaly of the branch of the internal iliac artery that supplies the uterus and the upper part of the vagina

Subject: clonic seizures [MP:0003996]
Value: increased number or decreased threshold for the induction of a seizure characterized by unilateral or bilateral rhythmic jerking movements of the arms and legs caused by alternating contraction and relaxation of muscle

Subject: tonic-clonic seizures [MP:0003997]

Subject: decreased thermal nociceptive threshold [MP:0003998]
Value: a lower than average point at which thermal pain sensation is first detectable

Subject: enhanced passive avoidance behavior [MP:0003999]

Subject: impaired passive avoidance behavior [MP:0004000]

Subject: decreased hepatocyte proliferation [MP:0004001]
Value: reduction in the expansion rate of the hepatocyte cell population by cell division

Subject: abnormal jejunum morphology [MP:0004002]
Value: any structural anomaly of the portion of the small intestine that extends from the duodenum to the ileum

Subject: abnormal vascular endothelial cell physiology [MP:0004003]
Value: anomaly in the function of the cells that line the vasculature

Subject: patent ductus venosus [MP:0004004]
Value: failure of the embryonic connection between the portal vein and inferior vena cava formed by the left umbilical vein (that allows oxygenated blood to bypass the developing liver) to close in adults

Subject: impaired contractility of intestinal smooth muscle [MP:0004005]
Value: inability or reduced ability of intestinal smooth muscle to shorten or to develop increased tension

Subject: impaired contractility of jejunal smooth muscle [MP:0004006]
Value: inability or reduced ability of the jejunal smooth muscle to shorter or to develop increased tension

Subject: abnormal lung vasculature morphology [MP:0004007]
Value: any structural anomaly of the blood vessels of the lung

Subject: abnormal GABA-mediated receptor currents [MP:0004008]
Value: change in the measured amplitude, current density or duration of response to stimulation of GABA receptors

Subject: abnormal diastolic filling velocity [MP:0004009]
Value: anomaly in the rate of fluid inflow to the heart during diastole compared to controls; usually measured in the left ventricle; altered filling velocity often contributes to various cardiovascular disorders

Subject: increased diastolic filling velocity [MP:0004010]
Value: greater rate of fluid inflow to the heart during diastole compared to controls; usually measured in the left ventricle; altered filling velocity often contributes to various cardiovascular disorders

Subject: decreased diastolic filling velocity [MP:0004011]
Value: reduction in the rate of fluid inflow to the heart during diastole compared to controls; usually measured in the left ventricle; altered filling velocity often contributes to various cardiovascular disorders

Subject: increased pulmonary artery pressure [MP:0004012]
Value: increased pulmonary pressure compared to controls

Subject: decreased pulmonary artery pressure [MP:0004013]
Value: reduced pulmonary pressure compared to controls

Subject: abnormal uterine environment [MP:0004014]
Value: anomaly or inability of the uterus to support embryonic development

Subject: abnormal oviduct environment [MP:0004015]
Value: anomaly or inability of the oviduct to support egg viability

Subject: decreased bone mass [MP:0004016]
Value: a reduction in the total amount of bone tissue contained in the skeleton

Subject: duplex kidney [MP:0004017]
Value: a kidney that is split into two separate collecting systems; there may be a duplex ureter or a single ureter; may present unilaterally or bilaterally

Subject: abnormal galactose homeostasis [MP:0004018]
Value: anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of galactose in the fluids and tissues

Subject: abnormal vitamin homeostasis [MP:0004019]
Value: anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of organic substances found in food and are not synthesized by the body and are necessary in trace amounts for normal metabolic function

Subject: polyhydramnios [MP:0004020]
Value: abnormally high amniotic fluid volume; may result from maternal diabetes, chromosomal abnormalities or other congenital abnormalities

Subject: abnormal rod electrophysiology [MP:0004021]
Value: any functional anomaly of dark adapted vision mediated by the rods

Subject: abnormal cone electrophysiology [MP:0004022]
Value: any functional anomaly of light adapted vision mediated by the cones

Subject: abnormal chromosome number [MP:0004023]
Value: chromosome count is other than the expected diploid chromosome number

Subject: aneuploidy [MP:0004024]
Value: chromosome count is not an exact multiple of the haploid number

Subject: polyploidy [MP:0004025]
Value: more than two chromosome sets are present

Subject: monosomy [MP:0004026]
Value: one chromosome missing from an otherwise diploid chromosome set

Subject: trisomy [MP:0004027]
Value: presence of an extra chromosome in an otherwise diploid chromosome set

Subject: chromosome breakage [MP:0004028]

Subject: spontaneous chromosome breakage [MP:0004029]
Value: chromosome breakage due to inherent instability of chromosomes

Subject: induced chromosome breakage [MP:0004030]
Value: chromosome breakage following treatment with a DNA-damaging agent

Subject: insulitis [MP:0004031]
Value: a histological change in the islets of Langerhans characterized by edema and the infiltration of small numbers of white blood cells

Subject: abnormal interventricular groove morphology [MP:0004032]
Value: any structural anomaly of the indentation dividing the two ventricles, comprised of the sulcus interventricularis anterior and the sulcus interventricularis posterior

Subject: supernumerary teeth [MP:0004033]
Value: presence of a supernumerary, i.e., extra, tooth or teeth

Subject: belly blaze [MP:0004034]
Value: the appearance of a stripe or zigzag of white fur on the ventrum

Subject: abnormal sublingual gland morphology [MP:0004035]
Value: any structural anomaly of the small mucin-producing salivary glands in the floor of the mouth beneath the tongue, anterior to the submandibular gland

Subject: abnormal muscle relaxation [MP:0004036]
Value: altered ability of the muscle to lengthen following contractions

Subject: increased muscle relaxation [MP:0004037]
Value: greater than the normal ability of the muscle to lengthen following contractions or increase in the ability of the muscle to lengthen following contractions

Subject: lymphangiectasis [MP:0004038]
Value: dilation of the lymphatic vessels, the basic process that may result in the formation of a lymphangioma

Subject: abnormal cardiac cell glucose uptake [MP:0004039]
Value: anomalous ability of the cells of the heart to take in glucose

Subject: altered susceptibility to kidney reperfusion injury [MP:0004040]
Value: a change in the likelihood or extent of damage to the kidney when the blood supply is restored after a period of ischemia

Subject: increased susceptibility to kidney reperfusion injury [MP:0004041]
Value: an increased likelihood or extent of damage to the kidney when the blood supply is restored after a period of ischemia

Subject: decreased susceptibility to kidney reperfusion injury [MP:0004042]
Value: a diminished likelihood or extent of damage to the kidney when the blood supply is restored after a period of ischemia

Subject: abnormal pH regulation [MP:0004043]
Value: anomaly in the function of the buffer systems of the body in combination with the respiratory and renal systems that control the relative acidity or alkalinity of the body, as measured by the concentration of hydrogen ion

Subject: aortic dissection [MP:0004044]
Value: a pathologic process, characterized by splitting of the media layer of the aorta, which leads to formation of a dissecting aneurysm

Subject: abnormal cell cycle checkpoint function [MP:0004045]
Value: anomaly in the amount of time spent at the points in the cell cycle (end of G1 phase, end of G2 phase, and during metaphase) which prevent the cell from progressing to the next phase when conditions are unfavorable

Subject: abnormal mitosis [MP:0004046]
Value: anomaly in the process of cell division including both division of the nucleus (karyokinesis) and the cytoplasm (cytokinesis)

Subject: abnormal milk composition [MP:0004047]
Value: anomaly in one or more of the constituents of milk including protein, lipid, and/or mineral content or in the appearance of milk

Subject: increased acute promyelocytic leukemia incidence [MP:0004049]
Value: higher than normal incidence of cancer characterized by rapid onset of abnormal leukocyte proliferation, manifesting as a severe bleeding disorder from coagulation abnormalities, and bone marrow infiltration of abnormal promyelocytes and myelocytes

Subject: abnormal synchondrosis [MP:0004053]
Value: anomalous or persistent cartilaginous fusion of two bones

Subject: abnormal periocular mesenchyme morphology [MP:0004054]
Value: any structural anomaly of the mesenchymal cells that give rise to the corneal endothelium, corneal stroma, sclera, iris stroma, ciliary muscle, ciliary stroma, and trabecular meshwork of the eye

Subject: atrium hypoplasia [MP:0004055]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size of one or both of the two upper chambers of the heart, usually due to reduced cell number

Subject: abnormal myocardium compact layer morphology [MP:0004056]
Value: any structural anomaly of the outer, dense layer of the myocardium uniting the epicardium and myocardium

Subject: thin myocardium compact layer [MP:0004057]
Value: reduced thickness of the outer, dense layer of the myocardium

Subject: abnormal ventricle papillary muscle morphology [MP:0004058]
Value: any structural anomaly of one of the group of myocardial bundles which terminate in the chordae tendineae that attach to the cusps of the atrioventricular valves; each ventricle has an anterior and a posterior papillary muscle; the right ventricle sometimes has a septal papillary muscle

Subject: absent papillary muscle [MP:0004060]
Value: absence of one of the group of myocardial bundles which terminate in the chordae tendineae that attach to the cusps of the atrioventricular valves; each ventricle has an anterior and a posterior papillary muscle; the right ventricle sometimes has a septal papillary muscle

Subject: papillary muscle hypoplasia [MP:0004061]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, in the papillary muscle

Subject: dilated heart right atrium [MP:0004062]
Value: the luminal space of the right upper chamber of the heart is increased in volume or area, usually with an increase in contained fluid

Subject: dilated heart left atrium [MP:0004063]
Value: the luminal space of the left upper chamber of the heart is increased in volume or area, usually with an increase in contained fluid

Subject: decreased susceptibility to induced muscular atrophy [MP:0004064]
Value: less than expected wasting of muscle tissue after experimental manipulation (starvation, neurectomy, immobilization, etc)

Subject: increased susceptibility to induced muscular atrophy [MP:0004065]
Value: greater than expected wasting of muscle tissue after experimental manipulation (starvation, neurectomy, immobilization, etc)

Subject: abnormal primitive node morphology [MP:0004066]
Value: any structural anomaly of the regional thickening of cells at the rostral tip of the vertebrate primitive streak through which gastrulating cells migrate anteriorly to form tissues in the future head and neck; this region organizes the formation of the three embryonic layers and establishes the longitudinal axis and the polarity of the embryo

Subject: abnormal trabecula carnea morphology [MP:0004067]
Value: any structural anomaly of the supporting bundles of muscular fibers lining the walls of the ventricles of the heart

Subject: dilated dorsal aorta [MP:0004068]

Subject: abnormal muscle spindle morphology [MP:0004069]
Value: any structural anomaly of the sensory organs in muscle that are involved in the stretch reflex

Subject: abnormal P wave [MP:0004070]
Value: any anomaly in the P wave which represents atrial depolarization and corresponds to electrical impulses rather than mechanical atria contractions; irregular or absent P waves may indicate arrhythmia and the shape of the P waves may indicate atrial problems

Subject: prolonged P wave [MP:0004071]
Value: increase in the length of time of the P wave electrical impulses, measured from the beginning to the end of the P wave

Subject: abnormal frontal plane axis [MP:0004072]
Value: any anomaly found in the sum of all electrical currents in the heart during systole

Subject: caudal body truncation [MP:0004073]
Value: caudal part of body truncated; typically with the rostral portion of the body relatively normal

Subject: abnormal Schwann cell precursor morphology [MP:0004074]
Value: any structural anomaly of the progenitors of cells that sheath the axons of the peripheral nervous system

Subject: decreased Schwann cell precursor number [MP:0004075]
Value: fewer numbers than normal of the progenitors of cells that sheath the axons of the peripheral nervous system

Subject: abnormal vitelline vascular remodeling [MP:0004076]
Value: anomaly in the conversion of the primary (honeycomb-like) vascular plexus of the yolk sac into a mature vascular network

Subject: abnormal striatum morphology [MP:0004077]
Value: any structural anomaly of a large cluster of dopaminergic nerve cells, consisting of the caudate nucleus and the putamen, that controls movement, balance, and walking

Subject: abnormal caudate nucleus morphology [MP:0004078]
Value: any structural anomaly of one or both C-shaped structures that border the lateral ventricle wall and contain input neurons involved with control of voluntary movement in the brain

Subject: abnormal putamen morphology [MP:0004079]
Value: any structural anomaly of the lens-shaped basal ganglion involved with control of voluntary movement in the brain

Subject: abnormal nucleus accumbens morphology [MP:0004080]
Value: any structural anomaly of the group of neurons located at the head of the caudate nucleus and anterior to the putamen; these neurons normally are involved in sensations of pleasure and reactions to addictive substances

Subject: abnormal globus pallidus morphology [MP:0004081]
Value: any structural anomaly of one of the basal ganglia involved with control of voluntary movement in the brain; consists of an external and an internal segment

Subject: abnormal habenula morphology [MP:0004082]
Value: any structural anomaly in the group of nuclei that makes up the small eminence on the dorsomedial surface of the thalamus, just in front of the dorsal commissure on the lateral edge of the habenular trigone

Subject: polysyndactyly [MP:0004083]
Value: greater than the normal complement of digits present on an autopod with interdigital webbing also present

Subject: abnormal cardiac muscle relaxation [MP:0004084]
Value: altered ability of the cardiac/heart muscle to lengthen following contractions, often measured by dP/dt min

Subject: abnormal heartbeat [MP:0004085]
Value: anomaly in the appearance of regularly spaced contractions of the heart due to defects in the frequency, rate, pattern or extent of heart contraction

Subject: absent heartbeat [MP:0004086]
Value: lack of a spontaneously beating heart (usually due to defects in the calcium delivery mechanism or loss of a functional contractile apparatus)

Subject: abnormal muscle fiber morphology [MP:0004087]
Value: any structural anomaly of the muscle fibers, the cylindrical multinucleated muscle cells that contract when stimulated

Subject: abnormal sarcoplasmic reticulum morphology [MP:0004088]
Value: any structural anomaly in the endoplasmic reticulum of skeletal and cardiac muscle, i.e. the complex of vesicles, tubules, and cisternae that form a continuous structure around striated myofibrils, with a repetition of structure within each sarcomere

Subject: dilated sarcoplasmic reticulum [MP:0004089]
Value: an expansion in the volume in the endoplasmic reticulum of skeletal and cardiac muscle, i.e. the complex of vesicles, tubules, and cisternae that form a continuous structure around striated myofibrils, with a repetition of structure within each sarcomere

Subject: abnormal sarcomere morphology [MP:0004090]
Value: any structural anomaly in the segment of a myofibril between two Z lines comprised of multi-protein complexes composed of three different filament systems; these systems work together to contract and relax muscle

Subject: abnormal Z line morphology [MP:0004091]

Subject: absent Z line [MP:0004092]

Subject: diffuse Z line [MP:0004093]

Subject: abnormal M line morphology [MP:0004094]
Value: any structural anomaly of the band in the center of the H band that contains proteins that crosslink the thick filament system (myosins) and the M-band part of the elastic filaments

Subject: ocular distichiasis [MP:0004095]
Value: presence of a double row of eyelashes on an eyelid, one or both of which are turned in against the eyeball

Subject: abnormal midbrain-hindbrain boundary development [MP:0004096]
Value: anomaly in the formation of the midbrain-hindbrain domain, comprised of the mesencephalic vesicle and the first rhombencephalic vesicle at early somitogenesis stages; an organizing center at the boundary patterns the midbrain and hindbrain primordia of the neural plate

Subject: abnormal cerebellar cortex morphology [MP:0004097]

Subject: abnormal cerebellar granule cell morphology [MP:0004098]
Value: any structural anomaly of the small neurons of the cerebellar granule cell layer that send parallel fibers to the upper molecular layer, where they synapse with Purkinje cell dendrites

Subject: abnormal cerebellar glomerulus morphology [MP:0004099]

Subject: abnormal spinal cord interneuron morphology [MP:0004100]
Value: any structural anomaly of neurons that exclusively interact with other neurons in the spinal cord

Subject: abnormal brain interneuron morphology [MP:0004101]
Value: any structural anomaly of neurons that exclusively interact with other neurons in the brain; this includes most brain neuronal cell types

Subject: abnormal dorsal striatum morphology [MP:0004102]
Value: any structural anomaly of the regions of the caudate nucleus and the putamen that lie dorsal to the anterior commissure

Subject: abnormal ventral striatum morphology [MP:0004103]
Value: any structural anomaly of the regions of the nucleus accumbens and some nuclei of the olfactory tubercle that lie ventral to the anterior commissure

Subject: corneal abrasion [MP:0004105]
Value: scraping away or denuding of the corneal surface

Subject: lymphatic vessel hyperplasia [MP:0004106]
Value: overdevelopment or increased size, usually due an increased number of cells in lymphatic vessels

Subject: abnormal thoracic duct morphology [MP:0004107]
Value: any structural anomaly in the largest collecting lymph vessel in the body, beginning at the cisterna chyli at about the level of the second lumbar vertebra, and drains into the systemic (blood) circulation at the left brachiocephalic vein between the left subclavian and left internal jugular veins

Subject: abnormal esophageal peristalsis [MP:0004108]
Value: altered esophageal movement characterized by waves of alternate circular contraction and relaxation of the muscular walls that move the esophagus contents forward

Subject: abnormal Sertoli cell development [MP:0004109]
Value: anomalous differentiation of cells that support germ cell differentiation in males

Subject: transposition of great arteries [MP:0004110]
Value: cardiovascular structural anomaly in which the aorta arises from the right ventricle while the pulmonary artery arises from the left ventricle

Subject: abnormal coronary artery morphology [MP:0004111]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the arteries that branch from the ascending aorta to supply blood to the heart

Subject: abnormal arteriole morphology [MP:0004112]
Value: any structural anomaly of the small diameter vessels that branch from the arteries and lead to the capillaries

Subject: abnormal aortic arch morphology [MP:0004113]
Value: any structural anomaly of the convex portion of the aorta between the ascending and descending parts of the aorta; branches from it include the brachiocephalic trunk, the left common carotid artery, and the left subclavian artery; the brachiocephalic trunk further splits to form the right subclavian artery and the right common carotid artery

Subject: abnormal atrioventricular node morphology [MP:0004114]

Subject: abnormal sinoatrial node morphology [MP:0004115]
Value: any structural anomaly of the small mass of modified cardiac muscle fibers located at the junction of the superior vena cava and the right atrium that is the source of contraction impulses for the heart

Subject: abnormal atrioventricular bundle conduction [MP:0004116]
Value: anomaly in the transfer of cardiac electrical impulses through the specialized cardiac muscle fibers that originates in the atrioventricular node and extends into the ventricle

Subject: abnormal atrioventricular bundle morphology [MP:0004117]
Value: any structural anomaly of the specialized cardiac muscle fibers that originates in the atrioventricular node and extends into the ventricle

Subject: abnormal baroreceptor morphology [MP:0004118]
Value: any structural anomaly in the sensory nerve endings in the wall of the atria of the heart, vena cava, aortic arch and carotid sinus that are sensitive to changes in blood pressure

Subject: hypokalemia [MP:0004119]
Value: excessively low concentrations of potassium in the circulating blood; may be chronic or due to gastrointestinal and kidney depletion due to infection

Subject: cardiac ischemia [MP:0004120]
Value: inadequate blood flow to the heart; may cause infarction and is usually caused by coronary artery disease

Subject: abnormal sarcolemma morphology [MP:0004121]
Value: any structural anomaly in the plasma membrane of a muscle fiber that is capable of conducting electrical impulses

Subject: abnormal sinus arrhythmia [MP:0004122]
Value: any anomaly in the normal phenomenon of mild acceleration and slowing of the heart rate that occurs during the respiratory cycle

Subject: abnormal impulse conducting system morphology [MP:0004123]
Value: any structural anomaly in the impulse-conducting system composed of modified cardiac muscle and having the power of spontaneous rhythmicity and conduction more highly developed than the rest of the heart

Subject: abnormal Purkinje fiber morphology [MP:0004124]

Subject: abnormal venule morphology [MP:0004125]

Subject: thin hypodermis [MP:0004126]

Subject: thick hypodermis [MP:0004127]
Value: increase in the width of the irregular layer of loose connective tissue containing fibroblasts, adipose cells, and macrophages, that is immediately deep to the skin and superficial to the deep fascia

Subject: abnormal respiratory quotient [MP:0004129]
Value: anomaly in the ratio of the volume of carbon dioxide released to oxygen consumed by a body tissue or an organism compared to controls

Subject: abnormal muscle cell glucose uptake [MP:0004130]
Value: anomaly in the ability of muscle cells to take in glucose

Subject: abnormal motile primary cilium morphology [MP:0004131]
Value: any structural anomaly of the cilia of the embryo found on the cells of the embryonic node, which generate flow of extraembryonic fluid surrounding the node in a distinct twirling motion that directs fluid flow asymmetrically across the cellular surface to affect asymmetric body plan organization

Subject: absent embryonic cilia [MP:0004132]
Value: absence of cilia on the cells of the embryonic node

Subject: heterotaxia [MP:0004133]
Value: abnormal arrangement of organs or parts of the body in relation to each other according to the left-right axis

Subject: abnormal chest morphology [MP:0004134]
Value: any structural anomaly of the part of the body between the neck and the abdomen

Subject: abnormal mammary gland embryonic development [MP:0004135]
Value: aberration in the differentiation of the mammary gland during early embryogenesis

Subject: abnormal tongue muscle morphology [MP:0004136]
Value: any structural anomaly of the muscular portion of the tongue

Subject: abnormal gastric surface mucous cell morphology [MP:0004137]
Value: any structural anomaly of the mucus secreting epithelial cells that line the luminal surface of the stomach and the gastric pits which secrete mucus and HCO3- to protect the gastric surface from the acidic environment of the stomach

Subject: abnormal mucous neck cell morphology [MP:0004138]
Value: any structural anomaly of the mucin-producing epithelial cells present in the neck of the gastric glands

Subject: abnormal gastric parietal cell morphology [MP:0004139]
Value: any structural anomaly of the gastric acid producing epithelial cells that are distributed throughout the length of the gastric gland

Subject: abnormal gastric chief cell morphology [MP:0004140]
Value: any structural anomaly of the pepsinogen producing epithelial cells that are clustered at the base of the gastric gland

Subject: abnormal enteroendocrine cell morphology [MP:0004141]
Value: any structural anomaly of the various hormone- or neurotransmitter-secreting epithelial cells present throughout the mucosa of the digestive tract

Subject: abnormal muscle tone [MP:0004142]
Value: anomaly in the resting tautness or laxity of a muscle, normally somewhere in the middle of the range between total contraction and total relaxation

Subject: muscle hypertonia [MP:0004143]
Value: increased muscle tension resulting in stiffness of the muscles in the resting state

Subject: hypotonia [MP:0004144]
Value: decreased muscle tension resulting in limpness of the muscles in the resting state, not to be confused with weakness

Subject: abnormal muscle electrophysiology [MP:0004145]
Value: any functional anomaly of the musculature as it relates to electrical phenomena

Subject: absent M line [MP:0004146]
Value: missing the band in the center of the H band that contains proteins that crosslink the thick filament system (myosins) and the M-band part of the elastic filaments

Subject: increased porphyrin level [MP:0004147]
Value: elevated concentration of porphyrins or protoporphyrins

Subject: increased compact bone thickness [MP:0004148]
Value: thicker than normal superficial layer of compact bone

Subject: increased bone strength [MP:0004149]
Value: increased ability of bone to endure the application of force without yielding or breaking

Subject: absent caveolae [MP:0004150]
Value: absence of the small pockets, vesicles, caves, or recesses communicating with the outside of a cell and extending inward, indenting the cytoplasm and the cell membrane

Subject: decreased circulating iron level [MP:0004151]
Value: less than the normal concentration of iron in the blood

Subject: abnormal circulating iron level [MP:0004152]
Value: anomalous blood concentration of the metallic element that normally occurs in the heme of hemoglobin, myoglobin, transferrin, ferritin, and iron-containing porphyrins; it is an essential component of enzymes such as catalase, peroxidase, and various cytochromes

Subject: increased renal tubule apoptosis [MP:0004153]
Value: increase in the number of renal tubule cells undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: renal tubular necrosis [MP:0004154]
Value: morphological changes resulting from pathological death of renal tubular tissue; usually due to irreversible damage

Subject: decreased susceptibility to induced pancreatitis [MP:0004155]
Value: reduced or absent inflammatory response in the pancreatic tissue after experimental manipulation

Subject: abnormal QT variability [MP:0004156]
Value: anomaly in the index of beat-to-beat QT interval fluctuations (temporal QT interval variability), normally expressed as a unitless negative number reflecting beat-to-beat changes in ventricular repolarization; an increased, positive QTVI number indicates significant repolarization abnormalities

Subject: interrupted aortic arch [MP:0004157]
Value: complete discontinuation between the ascending and descending aorta; includes Type A, interruption distal to the subclavian artery that is ipsilateral to the second carotid artery, and Type B, interruption between second carotid artery and ipsilateral subclavian artery

Subject: right aortic arch [MP:0004158]
Value: the aortic arch lies to the right of the trachea and esophagus; results from persistence of the entire right dorsal arch and involution of a segment of the left arch

Subject: double aortic arch [MP:0004159]
Value: defect in which the main aorta tube splits into large left and right branches (right and left aortic arches), encircling the trachea and esophagus, before becoming one tube to go to the lower body

Subject: retroesophageal right subclavian artery [MP:0004160]
Value: the subclavian artery aberrantly originates from the aortic arch distal to the origin of the left subclavian artery, i.e., it is the last branch of the aortic arch

Subject: cervical aortic arch [MP:0004161]
Value: aortic arch is located above the level of the clavicle

Subject: abnormal mammillary body morphology [MP:0004162]
Value: any structural anomaly of the protrusion at the posterior end of the hypothalamus that contains hypothalamic nuclei

Subject: abnormal adenohypophysis morphology [MP:0004163]
Value: any structural anomaly of the anterior part of the pituitary that secretes a variety of hormones; its function is regulated by the hypothalamus

Subject: abnormal neurohypophysis morphology [MP:0004164]
Value: any structural anomaly of the posterior part of the pituitary gland that secretes hormones involved in blood pressure regulation such as oxytocin and antidiuretic hormone

Subject: abnormal lateral geniculate nucleus morphology [MP:0004165]
Value: any structural anomaly of the group of neurons that serve as the primary processor of visual information received from the retina via the optic tract and send processed information to the visual cortex of the occipital lobe

Subject: abnormal limbic system morphology [MP:0004166]

Subject: abnormal cingulate gyrus morphology [MP:0004167]
