Subject: abnormal parahippocampal gyrus morphology [MP:0004168]
Value: any structural anomaly of the ridge in the cerebral cortex that contains the olfactory cortex and that plays a role in the formation of topographical memory

Subject: abnormal fornicate gyrus morphology [MP:0004169]
Value: any structural anomaly of the horseshoe-shaped gyrus of the cerebral cortex that consists of the cingulate gyrus and the parahippocampal gyrus

Subject: abnormal orbitofrontal cortex morphology [MP:0004170]
Value: any structural anomaly of the region of the cerebral cortex covering the basal surface of the frontal lobes; this region normally controls emotion and decision making

Subject: abnormal pallium development [MP:0004171]
Value: anomaly in the progression of the formation of the roof region of the telencephalon

Subject: abnormal subpallium development [MP:0004172]
Value: anomaly in the progression of the formation of the base region of the telencephalon

Subject: abnormal intervertebral disk morphology [MP:0004173]
Value: any structural anomaly of the cartilaginous and gelatinous structure found between vertebrae

Subject: abnormal spine curvature [MP:0004174]
Value: deviation from the typical S-shape of the spine

Subject: telangiectases [MP:0004175]
Value: vascular lesion formed by dilation of a group of small blood vessels

Subject: ear telangiectases [MP:0004176]
Value: vascular lesion formed by dilation of a group of small blood vessels in the ear

Subject: tail telangiectases [MP:0004177]
Value: vascular lesion formed by dilation of a group of small blood vessels in the tail

Subject: neck telangiectases [MP:0004178]
Value: vascular lesion formed by dilation of a group of small blood vessels in the neck

Subject: transmission ratio distortion [MP:0004179]
Value: the frequency that an allele or haplotype in the offspring of an organism deviates from expected Mendelian ratios

Subject: failure of initiation of embryo turning [MP:0004180]
Value: failure to begin the axial rotation of the germ layers of the embryo during the primitive streak/early somite stage

Subject: abnormal carotid artery morphology [MP:0004181]
Value: any structural anomaly of the bilaterally paired branched arteries that deliver oxygenated nutrient filled blood from the heart to the head, neck, and brain; of the two common carotid arteries, which extend headward on each side of the anterior neck, the left originates in the arch of the aorta over the heart; the right originates in the brachiocephalic trunk, the largest branch from the arch of the aorta; each common carotid artery divides into an external and an internal carotid artery near the top of the thyroid

Subject: abnormal spermiation [MP:0004182]
Value: anomaly in the process by which mature spermatozoa release from supporting Sertoli cells into the lumen of seminiferous tubules

Subject: abnormal sympathetic nervous system physiology [MP:0004183]
Value: any functional anomaly of the part of the autonomic nervous system that innervates smooth muscle, cardiac muscle and glands and mediates the body's response to stressful situations

Subject: abnormal baroreceptor physiology [MP:0004184]
Value: any functional anomaly of the sensory nerve endings found in the wall of the atria of the heart, vena cava, aortic arch and carotid sinus that are sensitive to changes in blood pressure

Subject: abnormal adipocyte glucose uptake [MP:0004185]
Value: anomaly in the ability of adipocytes to take in glucose

Subject: abnormal area postrema morphology [MP:0004186]
Value: any structural anomaly of the small, elevated area in the lateral wall of the inferior recess of the fourth ventricle, involved in the control of cardiorespiratory physiology; in addition, the area postrema is the location of the chemotoxic trigger zone at which emesis (vomiting) is induced by various toxins in the blood stream and that affect the hypothalamus to induce taste aversion

Subject: cardia bifida [MP:0004187]
Value: failure of the bilateral myocardial cells to coalesce into a single central heart tube resulting in the presence of two independent hearts

Subject: delayed embryo turning [MP:0004188]
Value: completion of axial rotation occurs later than in controls but is eventually completed

Subject: abnormal alveolar process morphology [MP:0004189]
Value: any structural anomaly of the thickened ridge of bone in the mandible and maxilla that holds the tooth sockets

Subject: abnormal direction of embryo turning [MP:0004190]
Value: axial rotation of the embryo in a direction other than the normal anticlockwise direction when viewed towards the caudal pole during the late primitive streak/early somite stage; clockwise rotation is frequently associated with heart and visceral defects

Subject: neuronal intranuclear inclusions [MP:0004191]
Value: presence of aggregates of protein within the nuclei of neurons; frequently seen in Huntington's disease

Subject: abnormal kidney pyramid morphology [MP:0004192]
Value: any structural anomaly of the conical mass of tissue, containing part of the secreting and collecting tubules, whose base faces the renal cortex

Subject: abnormal kidney papilla morphology [MP:0004193]
Value: any structural anomaly of the apex of the renal pyramid that projects into a calyx

Subject: abnormal kidney pelvis morphology [MP:0004194]
Value: any structural anomaly of the area at the center of the kidney formed by convergence of the major calices where urine collects and is funneled into the ureter

Subject: abnormal kidney calyx morphology [MP:0004195]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the branches of the renal pelvis that surround each renal papilla and collect urine

Subject: abnormal prenatal growth/weight/body size [MP:0004196]
Value: limited or accelerated growth or development apparent before birth

Subject: abnormal fetal growth/weight/body size [MP:0004197]
Value: limited or accelerated growth or development apparent during the fetal period (sensu Mus: from E14 through birth)

Subject: abnormal fetal size [MP:0004198]
Value: anomalous proportions of a fetus compared to littermates (sensu Mus: from E14 through birth)

Subject: increased fetal size [MP:0004199]
Value: larger proportions of a fetus compared to littermates (sensu Mus: from E14 through birth)

Subject: decreased fetal size [MP:0004200]
Value: smaller proportions of a fetus compared to littermates (sensu Mus: from E14 through birth)

Subject: fetal growth retardation [MP:0004201]
Value: slow or limited development during the fetal period (sensu Mus: from E14 through birth)

Subject: pulmonary hyperplasia [MP:0004202]
Value: overdevelopment or increased size, usually due an increased number of cells of the respiratory organ in all or part of the organ

Subject: abnormal cranial flexure morphology [MP:0004203]
Value: any structural anomaly or absence of the sharp, ventrally concave bend in the developing midbrain of the embryo

Subject: absent stapes [MP:0004204]
Value: absence of the smallest and innermost of the three auditory ossicles

Subject: absent hyoid bone [MP:0004205]
Value: absence of the U-shaped bone lying between the mandible and the larynx that supports the tongue muscles

Subject: abnormal dermomyotome development [MP:0004206]
Value: any structural anomaly of the portion of the embryonic somite that remains after migration of the sclerotomic tissue

Subject: increased squamous cell carcinoma incidence [MP:0004207]
Value: higher than normal incidence of a carcinoma that arises from stratified squamous epithelium that occurs in sites where glandular or columnar epithelium is normally present, such as the skin, esophagus, lungs and cervix

Subject: increased basal cell carcinoma incidence [MP:0004208]
Value: greater than the expected number of a slow-growing, invasive, but usually non-metastasizing neoplasm that originates from basal keratinocytes in the epidermis, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: abnormal sweet taste sensitivity [MP:0004209]
Value: changes in the ability to perceive a particular flavor or suggestion of something sweet by the chemoreceptors of the gustatory system

Subject: abnormal bitter taste sensitivity [MP:0004210]
Value: changes in the ability to perceive a particular flavor or suggestion of something bitter by the chemoreceptors of the gustatory system

Subject: abnormal sour taste sensitivity [MP:0004211]
Value: changes in the ability to perceive a particular flavor or suggestion of something sour by the chemoreceptors of the gustatory system

Subject: abnormal salty taste sensitivity [MP:0004212]
Value: changes in the ability to perceive a particular flavor or suggestion of something salty by the chemoreceptors of the gustatory system

Subject: abnormal umami taste sensitivity [MP:0004213]
Value: changes in the ability to perceive a particular flavor or suggestion of something umami (savory) by the chemoreceptors of the gustatory system

Subject: abnormal long bone diaphysis morphology [MP:0004214]
Value: any structural anomaly of the main or mid section (shaft) of a long bone

Subject: abnormal myocardial fiber physiology [MP:0004215]
Value: anomaly in the function of the terminally differentiated, non-proliferative, multinucleated muscle cells of the heart

Subject: salt-resistant hypertension [MP:0004216]
Value: sustained high blood pressure that is maintained regardless of the amount of salt consumed in the diet

Subject: salt-sensitive hypertension [MP:0004217]
Value: sustained high blood pressure that is maintained with a normal or increase in the amount of salt consumed in the diet; blood pressure may return to normotensive with a low salt diet

Subject: meiotic nondisjunction during M1 phase [MP:0004218]
Value: abnormal separation of pairs of homologous chromosomes during anaphase of the first meiotic division such that each daughter cell receives one set of paired chromosomes

Subject: meiotic nondisjunction during M2 phase [MP:0004219]
Value: abnormal separation of chromosomes during anaphase of the second meiotic division such that one complete chromosome goes to each daughter cell

Subject: abnormal peripheral nervous system regeneration [MP:0004220]
Value: changes in the ability or inability of healthy peripheral nervous system tissue to regenerate following injury or disease

Subject: abnormal iridocorneal angle [MP:0004221]
Value: any structural anomaly of the acute angle occurring between the iris and the cornea at the periphery of the anterior chamber of the eye

Subject: iris synechia [MP:0004222]
Value: an adhesion (synechia) of the iris to the cornea or lens of the eye that may develop from glaucoma, cataracts, uveitis, or keratitis or as a complication of surgery or trauma to the eye; synechiae may prevent or impede flow of aqueous fluid between the anterior and posterior chambers of the eye, resulting in angle closure glaucoma

Subject: hypoplastic trabecular meshwork [MP:0004223]
Value: reduced size of the pore-like structure surrounding the entire circumference of the anterior chamber through which aqueous humor circulates

Subject: absent trabecular meshwork [MP:0004224]
Value: absence of the pore-like structure surrounding the entire circumference of the anterior chamber through which aqueous humor circulates

Subject: patent cardiac foramen ovale [MP:0004225]
Value: incomplete closure of the atrial septum after birth, resulting in a flap or a valve-like opening in the atrial septal wall

Subject: absent Schlemm\'s canal [MP:0004226]
Value: absence of the vascular structure encircling the anterior chamber of the eye, through which the aqueous humor is returned to the blood circulation

Subject: increased cellular sensitivity to ionizing radiation [MP:0004227]
Value: increased incidence of cell death following exposure to ionizing radiation

Subject: decreased cellular sensitivity to ionizing radiation [MP:0004228]
Value: decreased incidence of cell death following exposure to ionizing radiation

Subject: abnormal embryonic erythropoiesis [MP:0004229]
Value: anomaly in the development of primarily large, nucleated erythroblasts occurring in blood islands in the yolk sac, generally occurs from E7-E11 in the mouse and through 10 weeks in humans

Subject: abnormal embryonic erythrocyte morphology [MP:0004230]
Value: any structural anomaly of the embryonic blood cells that carry oxygen; embryonic erythrocytes arise from yolk sac blood islands and express different types of hemoglobins (beta-H1, gamma-1 and zeta) than adult erythrocytes, and can enucleate in circulation

Subject: abnormal calcium ion homeostasis [MP:0004231]
Value: anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of calcium ions within the body or between a cell and its external environment

Subject: decreased muscle weight [MP:0004232]
Value: less than average muscle weight

Subject: abnormal muscle weight [MP:0004233]
Value: any anomaly in the average muscle weight

Subject: abnormal masticatory muscle morphology [MP:0004234]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the muscles responsible for the movement of the jaws during mastication, including the masseter, temporal, and medial and lateral pterygoid muscles

Subject: abnormal masseter muscle morphology [MP:0004235]
Value: any structural anomaly of the masticatory muscle of posterior cheek with origin from the inferior border and medial surface of the zygomatic arch, with insertion into the lateral surface of the ramus of the mandible, with nerve supply from the masseteric nerve, and whose action closes the jaw during chewing

Subject: absent masseter muscle [MP:0004236]
Value: absence of the masticatory muscle of posterior cheek

Subject: abnormal pterygoid muscle morphology [MP:0004237]
Value: any structural anomaly of the muscles descending from the sphenoid bone to the lower jaw including the internal, or medial, pterygoid muscle and external, or lateral, pterygoid muscle; the action of the former is closing the jaws and that of the latter is opening the jaws, protruding the mandible, and moving the mandible from side to side

Subject: absent pterygoid muscle [MP:0004238]
Value: absence of either the internal or external or of both pterygoid muscles

Subject: abnormal temporalis muscle morphology [MP:0004239]
Value: any structural anomaly of the superior-most masticatory muscle whose action is closing the jaws; its posterior portion retracts the mandible

Subject: absent temporalis muscle [MP:0004240]
Value: absence of the superior-most masticatory muscle whose action is closing the jaws; its posterior portion retracts the mandible

Subject: acantholysis [MP:0004241]
Value: separation of prickle cells of the spinous layer of the epidermis, resulting in atrophy of the prickle cell layer, as in conditions such as pemphigus vulgaris and Darier disease

Subject: abnormal plasmacytoid dendritic cell morphology [MP:0004242]
Value: any structural anomaly of phagocytic dendritic cells that are morphologically similar to plasma cells, but do not express B lineage markers, and produce large amounts of alpha/beta interferons (IFN-/) in response to viral and bacterial stimuli; plasmacytoid dendritic cells are found in the thymic medulla and lymph node T cell areas and are responsible for immune tolerance

Subject: abnormal motor nerve collateral sprouting [MP:0004243]
Value: aberrant response of a motor neuron to form new neuritic processes (sprouts) that emerge from the nodes of Ranvier or terminal arborizations in response to nerve injury (such as denervation), application of nerve toxin, or muscle inactivity (usually due to disease)

Subject: abnormal miscarriage rate [MP:0004244]
Value: change in frequency of a natural or accidental termination of a pregnancy at a stage where the embryo or the fetus is incapable of surviving independently of the mother

Subject: genital hemorrhage [MP:0004245]
Value: bleeding into the genitals

Subject: abnormal extensor digitorum longus morphology [MP:0004246]
Value: any structural anomaly of the penniform muscle of the lateral front part of the leg responsible for extension of the toes and dorsiflexion of the ankle

Subject: small pancreas [MP:0004247]
Value: decrease of the size of the pancreas compared to controls

Subject: abnormal epaxial muscle morphology [MP:0004248]
Value: any structural anomaly of the muscles derived from the medial myotome; includes the intrinsic back muscles

Subject: abnormal crista ampullaris morphology [MP:0004249]
Value: any structural anomaly in the elevation found on the inner surface of the ampullae of each semicircular duct; filaments of the vestibular nerve pass through the crista to reach hair cells on its surface; the hair cells are capped by the cupula, a gelatinous protein-polysaccharide mass

Subject: tau protein deposits [MP:0004250]
Value: formation of self-assembled tangles of paired helical filaments and straight filaments due to hyperphosphorylation of the tau protein; often seen in neuronal tissues of individuals with neurodegenerative disorders

Subject: failure of heart looping [MP:0004251]
Value: failure of the primitive heart tube to loop asymmetrically during early development

Subject: abnormal direction of heart looping [MP:0004252]
Value: deviation from the characteristic rightward direction of looping of the primitive heart tube; frequently seen in heterotaxy syndromes

Subject: bifid atrial appendage [MP:0004253]
Value: a cardiac anomaly whereby the left or right atrial appendage is cleaved, forming two separate pouches connected by a thin strand of muscular tissue

Subject: cerebral amyloid angiopathy [MP:0004254]
Value: a pathological condition where there is a deposition of amyloid in the walls of the small cerebral vessels which supply the brain; this results in an increased risk of infarcts and/or intracerebral hemorrhage, possibly resulting in dementia

Subject: abnormal spongiotrophoblast layer morphology [MP:0004255]
Value: any structural anomaly of the middle layer of the placenta between the outermost giant cells and the innermost labyrinth layer; it has a structural role and also produces several layer-specific secreted factors

Subject: abnormal maternal decidual layer morphology [MP:0004256]
Value: any structural anomaly of the maternal uterine-derived portion of the placenta

Subject: abnormal placenta weight [MP:0004257]
Value: any change in the weight of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother

Subject: abnormal placenta size [MP:0004258]
Value: anomaly in the size or shape of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother

Subject: small placenta [MP:0004259]
Value: reduced size of the size or shape of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother

Subject: enlarged placenta [MP:0004260]
Value: increased size of the size or shape of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother

Subject: abnormal embryonic neuroepithelium morphology [MP:0004261]
Value: any structural anomaly of the epithelial cell layer that lines the neural tube and develops into the nervous system and into the neural crest cells

Subject: abnormal physical strength [MP:0004262]
Value: altered ability of an organism to exert force on physical objects or of the body to support its load

Subject: abnormal limb posture [MP:0004263]
Value: atypical intentionally or habitually assumed position of the limbs compared to the normal carriage of the body

Subject: abnormal extraembryonic tissue physiology [MP:0004264]
Value: any functional anomaly of the membranes involved with embryonic protection and nutrition

Subject: abnormal placental transport [MP:0004265]
Value: anomaly in the conveyance of metabolic products and nutrients across the placenta

Subject: pale placenta [MP:0004266]
Value: placenta lacking normal reddish coloration, often refers to bloodless condition

Subject: abnormal optic tract morphology [MP:0004267]
Value: any structural anomaly of the paired bands of optic nerve fibers running from the optic chiasma mostly to the lateral geniculate body, with a smaller number of fibers terminating in the superior colliculus and the pretectal region

Subject: abnormal optic stalk morphology [MP:0004268]
Value: any structural anomaly of the narrow, proximal portion of the optic vesicle which connects the embryonic eye and forebrain

Subject: abnormal optic cup morphology [MP:0004269]
Value: any structural anomaly of double walled structure formed by expansion and invagination of the distal end of the optic vesicle that develops into the pigmented and neuronal layers of the retina, with the mouth of the optic cup developing into the pupil of the eye

Subject: analgesia [MP:0004270]
Value: inability to sense pain

Subject: abnormal basement membrane morphology [MP:0004272]
Value: anomaly in the structure, organization and/or placement of the extracellular supportive tissue adjacent to the basal surface of the epithelia, including the epithelium of muscle cells, fat cells and Schwann cells; it is comprised of type IV collagen, laminin, and sulfated proteoglycans and other components and consists of two layers, the basal lamina and the lamina reticularis

Subject: abnormal basal lamina morphology [MP:0004273]
Value: any structural anomaly of the sheet of extracellular matrix characteristically situated under epithelial cells, around muscles, nerves, capillaries, and fat cells, and situated between these elements and the underlying or surrounding connective tissue

Subject: abnormal embryonic/fetal subventricular zone morphology [MP:0004274]
Value: any structural anomaly of the transient proliferative population of neurons that expands exponentially during late prenatal development; it is a continuous germinal zone distinct from the ventricular zone that surrounds the brain ventricles

Subject: abnormal postnatal subventricular zone morphology [MP:0004275]
Value: any structural anomaly of the mitotically active layer of cells surrounding the brain ventricles in the adult that consists of migrating neuroblasts, astrocytes and transitory amplifying progenitor cells

Subject: abnormal medial ganglionic eminence morphology [MP:0004276]
Value: any structural anomaly of a distinct elevation of a transient proliferating cell mass of the fetal subventricular zone; this mass contributes most of its cells to the neocortex; however, hippocampal neurons, thalamus, septum and olfactory bulb neurons are also partly derived from the MGE

Subject: abnormal lateral ganglionic eminence morphology [MP:0004277]
Value: any structural anomaly of a distinct elevation of a transient proliferating cell mass of the fetal subventricular zone; this mass contributes most of its cells to the striatum; however, neocortex, thalamus, septum and olfactory bulb neurons are also partly derived from the LGE

Subject: abnormal caudal ganglionic eminence morphology [MP:0004278]
Value: any structural anomaly of the caudally located, distinct elevation of a transient proliferating cell mass of the fetal subventricular zone, located adjacent to the lateral ventricle

Subject: abnormal rostral migratory stream morphology [MP:0004279]
Value: any structural anomaly of the transient structure formed by neurons migrating from the subventricular zone into the olfactory bulbs

Subject: abnormal oculomotor nucleus morphology [MP:0004280]
Value: any structural anomaly of the group of motor neurons in the floor of the midbrain that gives rise to motor fibers of the oculomotor nerve

Subject: abnormal hypoglossal nucleus morphology [MP:0004281]
Value: any structural anomaly of the group of motor neurons throughout most of the length of the medulla oblongata that give rise to the motor fibers of the hypoglossal nerve

Subject: retrognathia [MP:0004282]
Value: abnormal posterior-shifted positioning of the upper or lower jaw relative to the facial skeleton and soft tissues; a type of malocclusion, that is, misalignment of the teeth caused by abnormal positioning of the jaws; the mandible is more frequently affected than the maxilla

Subject: absent corneal endothelium [MP:0004283]
Value: absence of the single layer of large flattened cells that cover the surface of the cornea

Subject: abnormal Descemet membrane [MP:0004284]
Value: any structural anomaly in the transparent homogeneous acellular layer found between the substantia propria and the endothelial layer of the cornea, considered to be a highly developed basement membrane

Subject: absent Descemet membrane [MP:0004285]
Value: absence of the transparent homogeneous acellular layer found between the substantia propria and the endothelial layer of the cornea

Subject: abnormal internal auditory canal morphology [MP:0004286]
Value: any structural anomaly in the canal beginning at the opening of the internal acoustic meatus in the posterior cranial fossa, passing laterally through the petrous portion of the temporal bone to end at the fundus, where a thin plate of bone separates it from the vestibule; it gives passage to the facial and vestibulocochlear nerves together with the labyrinthine artery and veins

Subject: abnormal spiral limbus morphology [MP:0004287]
Value: any structural anomaly in the border of the spiral lamina, i.e. the thickened periosteum covering the upper plate of the bony spiral lamina of the cochlea

Subject: abnormal spiral ligament morphology [MP:0004288]
Value: any structural anomaly in the thickened periosteal lining of the bony cochlea that forms the outer wall of the cochlear duct to which the basal lamina attaches

Subject: abnormal bony labyrinth [MP:0004289]
Value: any structural anomaly in the series of cavities (cochlea, vestibule, and semicircular canals) contained within the otic capsule of the petrous portion of the temporal bone; the bony labyrinth is filled with perilymph, in which the delicate, endolymph-filled membranous labyrinth is suspended

Subject: abnormal stapes footplate morphology [MP:0004290]
Value: any structural anomaly in the flat portion of the stapes that fits in the oval window

Subject: abnormal spiral ligament fibrocyte morphology [MP:0004292]
Value: any structural anomaly in the four types of fibrocytes (types I, II , III and IV) that constitute the spiral ligament

Subject: abnormal type I spiral ligament fibrocytes [MP:0004293]
Value: any structural anomaly of type I spiral ligament fibrocytes which occupy the region beneath the stria vascularis

Subject: abnormal type II spiral ligament fibrocytes [MP:0004294]
Value: any structural anomaly of type II spiral ligament fibrocytes found in the suprastrial zone and the central area of the spiral ligament beneath the spiral prominence

Subject: abnormal type III spiral ligament fibrocytes [MP:0004295]
Value: any structural anomaly of type III spiral ligament fibrocytes which form a cell layer attached to the otic capsule

Subject: abnormal type IV spiral ligament fibrocytes [MP:0004296]
Value: any structural anomaly of type IV spiral ligament fibrocytes found in the triangular space inferior to the basilar crest

Subject: abnormal proprioceptive neuron morphology [MP:0004297]
Value: any structural anomaly of the sensory neurons of the dorsal root ganglia that sense body position and send information about how much the muscle is stretched to the spinal cord

Subject: vestibular ganglion degeneration [MP:0004298]
Value: loss of the group of bipolar sensory nerve cell bodies concerned with equilibration that form a swelling on the vestibular part of the eighth cranial nerve in the fundus of the internal acoustic meatus

Subject: absent vestibular ganglion [MP:0004299]
Value: absence of the group of bipolar sensory nerve cell bodies concerned with equilibration that form a swelling on the vestibular part of the eighth cranial nerve in the fundus of the internal acoustic meatus

Subject: abnormal organ of Corti supporting cell morphology [MP:0004300]
Value: any structural anomaly in the highly differentiated epithelial cells with distinctive morphological features surrounding the hair cells in the organ of Corti; inner hair cells (IHCs) are normally surrounded by (inner and outer) phalangeal cells while OHCs are in contact with Deiters and pillar cells; Hensen cells are positioned further laterally in the organ of Corti

Subject: absent organ of Corti supporting cells [MP:0004301]
Value: absence of the highly differentiated epithelial cells with distinctive morphological features that surround all hair cells in the organ of Corti

Subject: abnormal Deiters cell morphology [MP:0004302]
Value: any structural anomaly in the supporting cells of the spiral organ which are attached to the basement membrane and receive the hair cells between their free extremities

Subject: abnormal Hensen cell morphology [MP:0004303]
Value: any structural anomaly in the supporting cells that form the lateral border of the organ of Corti, immediately to the outer side of Deiters' cells

Subject: absent spiral limbus [MP:0004304]
Value: absence of the border of the spiral lamina, i.e. the thickened periosteum covering the upper plate of the bony spiral lamina of the cochlea

Subject: abnormal Rosenthal canal morphology [MP:0004305]
Value: any structural anomaly in the winding tube of the bony labyrinth that makes two and a half turns about the modiolus of the cochlea; it is divided incompletely into two compartments by a winding shelf of bone, the bony spiral lamina

Subject: small Rosenthal canal [MP:0004306]
Value: reduced size of the winding tube of the bony labyrinth that makes two and a half turns about the modiolus of the cochlea

Subject: absent Rosenthal canal [MP:0004307]
Value: absence of the winding tube of the bony labyrinth that makes two and a half turns about the modiolus of the cochlea

Subject: abnormal basilar membrane morphology [MP:0004308]
Value: any structural anomaly in the membrane extending from the bony spiral membrane to the basilar crest of the cochlea; it forms the greater part of the floor of the cochlear duct separating the latter from the scala tympani, and it supports the organ of Corti

Subject: absent otic vesicle [MP:0004309]
Value: absence of the simple epithelial sac formed from the otic placode that gives rise to the structures of the inner ear

Subject: small otic vesicle [MP:0004310]
Value: reduced size of the simple epithelial sac formed from the otic placode that gives rise to the structures of the inner ear

Subject: otic vesicle hypoplasia [MP:0004311]
Value: underdevelopment of the simple epithelial sac formed from the otic placode that gives rise to the structures of the inner ear, usually due to a reduction in cell number

Subject: absent pillar cells [MP:0004312]
Value: absence of the supporting cells that form the inner and outer walls of the tunnel in the organ of Corti

Subject: absent vestibulocochlear ganglion [MP:0004313]
Value: absence of the group of neuron cell bodies associated with the eighth cranial nerve during embryogenesis; splits in later development to form the cochlear and vestibular ganglia

Subject: absent inner ear vestibule [MP:0004314]
Value: absence of the cavity between the semicircular canals and the cochlea of the inner ear

Subject: absent vestibular saccule [MP:0004315]
Value: absence of the smaller of the two sacs in the vestibule

Subject: enlarged vestibular saccule [MP:0004316]
Value: enlarged size of the cavity between the semicircular canals and the cochlea of the inner ear

Subject: small vestibular saccule [MP:0004317]
Value: reduced size of the cavity between the semicircular canals and the cochlea of the inner ear

Subject: absent incus [MP:0004318]
Value: absence of the middle of the three auditory ossicles

Subject: absent malleus [MP:0004319]
Value: absence of the largest of the three auditory ossicles, which resembles a club or hammer

Subject: split sternum [MP:0004320]
Value: the appearance of an abnormal division in the long flat bone of the chest which articulates with clavicle and first seven rib pairs

Subject: short sternum [MP:0004321]
Value: reduced length of the long flat bone of the chest which articulates with clavicle and first seven rib pairs

Subject: abnormal sternebra morphology [MP:0004322]
Value: any structural anomaly of one segments of the primordial sternum of the embryo; these segments fuse to form the body of the adult vertebrate sternum

Subject: sternum hypoplasia [MP:0004323]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, in the sternum

Subject: vestibular hair cell degeneration [MP:0004324]
Value: degeneration or loss of the sensory epithelial cells of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear which are normally in synaptic contact with the vestibular nerve

Subject: absent vestibular hair cells [MP:0004325]
Value: absence of the sensory epithelial cells of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear which are normally in synaptic contact with the vestibular nerve

Subject: abnormal vestibular hair cell number [MP:0004326]
Value: abnormal number of cells in the sensory epithelium of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the internal ear

Subject: increased vestibular hair cell number [MP:0004327]
Value: increased number of cells in the sensory epithelium of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the internal ear which are normally in synaptic contact with the vestibular nerve

Subject: decreased vestibular hair cell number [MP:0004328]
Value: decreased number of cells in the sensory epithelium of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the internal ear which are normally in synaptic contact with the vestibular nerve

Subject: vestibular saccular degeneration [MP:0004329]
Value: degeneration or loss of the smaller of the two sacs in the vestibule

Subject: abnormal vestibular saccular macula morphology [MP:0004330]
Value: any structural anomaly of the oval neuroepithelial sensory receptor in the anterior wall of the saccule; hair cells of the neuroepithelium support the statoconial membrane and have terminal arborizations of vestibular nerve fibers around their bodies

Subject: vestibular saccular macula degeneration [MP:0004331]
Value: degeneration or loss of the oval neuroepithelial sensory receptor in the anterior wall of the saccule

Subject: utricular degeneration [MP:0004332]
Value: degeneration or loss of the larger of the two sacs in the vestibule

Subject: abnormal utricular macula morphology [MP:0004333]
Value: any structural anomaly of the neuroepithelial sensory receptor in the inferolateral wall of the utricle; hair cells of the neuroepithelium support the statoconial membrane and have terminal arborizations of vestibular nerve fibers around their bodies; normally sensitive to linear acceleration in the longitudinal axis of the body and to gravitational influences

Subject: utricular macular degeneration [MP:0004334]
Value: degeneration or loss of the neuroepithelial sensory receptor in the inferolateral wall of the utricle

Subject: enlarged utricle [MP:0004335]
Value: increased size of the larger of the two sacs in the vestibule

Subject: small utricle [MP:0004336]
Value: reduced size of the larger of the two sacs in the vestibule

Subject: clavicle hypoplasia [MP:0004337]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, of one or both of the doubly curved long bone that forms part of the shoulder girdle and articulates with the sternum and the scapula

Subject: small clavicle [MP:0004338]
Value: reduced size of one or both of the doubly curved long bone that forms part of the shoulder girdle and articulates with the sternum and the scapula

Subject: absent clavicle [MP:0004339]
Value: missing one or both of the doubly curved long bone that forms part of the shoulder girdle and articulates with the sternum and the scapula

Subject: short scapula [MP:0004340]
Value: reduced length of either or both of the large, flat bones of the back part of the shoulder

Subject: absent scapula [MP:0004341]
Value: missing either or both of the large, flat bones of the back part of the shoulder

Subject: scapular bone foramen [MP:0004342]
Value: presence of a hole in either or both of the large, flat bones of the back part of the shoulder

Subject: small scapula [MP:0004343]
Value: reduced size of either or both of the large, flat bones of the back part of the shoulder

Subject: scapular bone hypoplasia [MP:0004344]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, in either or both of the large, flat bones of the back part of the shoulder

Subject: abnormal acromion morphology [MP:0004345]

Subject: bowed femur [MP:0004371]

Subject: absent prechordal plate [MP:0004388]

Subject: abnormal cochlear inner hair cell morphology [MP:0004393]

Subject: decreased cochlear inner hair cell number [MP:0004396]

Subject: absent cochlear inner hair cells [MP:0004397]

Subject: cochlear inner hair cell degeneration [MP:0004398]

Subject: abnormal cochlear outer hair cell morphology [MP:0004399]

Subject: abnormal cochlear outer hair cell number [MP:0004400]

Subject: decreased cochlear outer hair cell number [MP:0004402]

Subject: cochlear outer hair cell degeneration [MP:0004404]

Subject: absent cochlear hair cells [MP:0004405]

Subject: abnormal cochlear hair cell number [MP:0004406]

Subject: increased cochlear hair cell number [MP:0004407]

Subject: decreased cochlear hair cell number [MP:0004408]

Subject: abnormal crista ampullaris neuroepithelium morphology [MP:0004409]

Subject: absent endocochlear potential [MP:0004410]

Subject: decreased endocochlear potential [MP:0004411]

Subject: abnormal cochlear microphonics [MP:0004412]
Value: any anomaly in the bioelectric potentials produced by the hair cells of the organ of Corti in response to sound; the cochlear microphonic (CM) is an electric response dominated by OHC receptor potentials from the basal turn of the cochlea and provides a measure of transducer function in OHCs; in an active ear, CM waveforms show post-stimulus ringing (i.e. a cochlear echo) whereas in a passive ear system, CM decays at the cessation of the tone burst

Subject: absent cochlear microphonics [MP:0004413]

Subject: decreased cochlear microphonics [MP:0004414]

Subject: abnormal cochlear nerve compound action potential [MP:0004415]

Subject: decreased cochlear nerve compound action potential [MP:0004417]

Subject: small parietal bone [MP:0004418]

Subject: absent parietal bone [MP:0004419]

Subject: enlarged parietal bone [MP:0004421]

Subject: abnormal temporal bone squamous part morphology [MP:0004423]

Subject: abnormal otolith organ morphology [MP:0004425]

Subject: abnormal vestibular labyrinth morphology [MP:0004427]

Subject: abnormal type I vestibular cell [MP:0004428]

Subject: abnormal type II vestibular cells [MP:0004429]
Value: any structural anomaly in the cylindrical sensory cells of the maculae and cristae of the vestibular labyrinth of the inner ear which are normally contacted by bouton endings of afferent and efferent neurons; afferent and efferent nerve fibers of the vestibular nerve synapse with them; from the apical end of each cell a bundle of stereocilia and a kinocilium extend into the otolithic membrane of the maculae or the cupula of the cristae

Subject: abnormal Claudius cell morphology [MP:0004430]

Subject: abnormal hair cell mechanoelectric transduction [MP:0004431]

Subject: abnormal cochlear hair cell physiology [MP:0004432]
Value: any functional anomaly in processes pertinent to the integrated function of cochlear hair cells i.e. the sensory cells in the spiral organ which are in synaptic contact with sensory as well as efferent fibers of the cochlear (auditory) nerve

Subject: abnormal cochlear inner hair cell physiology [MP:0004433]

Subject: absent cochlear outer hair cell electromotility [MP:0004436]

Subject: decreased cochlear outer hair cell electromotility [MP:0004437]

Subject: abnormal vestibular hair cell physiology [MP:0004438]

Subject: absent Meckel\'s cartilage [MP:0004439]

Subject: small occipital bone [MP:0004441]

Subject: small supraoccipital bone [MP:0004444]

Subject: small exoccipital bone [MP:0004445]

Subject: abnormal presphenoid bone morphology [MP:0004448]

Subject: absent presphenoid bone [MP:0004449]

Subject: absent pterygoid process [MP:0004454]

Subject: pterygoid bone hypoplasia [MP:0004455]

Subject: small pterygoid bone [MP:0004456]

Subject: abnormal orbitosphenoid bone morphology [MP:0004457]

Subject: absent alisphenoid bone [MP:0004458]

Subject: small alisphenoid bone [MP:0004459]

Subject: alisphenoid bone hypoplasia [MP:0004460]

Subject: absent strial basal cell tight junctions [MP:0004464]

Subject: turbinate hypoplasia [MP:0004477]

Subject: increased testicular teratoma incidence [MP:0004478]

Subject: abnormal oval window morphology [MP:0004479]

Subject: abnormal round window morphology [MP:0004480]

Subject: abnormal interdental cell morphology [MP:0004482]

Subject: absent interdental cells [MP:0004483]

Subject: altered response of heart to induced stress [MP:0004484]

Subject: increased response of heart to induced stress [MP:0004485]

Subject: decreased response of heart to induced stress [MP:0004486]
Value: decrease in severity of the physiological response of the heart to induced stress such as cardiac hypertrophy due to mechanical pressure overload from aortic banding

Subject: abnormal synaptic glutamate release [MP:0004494]

Subject: decreased synaptic glutamate release [MP:0004495]
Value: reduced secretion across synapses of the major excitatory neurotransmitter of the central nervous system (CNS), which acts through both ligand gated ion channels (ionotropic receptors) and G protein-coupled (metabotropic) receptors

Subject: abnormal organ of Corti supporting cell number [MP:0004496]
Value: abnormal number of the highly differentiated epithelial cells with distinctive morphological features which surround the hair cells in the organ of Corti

Subject: decreased organ of Corti supporting cell number [MP:0004497]
Value: decreased number of the highly differentiated epithelial cells with distinctive morphological features which surround the hair cells in the organ of Corti

Subject: increased organ of Corti supporting cell number [MP:0004498]
Value: increased number of the highly differentiated epithelial cells with distinctive morphological features which surround the hair cells in the organ of Corti

Subject: increased incidence of tumors by chemical induction [MP:0004499]
Value: higher than normal frequency of tumor incidence induced by one or more chemical carcinogens or mutagens

Subject: increased incidence of tumors by ionizing radiation induction [MP:0004500]
Value: higher than normal frequency of tumor incidence induced by radiation in which the individual particle or photon carries sufficient energy to completely remove an electron from its orbit; common types of this radiation include gamma-rays and X-rays

Subject: increased incidence of tumors by UV-induction [MP:0004501]
Value: higher than normal frequency of tumor incidence induced by exposure to ultraviolet light

Subject: decreased incidence of tumors by chemical induction [MP:0004502]
Value: lower than normal frequency of tumor incidence induced by one or more chemical carcinogens or mutagens

Subject: decreased incidence of tumors by ionizing radiation induction [MP:0004503]
Value: lower than normal frequency of tumor incidence induced by radiation in which the individual particle or photon carries sufficient energy to completely remove an electron from its orbit; common types of this radiation include gamma-rays and X-rays

Subject: decreased incidence of tumors by UV induction [MP:0004504]
Value: lower than normal frequency of tumor incidence induced by exposure to ultraviolet light

Subject: decreased renal glomerulus number [MP:0004505]
Value: reduced number of the capillary loops of the kidney that normally function as a filtration unit

Subject: abnormal pubis morphology [MP:0004506]
Value: any structural anomaly of the forward portion of either of the hipbones, at the juncture forming the front arch of the pelvis

Subject: abnormal ischium morphology [MP:0004507]
Value: any structural anomaly of the lowest of the three major bones that constitute each half of the pelvis, distinct at birth but later becoming fused with the ilium and pubis

Subject: abnormal pectoral girdle bone morphology [MP:0004508]
Value: any structural anomaly of the bones of the shoulder by which the limbs attach to the axial skeleton

Subject: abnormal pelvic girdle bone morphology [MP:0004509]
Value: any structural anomaly of the bones of the pelvis by which the limbs attach to the axial skeleton

Subject: myositis [MP:0004510]
Value: inflammation of muscle; local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in muscle

Subject: anosmia [MP:0004512]
Value: loss of the sense of smell

Subject: avnosmia [MP:0004513]
Value: loss of the ability to detect pheromones through the vomeronasal system

Subject: dystocia [MP:0004514]
Value: slow or difficult delivery of offspring and/or placenta

Subject: abnormal vestibular hair cell stereociliary bundle morphology [MP:0004515]
Value: any structural anomaly or disruption of the typical staircase-like arrangement of the mechanosensitive hair bundles which are composed of thick long microvilli (stereocilia) and are located at the apical end of vestibular hair cells of the utricle and saccule

Subject: fused vestibular hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004516]
Value: coalescence of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) normally arrayed on vestibular hair cells, often resulting in giant stereocilia

Subject: decreased vestibular hair cell stereocilia number [MP:0004517]
Value: decreased number of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) normally arrayed on vestibular hair cells in a staircase-like pattern

Subject: absent vestibular hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004518]
Value: complete absence of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) which are normally arrayed on vestibular hair cells in a staircase-like pattern

Subject: thin vestibular hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004519]
Value: reduced thickness of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) which are normally arrayed on vestibular hair cells in a staircase-like pattern

Subject: short vestibular hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004520]
Value: reduced length of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) which are normally arrayed on vestibular hair cells in a staircase-like pattern

Subject: abnormal cochlear hair cell stereociliary bundle morphology [MP:0004521]
Value: any structural anomaly or disruption of the typical pattern of arrangement of mechanosensitive hair bundles which are composed of thick long microvilli (stereocilia) and are located at the apical end of cochlear inner and outer hair cells

Subject: abnormal orientation of cochlear hair cell stereociliary bundles [MP:0004522]
Value: misorientation or rotation of inner and/or outer hair cell stereociliary bundles, resulting in defective planar cell polarity of the inner ear sensory epithelium

Subject: decreased cochlear hair cell stereocilia number [MP:0004523]
Value: decreased number (or less than the expected 100 or so) of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) normally arrayed on cochlear inner and outer hair cells

Subject: short cochlear hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004524]
Value: reduced length of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) which are normally arrayed on cochlear inner and outer hair cells

Subject: thin cochlear hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004525]
Value: reduced thickness of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) which are normally arrayed on cochlear inner and outer hair cells

Subject: absent cochlear hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004526]
Value: complete absence of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) which are normally arrayed on cochlear inner and outer hair cells

Subject: abnormal outer hair cell stereociliary bundle morphology [MP:0004527]
Value: any structural anomaly or disruption of the typical V or W-like pattern of arrangement of mechanosensitive hair bundles located at the apical end of cochlear OHCs; each hair bundle is normally composed of ~100 nonmotile, actin-filled microvilli (stereocilia) arranged in rows of increasing height and coupled to one another by morphologically distinct links: tip links, horizontal top connectors, shaft connectors, and ankle links; most hair bundles also possess a single motile kinocilium immediately adjacent to the tallest (outermost) row of stereocilia; a fifth link type, the kinocilial link, connects the kinocilium to its neighboring stereocilia

Subject: fused outer hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004528]
Value: coalescence of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) normally arrayed on cochlear outer hair cells, often resulting in giant stereocilia

Subject: decreased outer hair cell stereocilia number [MP:0004529]
Value: decreased number (or less than the expected 100 or so) of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) normally arrayed on cochlear outer hair cells

Subject: absent outer hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004530]
Value: complete absence of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) which are normally arrayed on cochlear outer hair cells

Subject: short outer hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004531]
Value: reduced length of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) which are normally arrayed on cochlear outer hair cells

Subject: abnormal inner hair cell stereociliary bundle morphology [MP:0004532]
Value: any structural anomaly or disruption of the typically linear or U-shaped pattern of arrangement of mechanosensitive hair bundles located at the apical end of cochlear IHCs; each hair bundle is normally composed of ~100 nonmotile, actin-filled microvilli (stereocilia) arranged in rows of increasing height and coupled to one another by morphologically distinct links: tip links, horizontal top connectors, shaft connectors, and ankle links; most hair bundles also possess a single motile kinocilium immediately adjacent to the tallest row of stereocilia; a fifth link type, the kinocilial link, connects the kinocilium to its neighboring stereocilia

Subject: fused inner hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004533]
Value: coalescence of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) normally arrayed on cochlear inner hair cells, often resulting in giant stereocilia

Subject: decreased inner hair cell stereocilia number [MP:0004534]
Value: decreased number (or less than the expected 100 or so) of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) normally arrayed on cochlear inner hair cells

Subject: absent inner hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004535]
Value: complete absence of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) which are normally arrayed on cochlear inner hair cells

Subject: short inner hair cell stereocilia [MP:0004536]
Value: reduced length of the nonmotile, actin-filled specialized microvilli (stereocilia) which are normally arrayed on cochlear inner hair cells

Subject: abnormal palatine bone horizontal plate morphology [MP:0004537]
Value: any structural anomaly of the bony plate of the palatine bone that normally fuses with maxillary shelf to form secondary (hard) palate

Subject: abnormal maxillary shelf morphology [MP:0004538]
Value: any structural anomaly of the bony projection of the maxilla that normally fuses with palatine shelf to form secondary (hard) palate

Subject: absent maxilla [MP:0004539]
Value: missing the upper bony framework of the mouth where the superior teeth are held

Subject: small maxilla [MP:0004540]
Value: reduced size of the upper bony framework of the mouth where the superior teeth are held

Subject: absent auditory tube [MP:0004541]
Value: absence of the tube connecting the tympanic cavity and the nasopharynx

Subject: impaired acrosome reaction [MP:0004542]
Value: reduced ability or inability to execute the cellular exocytosis of a single, anterior secretory granule following a sperm's attachment to the zona pellucida surrounding an oocyte

Subject: abnormal sperm physiology [MP:0004543]
Value: anomaly in the normal function of spermatozoa

Subject: absent esophagus [MP:0004544]
Value: absence of the part of the digestive canal through which food passes from the pharynx to the stomach

Subject: enlarged esophagus [MP:0004545]
Value: increased size of the part of the digestive canal through which food passes from the pharynx to the stomach

Subject: esophagus hyperplasia [MP:0004546]
Value: overdevelopment or increased size, usually due an increased number of cells of the esophagus

Subject: esophageal ulcer [MP:0004547]
Value: a lesion on the mucosal surface of the esophagus, usually produced by the sloughing of inflammatory necrotic tissue

Subject: dilated esophagus [MP:0004548]
Value: an expansion in the lumen volume of the part of the digestive canal through which food passes from the pharynx to the stomach

Subject: small trachea [MP:0004549]
Value: reduced size of the tube descending from the larynx and branching into the right and left main bronchi

Subject: short trachea [MP:0004550]
Value: reduced length of the tube descending from the larynx and branching into the right and left main bronchi

Subject: decreased tracheal cartilage ring number [MP:0004551]
Value: less than the 16-20 incomplete rings of hyaline cartilage forming the skeleton of the trachea

Subject: fused tracheal cartilage rings [MP:0004552]
Value: fusion of the 16-20 incomplete rings of hyaline cartilage that form the skeleton of the trachea

Subject: absent tracheal cartilage rings [MP:0004553]
Value: absence of the 16-20 incomplete rings of hyaline cartilage forming the skeleton of the trachea

Subject: small pharynx [MP:0004554]
Value: reduced size of the passage between the mouth and the posterior nares and the larynx and esophagus

Subject: pharynx hypoplasia [MP:0004555]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, of the passage between the mouth and the posterior nares and the larynx and esophagus

Subject: enlarged allantois [MP:0004556]
Value: increased size of the fetal membrane which contributes to the formation of the umbilical cord and placental blood vessels

Subject: dilated allantois [MP:0004557]
Value: an expansion in the volume of the fetal membrane which contributes to the formation of the umbilical cord and placental blood vessels, as by stretching or distention

Subject: delayed allantois development [MP:0004558]
Value: late onset of development of the fetal membrane which contributes to the formation of the umbilical cord and placental blood vessels

Subject: small allantois [MP:0004559]
Value: reduced size of the fetal membrane which contributes to the formation of the umbilical cord and placental blood vessels

Subject: abnormal chorionic plate morphology [MP:0004560]
Value: any structural anomaly of the portion of the chorion from which chorionic villi develop that establish a connection with the endometrium, giving rise to the fetal portion of the mature placenta

Subject: absent facial nerve [MP:0004561]
Value: absence of the sensory and motor nerve that supplies the muscles of facial expression and the expression and taste at the anterior two-thirds of the tongue

Subject: abnormal inner hair cell synaptic ribbon morphology [MP:0004562]
Value: any structural anomaly in the presynaptic active zone of mature cochlear IHCs which usually contain a single synaptic ribbon, i.e. a submicrometer, electron-dense structure tethering synaptic vesicles; each spiral ganglion neuron receives input from only one IHC synapse

Subject: absent active-zone-anchored inner hair cell synaptic ribbon [MP:0004563]
Value: absence or loss of the usually single synaptic ribbon, a characteristic osmiophilic, electron-dense structure to which synaptic vesicles are tethered at the active zone of the cochlear inner hair cell afferent synapse

Subject: enlarged myocardial fiber [MP:0004564]
Value: increased size of the terminally differentiated, non-proliferative, cardiac muscle fibers, the multinucleated muscle cells of the heart

Subject: small myocardial fiber [MP:0004565]
Value: decreased size of the terminally differentiated, non-proliferative, cardiac muscle fibers, the multinucleated muscle cells of the heart

Subject: myocardial fiber degeneration [MP:0004566]
Value: deterioration or destruction of the terminally differentiated, non-proliferative, cardiac muscle fibers, the multinucleated muscle cells of the heart

Subject: decreased myocardial fiber number [MP:0004567]
Value: decreased number of the terminally differentiated, non-proliferative, cardiac muscle fibers, the multinucleated muscle cells of the heart

Subject: fusion of glossopharyngeal and vagus nerve [MP:0004568]
Value: union of the ninth and tenth cranial nerves into a single structure

Subject: glossopharyngeal nerve hypoplasia [MP:0004569]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, of the sensory and autonomic axons to the parotid gland, carotid body, posterior third of the tongue; the branchial motor component contains motor fibers that innervate muscles that elevate the pharynx and larynx, and the tympanic branch supplies parasympathetic fibers to the otic ganglion

Subject: absent glossopharyngeal nerve [MP:0004570]
Value: absence of the sensory and autonomic axons to the parotid gland, carotid body, posterior third of the tongue; the branchial motor component contains motor fibers that innervate muscles that elevate the pharynx and larynx, and the tympanic branch supplies parasympathetic fibers to the otic ganglion

Subject: absent vagus nerve [MP:0004571]
Value: absence of the autonomic, sensory and motor axons of the tenth cranial nerve; it is primarily sensory but also has visceromotor components; it originates in the brain stem and controls many autonomic functions of the heart, lungs, stomach, pharynx, larynx, trachea, esophagus and other gastrointestinal tract components, and also controls some motor functions such as speech; the sensory branches mediate sensation from the pharynx, larynx, thorax and abdomen; it also innervates taste buds in the epiglottis

Subject: fusion of basioccipital and basisphenoid bone [MP:0004572]
Value: union of the basioccipital and basisphenoid bones into one structure, when this fusion does not normally occur (such as in a species where these bones normally persist as separate entities)

Subject: absent limb buds [MP:0004573]
Value: missing the mesenchymal outgrowth on the lateral trunk of the embryo that develops into the limbs

Subject: broad limb buds [MP:0004574]
Value: increased anterior-posterior width of the mesenchymal outgrowth on the lateral trunk of the embryo that develops into the limbs

Subject: small limb buds [MP:0004575]
Value: reduced size of the mesenchymal outgrowth on the lateral trunk of the embryo that develops into the limbs

Subject: abnormal embryonic autopod plate morphology [MP:0004576]
Value: any structural anomaly of transient  developing limb structure that forms by expansion of the distal end of the limb paddle and will give rise to the pedal appendages (e.g. hand, foot, paw)

Subject: abnormal cochlear hair cell inter-stereocilial links morphology [MP:0004577]
Value: any structural anomaly in the morphologically and biochemically distinct link types that extend between the stereocilia of cochlear hair bundles; link types can be distinguished by their relative sensitivities to treatment with calcium chelators and the protease subtilisin; in the mature mouse cochlea, tip links and horizontal top connectors are the only inter-stereocilial links associated with the hair bundle; ankle links and transient lateral links are both prominent features of developing auditory hair bundles

Subject: abnormal cochlear hair bundle tip links morphology [MP:0004578]
Value: any structural anomaly in single, three-stranded interrow filaments that extend obliquely from the tip of one stereocilium to the lateral side of an adjacent taller stereocilium; in the mouse, tip links are already detectable prenatally and persist throughout life; tips links are thought to gate the mechanotransducer channel, are lost from the cell surface after exposure to either calcium chelator BAPTA or lanthanum, and resist degradation by the protease subtilisin

Subject: abnormal cochlear hair bundle horizontal top connectors morphology [MP:0004579]
Value: any structural anomaly in the inter-stereocilial links that connect the top of a shorter stereocilium to an adjacent longer stereocilium at a short distance below the tip links; the appearance of horizontal top connectors, which persist into adulthood, occurs concomitant with this loss of ankle links; top connectors are essentially unaffected by treatment with subtilisin and EGTA

Subject: abnormal cochlear hair bundle transient lateral links morphology [MP:0004580]
Value: any structural anomaly in the fine lateral links that interconnect stereocilia at prenatal stages; transient lateral links diminish at early postnatal stages when ankle links appear at the base of stereocilia, and are essentially unaffected by treatment with subtilisin and EGTA

Subject: abnormal cochlear hair bundle ankle links morphology [MP:0004581]
Value: any structural anomaly in the long, single-stranded filaments that form a dense web or mesh around the base of cochlear hair bundles just above the region in which the stereocilia begin to taper down; in the mouse, ankle links are only a transient feature of the developing cochlear hair bundles, present predominantly from P2 though P9, but are absent by P12; ankle links are disrupted by treatment of hair cells with EGTA and subtilisin but not by La3+ and elastase

Subject: absent cochlear hair bundle ankle links [MP:0004582]
Value: absence of the long, single-stranded filaments that form a dense web or mesh around the base of cochlear hair bundles just above the region in which the stereocilia begin to taper down

Subject: abnormal vestibular hair bundle inter-stereocilial links [MP:0004583]
Value: any structural anomaly in the morphologically and biochemically distinct link types that extend between the stereocilia of vestibular hair bundles

Subject: abnormal vestibular hair bundle shaft connectors [MP:0004584]
Value: any structural anomaly in the links that connect the shafts of neighboring stereocilia in vestibular hair bundles; each shaft connector is composed of a ruthenium red-reactive, electron-dense particle that is connected to the plasma membrane by several fine strands of variable length

Subject: absent vestibular hair bundle shaft connectors [MP:0004585]
Value: absence of the inter-stereocilial links that connect the shafts of neighboring stereocilia in vestibular hair bundles

Subject: pillar cell degeneration [MP:0004586]
Value: degeneration or loss of the supporting cells that form the inner and outer walls of the tunnel in the organ of Corti

Subject: decreased cellular sensitivity to X-ray irradiation [MP:0004587]
Value: decreased incidence of cell death following exposure to X-ray irradiation

Subject: abnormal vestibular hair cell development [MP:0004588]
Value: atypical initial production, differentiation, migration or maturation of hair cells in the sensory epithelium of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear

Subject: abnormal cochlear hair cell development [MP:0004589]
Value: atypical initial production, differentiation, migration or maturation of the sensory epithelial cells of the cochlea

Subject: absent Deiters cells [MP:0004590]
Value: absence of the supporting cells of the spiral organ which are attached to the basement membrane and receive the hair cells between their free extremities

Subject: enlarged tectorial membrane [MP:0004591]
Value: increased size of the overlaying membrane of cochlear duct, an extracellular matrix of the inner ear that contacts the stereocilia bundles of specialized sensory hair cells

Subject: small mandible [MP:0004592]
Value: reduced size of the lower bony framework of the mouth where the inferior teeth are held

Subject: long mandible [MP:0004593]
Value: increased length of the lower bony framework of the mouth where the inferior teeth are held

Subject: abnormal mandibular coronoid process morphology [MP:0004594]
Value: any structural anomaly of the thin, flattened, triangular eminence that arises from the upper surface of the mandibular ramus (perpendicular portion); includes the attachment site to the temporal muscle

Subject: abnormal mandibular condyloid process morphology [MP:0004595]
Value: any structural anomaly of the round bump of bone and constricted neck portion that arises from the upper surface of the mandibular ramus (perpendicular portion) and articulates with the articular disk of the temporomandibular joint

Subject: abnormal mandibular angle morphology [MP:0004596]
Value: any structural anomaly of the portion of the mandible where the body of the mandible (horizontal portion) and the rami (perpendicular portions) meet; these normally unite nearly at right angles

Subject: increased susceptibility to noise-induced hearing loss [MP:0004597]
Value: greater than normal reduction in hearing sensitivity following exposure to acute noise that is injurious to the cochlea

Subject: abnormal cochlear basement membrane morphology [MP:0004598]
Value: any structural anomaly in the continuous basement membrane found within the membranous labyrinth of the cochlea, known to extend from the limbus, down to the inner sulcus, across the basilar membrane, up to the external sulcus to the spiral prominence and radiating into the spiral ligament ensheathing the root cell processes

Subject: abnormal vertebral arch morphology [MP:0004599]
Value: any structural anomaly of the dorsal bony and/or cartilaginous part of a vertebra, consisting of a pair of pedicles, a pair of laminae, and seven processes (four articular processes, two transverse processes, and one spinous process)

Subject: abnormal vertebral transverse process morphology [MP:0004600]
Value: any structural anomaly of the bony protrusions on either side of the arch of a vertebrae at the point where the lamina joins the pedicle, between the superior and inferior articular processes; muscles and ligaments attach to these processes

Subject: abnormal vertebral spinous process morphology [MP:0004601]
Value: any structural anomaly of the dorsal projection of the vertebral arch that projects backward and downward from the junction of the laminae, and serves for the attachment of muscles and ligaments

Subject: abnormal vertebral articular process morphology [MP:0004602]
Value: any structural anomaly of the bilateral flat projections that arise from the junctions of the pedicles and laminae

Subject: absent vertebral arch [MP:0004603]
Value: loss of the dorsal part of a vertebra, consisting of a pair of pedicles, a pair of laminae, and seven processes (four articular processes, two transverse processes, and one spinous process)

Subject: abnormal vertebral pedicle morphology [MP:0004604]
Value: any structural anomaly of the two short, thick processes, which project backward, one on either side, from the upper part of the body to the laminae

Subject: abnormal vertebral lamina morphology [MP:0004605]
Value: any structural anomaly of two broad plates directed dorsomedially from the pedicles; these fuse at the dorsal midline, and complete the dorsal wall of the vertebral foramen

Subject: absent vertebral spinous process [MP:0004606]
Value: missing the dorsal projection of the vertebral arch that projects backward and downward from the junction of the laminae, and serves for the attachment of muscles and ligaments

Subject: abnormal cervical atlas morphology [MP:0004607]
Value: any structural anomaly of the first (topmost, C1) cervical vertebra which supports the globe of the head

Subject: abnormal cervical axis morphology [MP:0004608]
Value: any structural anomaly of the second cervical vertebra (C2) which forms the pivot upon which the first cervical (atlas, C1) vertebra rotates

Subject: vertebral fusion [MP:0004609]
Value: the union of one or more vertebrae into a single structure

Subject: small vertebrae [MP:0004610]
Value: reduced size of the bony segments of the spinal column

Subject: increased susceptibility to ototoxicity-induced hearing loss [MP:0004611]
Value: greater than normal reduction in hearing sensitivity following exposure to an ototoxic compound, such as aminoglycoside-induced hearing loss mediated via a glutamate excitotoxic process

Subject: fusion of vertebral bodies [MP:0004612]
Value: improper union of the main cylindrical portion of adjacent vertebra ventral to the vertebral canal

Subject: fusion of vertebral arches [MP:0004613]
Value: improper union of the dorsal part of adjacent vertebra

Subject: caudal vertebral transformation [MP:0004614]
Value: homeotic transformation of any caudal vertebrae to adopt the fate of another vertebrae

Subject: cervical vertebral transformation [MP:0004615]
Value: homeotic transformation of any cervical vertebrae to adopt the fate of another vertebrae

Subject: lumbar vertebral transformation [MP:0004616]
Value: homeotic transformation of any lumbar vertebrae to adopt the fate of another vertebrae

Subject: sacral vertebral transformation [MP:0004617]
Value: homeotic transformation of any sacral vertebrae to adopt the fate of another vertebrae

Subject: thoracic vertebral transformation [MP:0004618]
Value: homeotic transformation of any thoracic vertebrae to adopt the fate of another vertebrae

Subject: caudal vertebral fusion [MP:0004619]
Value: the union of one or more caudal vertebrae into a single structure in species where this does not normally occur

Subject: cervical vertebral fusion [MP:0004620]
Value: the union of one or more cervical vertebrae into a single structure

Subject: lumbar vertebral fusion [MP:0004621]
Value: the union of one or more lumbar vertebrae into a single structure

Subject: sacral vertebral fusion [MP:0004622]
Value: the union of one or more sacral vertebrae into a single structure in species where this does not normally occur

Subject: thoracic vertebral fusion [MP:0004623]
Value: the union of one or more thoracic vertebrae into a single structure

Subject: abnormal thoracic cage morphology [MP:0004624]
Value: any structural anomaly of the bony and cartilaginous structure enclosing the thoracic cavity, consisting of the thoracic vertebrae, ribs, costal cartilages, and sternum

Subject: abnormal rib joint morphology [MP:0004625]
Value: any anomaly in the normal joining of the ribs to the vertebral column or to the sternum

Subject: vertebral compression [MP:0004626]
Value: appearance of vertebrae that are flattened laterally along the whole length such that they appear pressed together and take up less rostrocaudal space

Subject: abnormal trochanter morphology [MP:0004627]
Value: any structural anomaly of the bony prominences near the upper extremity of the femur; there are two in human (greater and lesser trochanters) and three in many other mammalian species (greater, lesser and third); these normally serve as attachment points for hip and thigh muscles

Subject: Deiters cell degeneration [MP:0004628]
Value: degeneration or loss of the supporting cells of the spiral organ which are attached to the basement membrane and receive the hair cells between their free extremities

Subject: abnormal spiral modiolar artery morphology [MP:0004629]
Value: any structural anomaly of the artery which parallels the spiral ganglion in the root of the spiral lamina of the modiolus, serving the ganglion and the cochlear duct and its contents

Subject: spiral modiolar artery stenosis [MP:0004630]
Value: abnormal narrowing of the artery which parallels the spiral ganglion in the root of the spiral lamina of the modiolus and serves the ganglion and the cochlear duct and its contents

Subject: abnormal auditory cortex morphology [MP:0004631]
Value: any structural anomaly in the region of the cerebral cortex that receives the auditory radiation from the medial geniculate body, a thalamic cell group receiving auditory input from the cochlear nuclei in the rhombencephalon and is responsible for processing of auditory (sound) information

Subject: abnormal cochlear OHC efferent innervation pattern [MP:0004632]
Value: any changes in the morphology or number of efferent terminals, occurring as clusters, in the cochlear OHC region; normally, medial olivocochlear neurons, which are primarily found in rostral and ventral periolivary regions, project mainly to the contralateral cochlea, and terminate directly on OHCs

Subject: abnormal cochlear IHC efferent innervation pattern [MP:0004633]
Value: any changes in the morphology of the normally dense plexus of efferent terminals that contact radial fibers of the spiral ganglion below cochlear IHCs or of the sparser plexus of terminals positioned around IHC somata; normally, lateral olivocochlear neurons, which are found in and/or around the lateral superior olive, project mainly to the ipsilateral cochlea and terminate mostly on dendritic fibers below IHCs

Subject: short metacarpal bones [MP:0004634]
Value: reduced length of the five bones of the forepaws that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges

Subject: short metatarsal bones [MP:0004635]
Value: reduced length of the five bones of the hindpaws that articulate proximally with the cuneiform and cuboid bones of the tarsus and distally with the phalanges

Subject: decreased metacarpal bone number [MP:0004636]
Value: reduced number of the five bones of the forepaws/hands that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges

Subject: metacarpal bone hypoplasia [MP:0004637]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, of the five bones of the forepaws/hands that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges

Subject: elongated metacarpal bones [MP:0004638]
Value: increased length of the five bones of the forepaws/hands that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges

Subject: fused metacarpal bones [MP:0004639]
Value: improper union of one or more of the five bones of the forepaws/hands that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges

Subject: decreased metatarsal bone number [MP:0004640]
Value: reduced number of the five bones of the hindpaws/feet that articulate proximally with the cuneiform and cuboid bones of the tarsus and distally with the phalanges

Subject: elongated metatarsal bones [MP:0004641]
Value: increased length of the five bones of the hindpaws/feet that articulate proximally with the cuneiform and cuboid bones of the tarsus and distally with the phalanges

Subject: fused metatarsal bones [MP:0004642]
Value: improper union of the five bones of the hindpaws/feet that articulate proximally with the cuneiform and cuboid bones of the tarsus and distally with the phalanges

Subject: abnormal vertebrae number [MP:0004643]
Value: altered number of the bony segments of the spinal column

Subject: increased vertebrae number [MP:0004644]
Value: an increase over the normal number of the bony segments of the spinal column

Subject: decreased vertebrae number [MP:0004645]
Value: a reduction from the normal number of the bony segments of the spinal column

Subject: decreased cervical vertebrae number [MP:0004646]
Value: reduced number of the seven bony segments of the spine located anterior to the thoracic vertebrae and caudal to the skull

Subject: decreased lumbar vertebrae number [MP:0004647]

Subject: short vertebral column [MP:0004704]

Subject: short vertebral body [MP:0004706]

Subject: decreased platelet serotonin level [MP:0004725]

Subject: absent epididymis [MP:0004727]

Subject: abnormal circulating gastrin level [MP:0004730]

Subject: obsolete absent brainstem auditory evoked potential [MP:0004763]

Subject: obsolete increased brainstem auditory evoked potential [MP:0004764]

Subject: decreased susceptibility to systemic lupus erythematosus [MP:0004802]

Subject: decreased susceptibility to autoimmune diabetes [MP:0004804]

Subject: abnormal somite size [MP:0005222]

Subject: abnormal palatine bone morphology [MP:0005249]

Subject: ectopia lentis [MP:0005263]

Subject: abnormal metabolism [MP:0005266]

Subject: abnormal occipital bone morphology [MP:0005269]

Subject: abnormal fatty acid level [MP:0005280]

Subject: increased fatty acid level [MP:0005281]

Subject: decreased fatty acid level [MP:0005282]

Subject: decreased oxygen consumption [MP:0005290]

Subject: decreased susceptibility to atherosclerosis [MP:0005341]

Subject: increased circulating aspartate transaminase level [MP:0005343]

Subject: decreased susceptibility to prion infection [MP:0005363]

Subject: decreased susceptibility to fungal infection [MP:0005398]

Subject: decreased plasma anion gap [MP:0005626]

Subject: abnormal malleus processus brevis morphology [MP:0010324]

Subject: thin malleus neck [MP:0010328]

Subject: abnormal lipoprotein level [MP:0010329]
Value: any anomaly in the concentrations of any complex or compound containing both lipid and protein, are important components of biological membranes and myelin, and participate in lipid transport

Subject: abnormal circulating lipoprotein level [MP:0010330]
Value: any anomaly in the concentration in the blood of any complex or compound containing both lipid and protein, are important components of biological membranes and myelin, and participate in lipid transport

Subject: abnormal apolipoprotein level [MP:0010331]

Subject: abnormal circulating apolipoprotein level [MP:0010332]

Subject: abnormal circulating apolipoprotein E level [MP:0010333]

Subject: pleural effusion [MP:0010334]

Subject: fused first pharyngeal arch [MP:0010335]

Subject: increased desmoid tumor incidence [MP:0010338]
Value: greater than the expected number of a monoclonal, fibroblastic proliferation arising in musculoaponeurotic structures in a specific population in a given time period; this connective tissue hyperplasia infiltrates locally, recurs frequently after resection but does not metastasize; this tumor may occur at the site of any fascia, but in particular in muscle

Subject: increased cardiac fibroma incidence [MP:0010339]

Subject: increased lung fibroma incidence [MP:0010340]
