Subject: increased mammary gland fibroma incidence [MP:0010341]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign tumor of fibrous or fully developed connective tissue in the mammary gland, in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased facial angiofibroma incidence [MP:0010342]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign tumor of fibrous or fully developed connective tissue on the face, in a specific population in a given time period; appear as red or yellow papules containing dilated vascular channels

Subject: increased lipoma incidence [MP:0010343]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign neoplasia derived from lipoblasts or lipocytes of white or brown fat, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased hibernoma incidence [MP:0010344]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign neoplasm derived from brown fat occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased thyroid C-cell carcinoma incidence [MP:0010345]

Subject: increased thyroid carcinoma incidence [MP:0010346]
Value: greater than the expected number of a malignant epithelial neoplasms of the thyroid gland, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: osseous metaplasia [MP:0010347]

Subject: increased pancreatic islet cell carcinoma incidence [MP:0010348]
Value: greater than the expected number of malignant neoplasms arising in the pancreatic islet cells, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased teratocarcinoma incidence [MP:0010349]
Value: greater than the expected number of a mixed germ cell neoplasm contaning elements of embryonal carcinoma and teratoma, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased pituitary adenohypophysis tumor incidence [MP:0010350]
Value: greater than the expected number of neoplasms in the anterior part of the pituitary that secretes a variety of hormones, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased pituitary melanotroph tumor incidence [MP:0010351]
Value: greater than the expected number of neoplasms derived from the cells of intermediate pituitary that produce melanocyte stimulating hormone and other peptides from the post-translational processing of pro-opiomelanocortin (POMC)

Subject: gastrointestinal tract polyps [MP:0010352]
Value: abnormal tissue masses that protrude into the lumen of the gastrointestinal tract and are tethered to the wall of the gastrointestinal tract

Subject: increased odontoma incidence [MP:0010353]
Value: greater than the expected number of a hamartomatous odontogenic tumor composed of enamel, dentin, cementum, and pulp tissue that may or may not be arranged in the form of a tooth, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased odontosarcoma incidence [MP:0010354]
Value: greater than the expected number of an a gnathic malignant connective tissue tumor in which the epithelial component is benign and the proliferative mesenchymal component is malignant, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: abnormal first pharyngeal arch artery morphology [MP:0010355]
Value: any structural anomaly of the vessels formed within the first pair of branchial arches in embryogenesis

Subject: abnormal second pharyngeal arch artery morphology [MP:0010356]
Value: any structural anomaly of the vessels formed within the second pair of branchial arches in embryogenesis

Subject: increased prostate gland tumor incidence [MP:0010357]
Value: greater than the expected number of neoplams in the prostate gland occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: abnormal free fatty acids level [MP:0010358]

Subject: increased liver free fatty acids level [MP:0010359]

Subject: decreased liver free fatty acids level [MP:0010360]
Value: reduced liver concentration of the fatty acids which occur in plasma as a result of lipolysis in adipose tissue or when plasma triacyglycerols are taken into tissues

Subject: increased gangliosarcoma incidence [MP:0010361]
Value: greater than the expected number of a highly aggressive malignant neoplasm arising from mature ganglionic neurons, in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased ganglioneuroma incidence [MP:0010362]

Subject: increased fibrosarcoma incidence [MP:0010363]
Value: greater than the expected number of a highly aggressive malignant neoplasm arising from fibrous connective tissue, in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased fibroadenoma incidence [MP:0010364]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign mammary gland tumor composed of both fibrous tissue and glandular tissue, in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased thymus tumor incidence [MP:0010365]
Value: greater than the expected number of neoplams in the thymus occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased adrenal cortical tumor incidence [MP:0010366]
Value: greater than the expected number of neoplams in the adrenal cortex occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased spindle cell carcinoma incidence [MP:0010367]

Subject: abnormal lymphatic system physiology [MP:0010368]
Value: any functional anomaly of the interconnected system of spaces, organs and vessels between body tissues and organs through which fluid, fats, proteins, and lymphocytes are transported to the bloodstream as lymph, and microorganisms and other debris are removed from tissues

Subject: abnormal thalamus neuron morphology [MP:0010369]
Value: any structural anomaly of the impulse-conducting cells in the thalamus or its parts, a midline paired symmetrical structure between the cerebral cortex and midbrain within the brain that controls the flow of information to the cortex

Subject: abnormal throat morphology [MP:0010370]
Value: any structural anomaly in the anterior part of the neck, in front of the vertebral column comprising the pharynx and larynx

Subject: abnormal epiglottis morphology [MP:0010371]
Value: any structural anomaly of the most superior of the laryngeal cartilages, which is found at the root of the tongue and folds back over the entrance to the larynx during swallowing, preventing inhalation of food or drink

Subject: throat cyst [MP:0010372]
Value: presence of fluid-filled usually benign growths in the passage from the mouth to the pharynx

Subject: myeloid hyperplasia [MP:0010373]
Value: greater than normal number of nucleated cells of the myeloid lineage (a monocyte, granulocyte, or mast cell), found in blood or other tissue

Subject: bilirubinate stones [MP:0010374]
Value: caliculi in the gallbladder or a bile duct that is composed of calcium bilirubinate

Subject: increased kidney iron level [MP:0010375]
Value: increase in the amount of iron present in the renal tissue

Subject: decreased kidney iron level [MP:0010376]
Value: reduction in the amount of iron present in the renal tissue

Subject: abnormal gut flora balance [MP:0010377]
Value: anomaly in the ratio of microorganisms that live in the digestive tracts of animals, many of which perform symbiotic functions to the host

Subject: increased respiratory quotient [MP:0010378]
Value: increase in the ratio of the volume of carbon dioxide released to oxygen consumed by a body tissue or an organism compared to controls

Subject: decreased respiratory quotient [MP:0010379]
Value: reduction in the ratio of the volume of carbon dioxide released to oxygen consumed by a body tissue or an organism compared to controls

Subject: abnormal inner cell mass apoptosis [MP:0010380]
Value: the cells of the blastocyst that develop into the body of the embryo are undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: abnormal dosage compensation [MP:0010381]
Value: anomaly in the process of compensating for the two-fold variation in X:autosome chromosome ratios between sexes by a global activation or inactivation of all, or most of, genes on one or both of the X chromosomes

Subject: abnormal dosage compensation, by inactivation of X chromosome [MP:0010382]
Value: anomaly in the process of compensating for the two-fold variation in X-chromosome:autosome ratios between sexes by a global inactivation of all, or most of, the genes on one of the X-chromosomes in the XX sex

Subject: increased adenoma incidence [MP:0010383]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign epithelial neoplasm with a glandular organization, occurring in a specific population in a given time period; this tumor type usually does not invade or infiltrate surrounding tissue but may remain a benign tumor or progress to malignancy

Subject: increased renal carcinoma incidence [MP:0010384]
Value: greater than the expected number of malignant neoplasms arising from kidney epithelial tissue, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: abnormal glycinergic neuron morphology [MP:0010385]
Value: any structural anomaly of the neurons that utilize glycine as a neurotransmitter

Subject: abnormal urinary bladder physiology [MP:0010386]
Value: any functional anomaly of the distensible musculomembranous organ that serves to collect and store urine excreted by the kidneys

Subject: abnormal Bergmann glial cell morphology [MP:0010387]
Value: any structural anomaly of one or more astrocyte-type glia cells associated with Purkinje cells in the cerebellum

Subject: abnormal Bergmann glial cell differentiation [MP:0010388]
Value: abnormal formation of the astrocyte-type glia cells associated with Purkinje cells in the cerebellum

Subject: mosaic coat color [MP:0010389]
Value: a random coat color pattern due to genetically different populations of cells in the skin e.g. as the result of X-inactivation

Subject: increased adrenocortical adenoma incidence [MP:0010390]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign epithelial neoplasm with a glandular organization arising in the adrenal cortex, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: increased rhabdomyoma incidence [MP:0010391]
Value: greater than the expected number of a benign neoplasm derived from striated muscle and comprised of an encapsulated mass of polygonal cells, occurring in a specific population in a given time period

Subject: prolonged QRS complex duration [MP:0010392]
Value: increase in the length of time of the largest-amplitude portion of the ECG, caused by currents generated when the ventricles depolarize prior to their contraction; prolongation of the QRS complex duration reflects slowed conduction in the heart

Subject: shortened QRS complex duration [MP:0010393]
Value: decrease in the length of time of the largest-amplitude portion of the ECG, caused by currents generated when the ventricles depolarize prior to their contraction; prolongation of the QRS complex duration reflects slowed conduction in the heart

Subject: decreased QRS amplitude [MP:0010394]
Value: reduction in the size (height or maximum displacement) of the largest-amplitude portion of the ECG, caused by currents generated when the ventricles depolarize prior to their contraction, suggesting ventricular excitation defects

Subject: abnormal pharyngeal arch development [MP:0010395]
Value: abnormal formation of the of the transient structures of the embryo that develop into regions of the head, neck and ears

Subject: ectopic pharyngeal arch [MP:0010396]
Value: abnormal location of any of the transient structures of the embryo resulting in misplaced regions of the head, neck and/or ears

Subject: abnormal otic capsule development [MP:0010397]
Value: any anomaly in the embryonic cartilage covering that surrounds the inner ear mechanism and develops into bone

Subject: decreased liver glycogen level [MP:0010398]
Value: less than the normal concentration of a readily converted carbohydrate reserve in liver

Subject: decreased skeletal muscle glycogen level [MP:0010399]
Value: less than the normal concentration of a readily converted carbohydrate reserve in skeletal muscle

Subject: increased liver glycogen level [MP:0010400]
Value: greater than the normal concentration of a readily converted carbohydrate reserve in liver

Subject: increased skeletal muscle glycogen level [MP:0010401]
Value: greater than the normal concentration of a readily converted carbohydrate reserve in skeletal muscle

Subject: ventricular septal defect [MP:0010402]
Value: abnormal communications between the two lower chambers of the heart, including such defects in the perimembranous, inlet, outlet (infundibular), central muscular, marginal muscular, or apical muscular regions

Subject: atrial septal defect [MP:0010403]
Value: abnormal communications between the two upper chambers of the heart, including such defects in any or all of the ostium primum, ostium secundum, sinus venosus, and coronary sinus regions

Subject: ostium primum atrial septal defect [MP:0010404]
Value: interatrial communication (atrial septal defect) through the most anterior and inferior aspect of the atrial septum

Subject: ostium secundum atrial septal defect [MP:0010405]
Value: large interatrial communication (atrial septal defect) through the center of the wall between the atria at the site of the foramen ovale and the ostium secundum

Subject: common atrium [MP:0010406]
Value: absence of the thin membranous structure between the two heart atria, resulting in the appearance of one upper chamber

Subject: coronary sinus atrial septal defect [MP:0010407]
Value: interatrial communication (atrial septal defect) through coronary sinus orifice, that is characterized by the absence of at least a portion of the common wall that separates the coronary sinus and the left atrium; interatrial shunting occurs through the defect in the wall on the left atrial side, which is continuous with the orifice of the coronary sinus opening on the right atrial side of the septum

Subject: sinus venosus atrial septal defect [MP:0010408]
Value: interatrial communication (atrial septal defect) through the upper atrial septum and that is contiguous with the superior vena cava (SVC); it is rostral and posterior to the fossa ovalis (where secundum type defects occur) and is separate from it

Subject: cor triatriatum [MP:0010409]
Value: a heart with 3 atria, is in which either the left or right atrium is divided into 2 parts by a fold of tissue, a membrane, or a fibromuscular band that may vary significantly in size and shape, appearing similar to a diaphragm or funnel-shaped, bandlike, entirely intact (imperforate) or contain 1 or more openings (fenestrations) ranging from small, restrictive-type to large and widely open

Subject: cor triatriatum sinistrum [MP:0010410]
Value: a heart with 3 atria, is in which the left atrium is divided into 2 parts by a fold of tissue, a membrane, or a fibromuscular band

Subject: cor triatriatum dextrum [MP:0010411]
Value: a heart with 3 atria, is in which the right atrium is divided into 2 parts by a fold of tissue, a membrane, or a fibromuscular band

Subject: atrioventricular septal defect [MP:0010412]
Value: defects in the thin membranous structure between the right atrium and left ventricle that arise from faulty development of the embryonic endocardial cushions; the spectrum ranges from a primum atrial septal defect and cleft mitral valve, known as a partial atrioventricular septal defect (partial AVSD), to defects of both the primum atrial septum and inlet ventricular septum and the presence of a common atrioventricular valve, referred to as complete atrioventricular septal defect (complete AVSD)

Subject: complete atrioventricular septal defect [MP:0010413]
Value: a type of atrioventricular septal defect in which a single atrioventricular valve annulus, a common atrioventricular valve, and a defect of the inlet ventricular septum are observed; deficiency of the atrioventricular septum also results in the presence of a large primum atrial septal defect

Subject: partial atrioventricular septal defect [MP:0010414]
Value: a type of atrioventricular septal defect in which the endocardial cushion defects present have an interatrial communication but lack an interventricular communication; the mitral and tricuspid annuli are separate but one or more additional features are present, including primum atrial septal defect (ASD), inlet ventricular septal defect (VSD), cleft of the anterior mitral valve leaflet, and wide anteroseptal tricuspid valve commissure or cleft septal tricuspid leaflet

Subject: intermediate atrioventricular septal defect [MP:0010415]
Value: a type of atrioventricular septal defect in which a partial AVSD is present together with a small interventricular communication; a single valvar annulus is usually present where the anterior and posterior bridging leaflets fuse overlying the ventricular septum, with two distinct valvar components observed

Subject: interventricular septum membranous part aneurysm [MP:0010416]
Value: a a saclike thinning, stretching and widening of the ventricular membranous septum resulting from weakening of the membraneous septum wall

Subject: subarterial ventricular septal defect [MP:0010417]
Value: abnormal communications between the two lower chambers of the heart, located beneath the pulmonic valve, communicating with the RV outflow tract above the supraventricular crest, and are associated with aortic regurgitation secondary to the prolapse of the right aortic cusp

Subject: perimembraneous ventricular septal defect [MP:0010418]
Value: abnormal communications between the two lower chambers of the heart, occurring in the membranous septum with defects in the adjacent muscular portion of the septum; it is generally located in the LV outflow tract just below the aortic valve, associated with pouches or aneurysms of the septal leaflet of the tricuspid valve, which may partially or completely close the defect; an LV-to-RA shunt may also be associated with this defect

Subject: inlet ventricular septal defect [MP:0010419]
Value: abnormal communications between the two lower chambers of the heart, located posterior to the septal leaflet of the tricuspid valve and which are not associated with defects of the atrioventricular valves

Subject: muscular ventricular septal defect [MP:0010420]
Value: abnormal communications between the two lower chambers of the heart, involving the muscular septum and often occurring as multiple communications, and includes central muscular or midmuscular, apical, or marginal communications when the defect is along the RV-septal junction; any single defect observed from the LV aspect may have several openings on the RV aspect

Subject: ventricular aneurysm [MP:0010421]
Value: thinning, stretching and bulging of a weakened ventricular wall

Subject: heart right ventricle hypoplasia [MP:0010422]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size of the heart right ventricle, often due to a reduced number of cells

Subject: heart right ventricle aneurysm [MP:0010423]
Value: thinning, stretching and bulging of a weakened heart right ventricular wall

Subject: double chambered heart right ventricle [MP:0010424]
Value: septated right ventricle caused by the presence of abnormally located or hypertrophied cardiac muscle bands that divide the ventricular cavity into a proximal and a distal chamber; the muscle bundles typically run between an area located in the ventricular septum, beneath the level of the septal leaflet of the tricuspid valve, and the anterior wall of the right ventricle

Subject: abnormal heart and great vessel attachment [MP:0010425]
Value: any anomaly in the in the position or pattern of the connection site of the heart to any of the primary vessels, including the superior vena cavae, inferior vena cavae, pulmonary artery, pulmonary veins, and aorta

Subject: abnormal heart and great artery attachment [MP:0010426]
Value: any anomaly in the in the position or pattern of the connection site of the heart to any of the great arteries, including the pulmonary artery and aorta

Subject: double outlet left ventricle [MP:0010427]
Value: both the aorta and the pulmonary trunk originate from the left ventricle

Subject: abnormal heart right ventricle outflow tract morphology [MP:0010428]
Value: any structural anomaly of the anteriosuperior, smooth-walled portion of the cavity of the right ventricle, beginning at the supraventricular crest and terminating in the pulmonary trunk

Subject: abnormal heart left ventricle outflow tract morphology [MP:0010429]
Value: any structural anomaly of the anterosuperior fibrous portion of the left ventricle that connects to the ascending aorta

Subject: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection, supracardiac [MP:0010430]
Value: the pulmonary veins drain via a common vein into the right superior vena cava, left superior vena cava, or their tributaries instead of the left atrium

Subject: atrial situs inversus [MP:0010431]
Value: anomaly in the asymmetry of the cardiac atria such that atria on both the left and right side have the morphology normally seen on the opposite side of the body

Subject: common ventricle [MP:0010432]
Value: the presence of only one working lower chamber in the heart, usually with a virtual absence of the ventricular septum and usually present in conjunction with double inlet left or right ventricle

Subject: double inlet heart left ventricle [MP:0010433]
Value: congenital heart defect in which both atriums are connected to the left ventricle, with a hypoplastic right ventricle often present, which may be on the opposite side of the heart

Subject: double inlet heart right ventricle [MP:0010434]
Value: congenital heart defect in which both atriums are connected to the right ventricle, with a hypoplastic left ventricle often present

Subject: abnormal heart atrium and ventricle connection [MP:0010435]
Value: any anomaly in the in the position or pattern of the connection site of the heart atrium to the ventricles, usually occurring through the atrioventricular valves

Subject: abnormal coronary sinus morphology [MP:0010436]
Value: any structural anomaly of the short trunk that recieves most of the cardiac veins carrying the blood from the myocardium and delivers it to the right atrium, with the sinoatrial connection occurring between the inferior vena cava and the atrioventricular orifice

Subject: absent coronary sinus [MP:0010437]
Value: absence of the short trunk that recieves most of the cardiac veins carrying the blood from the myocardium and delivers it to the right atrium

Subject: pulmonary vein stenosis [MP:0010438]
Value: a stricture or occlusion of the lumen of the pulmonary vein

Subject: abnormal hepatic vein morphology [MP:0010439]
Value: any structural anomaly of the veins that drain blood from the liver and terminate in three large openings to the inferior vena cava below the diaphragm and into smaller openings in more inferior positions

Subject: anomalous pulmonary venous connection [MP:0010440]
Value: abnormal development and attachment of the four pulmonary veins that normally attach to the left atrium of the heart, resulting in either partial or complete anomalous drainage back into the systemic venous circulation via an anomalous connection to the right atrium, the superior or inferior vena cava, the innominate vein, the coronary sinus or the left subclavian artery

Subject: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection [MP:0010441]
Value: abnormal development and attachment of all four pulmonary veins that normally attach to the left atrium of the heart, resulting in complete anomalous drainage back into the systemic venous circulation via an anomalous connection to the right atrium, the superior or inferior vena cava, the innominate vein, the coronary sinus or the left subclavian artery; in TAPVC, none of the four pulmonary veins are attached to the left atrium

Subject: partial anomalous pulmonary venous connection [MP:0010442]
Value: abnormal development and attachment of one to three of the four pulmonary veins that normally attach to the left atrium of the heart, resulting in partial drainage back into the systemic venous circulation via an anomalous connection to the right atrium, the superior or inferior vena cava, the innominate vein, the coronary sinus or the left subclavian artery; in PAPVC, at least one pulmonary vein remains attached to the left atrium

Subject: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection, intracardiac [MP:0010443]
Value: the pulmonary veins connect directly to the right side of heart (eg, coronary sinus or directly to the right atrium) instead of the left atrium

Subject: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection, infracardiac [MP:0010444]
Value: the common pulmonary vein travels down anterior to the esophagus through the diaphragm to connect to the portal venous system instead of the left atrium

Subject: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection, mixed [MP:0010445]
Value: the right and left pulmonary veins drain to different sites other than the left atrium; for example, the left pulmonary veins into the left vertical vein to the left innominate, and/or the right pulmonary veins directly into the right atrium or coronary sinus

Subject: heart left ventricle hypoplasia [MP:0010446]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size of the heart left ventricle, often due to a reduced number of cells

Subject: heart left ventricle aneurysm [MP:0010447]
Value: thinning, stretching and bulging of a weakened heart left ventricular wall

Subject: heart left ventricle outflow tract stenosis [MP:0010448]
Value: abnormal constriction or narrowing of the portion of the left ventricle through which blood normally flows into the aorta

Subject: heart right ventricle outflow tract stenosis [MP:0010449]
Value: abnormal constriction or narrowing of part of the anteriosuperior, smooth-walled portion of the cavity of the right ventricle, beginning at the supraventricular crest and terminating in the pulmonary trunk

Subject: atrial septal aneurysm [MP:0010450]
Value: a saclike thinning, stretching and widening of the heart atrial septum resulting from weakening of the septum wall

Subject: kidney microaneurysm [MP:0010451]
Value: focal dilation of arteriocapillary junctions in the kidney

Subject: retina microaneurysm [MP:0010452]
Value: focal dilation of arteriocapillary junctions in the retina

Subject: abnormal coronary vein morphology [MP:0010453]
Value: any structural anomaly of any of the veins that return blood from the heart muscles to the right atrium through the coronary sinus

Subject: abnormal truncus arteriosus septation [MP:0010454]
Value: anomaly in the process of dividing the common arterial trunk arising out of both heart ventricles to divide into the aorta and pulmonary artery during development

Subject: aortopulmonary window [MP:0010455]
Value: a defect between the great vessels that results from failure of the conotruncal ridges to fuse resulting in an abnormal communication between the aorta and the pulmonary arteries

Subject: hemitruncus [MP:0010456]
Value: congenital heart defect in which the origin of a pulmonary artery, usually the right, arises from the ascending aorta instead of the pulmonary trunk with the aortic and pulmonary valves remaining separate

Subject: pulmonary artery stenosis [MP:0010457]
Value: constriction or narrowing of the pulmonary artery

Subject: pulmonary trunk hypoplasia [MP:0010458]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size of the region of the pulmonary artery that arises from the right ventricle to the division of the right and left pulmonary artery, usually due to reduced cell number

Subject: supravalvar pulmonary trunk stenosis [MP:0010459]
Value: diffuse constriction or narrowing of the pulmonary trunk distal to the pulmonary valve

Subject: pulmonary artery hypoplasia [MP:0010460]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size of the artery that arises from the right ventricle and conveys unaerated blood to the lungs, usually due to reduced cell number

Subject: discontinuous pulmonary artery [MP:0010461]
Value: one or more pulmonary arteries is disconnected from the main pulmonary trunk and arises from a patent ductus arteriosus

Subject: pulmonary artery aneurysm [MP:0010462]
Value: a protruding sac formed by the dilation of the wall of a pulmonary artery resulting from a weakening of the vessel wall

Subject: aorta stenosis [MP:0010463]
Value: diffuse constriction or narrowing of the aorta

Subject: abnormal aortic arch and aortic arch branch attachment [MP:0010464]

Subject: myocardium hypoplasia [MP:0010500]

Subject: abnormal hippocampus stratum oriens morphology [MP:0011150]

Subject: superior-inferior ventricles [MP:0011254]
Value: an abnormality in which the heart ventricles are in a superior-inferior relationship due to abnormal displacement of the ventricular mass along the horizontal plane of its long axis; this frequently occurs together with criss-cross atrio-ventricular relationships

Subject: abnormal anterior visceral endoderm cell migration [MP:0011255]
Value: any anomaly in the movement of the cells of the extraembryonic tissue that is responsible for the proper orientation of the anterior-posterior axis of the embryo and for appropriate patterning of adjacent embryonic tissue

Subject: abnormal neural fold morphology [MP:0011256]
Value: any structural anomaly of the elevated margins of the neural groove

Subject: abnormal head fold morphology [MP:0011257]
Value: any structural anomaly of the crescent-shaped, ventrally located fold of the embryonic disc at the future cephalic end of the developing embryo; it constitutes the first body fold, and initiates brain, foregut and heart development

Subject: abnormal tail fold morphology [MP:0011258]
Value: any structural anomaly of the crescent-shaped, ventrally located fold of the embryonic disc at the future caudal end of the developing embryo

Subject: abnormal cephalic neural fold morphology [MP:0011259]
Value: any structural anomaly of the elevated margins of the neural groove that are located in the future cephalic region of the embryo

Subject: abnormal head mesenchyme morphology [MP:0011260]
Value: any structural anomaly of the primordial embryonic connective tissue of the developing head, consisting of mesenchymal cells supported in interlaminar jelly, that derive mostly from the mesoderm and contribute to head connective tissue, bone and musculature in conjunction with cranial neural crest cells

Subject: abnormal limb mesenchyme morphology [MP:0011261]
Value: any structural anomaly in the primordial embryonic connective tissue of the developing limbs, autopods and digits, consisting of mesenchymal cells supported in interlaminar jelly, that derive mostly from the mesoderm and contribute to limb connective tissue, bone and musculature in conjunction with myotome cells

Subject: abnormal pharyngeal arch mesenchyme morphology [MP:0011262]
Value: any structural anomaly in the primordial embryonic connective tissue associated with the branchial arches, consisting of mesenchymal cells supported in interlaminar jelly, that derive mostly from the mesoderm and contribute to facial and cranial nerve-associated structures

Subject: abnormal spleen mesenchyme morphology [MP:0011263]
Value: any structural anomaly of the embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing spleen

Subject: abnormal cardiac mesenchyme morphology [MP:0011264]
Value: any structural anomaly of the embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing cardiac structures

Subject: abnormal pancreas mesenchyme morphology [MP:0011265]
Value: any structural anomaly of the embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing pancreas

Subject: abnormal frontonasal mesenchyme morphology [MP:0011266]
Value: any structural anomaly of the embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the frontonasal region of the head

Subject: abnormal excitatory postsynaptic current amplitude [MP:0011267]
Value: anomaly in the size (height or maximum displacement) or shape of the evoked excitatory postsynaptic current wave

Subject: biphasic excitatory postsynaptic current amplitude [MP:0011268]
Value: the appearance of two peaks instead of one peak in the evoked excitatory postsynaptic current wave

Subject: increased excitatory postsynaptic current amplitude [MP:0011269]
Value: increase in the size (height or maximum displacement) of the evoked excitatory postsynaptic current wave

Subject: decreased excitatory postsynaptic current amplitude [MP:0011270]
Value: reduction in the size (height or maximum displacement) of the evoked excitatory postsynaptic current wave

Subject: prolonged excitatory postsynaptic current rise time [MP:0011271]
Value: an increase in the time required for a signal to change from resting to the peak amplitude value in the evoked excitatory postsynaptic current wave

Subject: short excitatory postsynaptic current rise time [MP:0011272]
Value: an decrease in the time required for a signal to change from resting to the peak amplitude value in the evoked excitatory postsynaptic current wave

Subject: abnormal behavioral response to light [MP:0011275]
Value: unexpected change in the activity of an organism (in terms of movement, outward responses) as a result of a light stimulus, electromagnetic radiation of wavelengths classified as infrared, visible or ultraviolet light

Subject: increased tail pigmentation [MP:0011276]
Value: visually detectable excess of pigment present on the tail surface

Subject: decreased tail pigmentation [MP:0011277]
Value: visually detectable dilution of pigment present on the tail surface

Subject: increased ear pigmentation [MP:0011278]
Value: visually detectable excess of pigment present in the outer ear

Subject: decreased ear pigmentation [MP:0011279]
Value: visually detectable dilution of pigment present in the outer ear

Subject: abnormal flank coat pigmentation [MP:0011280]
Value: irregular or unusual pigmentation of the hair between the last rib and the hip

Subject: abnormal olfactory epithelium cilium morphology [MP:0011281]
Value: any structural anomaly of the cilia of the epithelial cells that line the interior of the nose

Subject: increased podocyte apoptosis [MP:0011282]
Value: increase in the number of podocytes undergoing programmed cell death; podocyte apoptosis is an early step in the pathophysiological progression to proteinuria and glomerulosclerosis

Subject: abnormal erythropoietin level [MP:0011283]
Value: anomalous fluid or tissue concentration of a sialic acid-containing glycoprotein hormone that enhances erythropoiesis and participates in wound healing; it is formed in the kidney and liver and can be detected in plasma and urine

Subject: abnormal circulating erythropoietin level [MP:0011284]
Value: anomalous blood concentration of a sialic acid-containing glycoprotein hormone that enhances erythropoiesis and participates in wound healing; it is formed in the kidney and liver and can be detected in plasma and urine

Subject: increased circulating erythropoietin level [MP:0011285]
Value: greater blood concentration of a sialic acid-containing glycoprotein hormone that enhances erythropoiesis and participates in wound healing; it is formed in the kidney and liver and can be detected in plasma and urine

Subject: decreased circulating erythropoietin level [MP:0011286]
Value: reduced blood concentration of a sialic acid-containing glycoprotein hormone that enhances erythropoiesis and participates in wound healing; it is formed in the kidney and liver and can be detected in plasma and urine

Subject: increased erythropoietin level [MP:0011287]
Value: greater fluid or tissue concentration of a sialic acid-containing glycoprotein hormone that enhances erythropoiesis and participates in wound healing; it is formed in the kidney and liver and can be detected in plasma and urine

Subject: decreased erythropoietin level [MP:0011288]
Value: reduced fluid or tissue concentration of a sialic acid-containing glycoprotein hormone that enhances erythropoiesis and participates in wound healing; it is formed in the kidney and liver and can be detected in plasma and urine

Subject: abnormal nephron number [MP:0011289]
Value: anomaly in the total number of the filtering units of the kidney; nephron number can be used as an index of the efficiency of ureteric branching and nephrogenesis

Subject: decreased nephron number [MP:0011290]
Value: reduction in the total number of filtering units of the kidney

Subject: nephron necrosis [MP:0011291]
Value: morphological changes resulting from pathological death of nephron tissue; usually due to irreversible damage

Subject: absent nephron [MP:0011292]
Value: complete absence of functional filtering units in the kidney

Subject: dilated nephron [MP:0011293]
Value: stretched or widened aperture of the luminal space of the filtering unit of the kidney

Subject: renal glomerulus hypertrophy [MP:0011294]
Value: increase in the bulk size of the capillary loops of the kidney that normally function as a filtration unit, due to cell enlargement

Subject: abnormal tubuloglomerular feedback response [MP:0011295]
Value: any anomaly in the blood flow control mechanism that is operated in the juxtaglomerular apparatus of the kidney and involved in renal autoregulation by limiting changes in the glomerular filtration rate. TGF responds to changes in the concentration of NaCl in the tubular fluid at the level of the macula densa

Subject: decreased tubuloglomerular feedback response [MP:0011296]
Value: attenuation of the blood flow control mechanism that is operated in the juxtaglomerular apparatus of the kidney and involved in renal autoregulation by limiting changes in the glomerular filtration rate. TGF responds to changes in the concentration of NaCl in the tubular fluid at the level of the macula densa

Subject: absent tubuloglomerular feedback response [MP:0011297]
Value: absence of the blood flow control mechanism that is operated in the juxtaglomerular apparatus of the kidney and involved in renal autoregulation by limiting changes in the glomerular filtration rate. TGF responds to changes in the concentration of NaCl in the tubular fluid at the level of the macula densa

Subject: ureter hypoplasia [MP:0011298]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size of the ureter, usually due to a reduced number of cells

Subject: abnormal macula densa morphology [MP:0011299]
Value: any structural anomaly of the specialized group of densely packed epithelial cells marking the origin of the convoluted portion of the distal tubule of a nephron, in contact with the afferent arteriole of the renal corpuscle and contiguous with the juxtaglomerular cells; these cells are tall, thin and columnar, have prominent nuclei, and act as sensors of solute concentration and flow of tubular fluid

Subject: abnormal juxtaglomerular cell morphology [MP:0011300]
Value: any structural anomaly of the specialized smooth muscle cells that synthesize, store, and secrete renin and are found in the wall of each afferent arteriole of a kidney glomerulus near its point of entry adjacent to a macula densa; J-G cells are distinguished by their granulated cytoplasm and play a critical role in the renin-angiotensin system and thus in renal autoregulation

Subject: juxtaglomerular cell hyperplasia [MP:0011301]
Value: increased number of the specialized smooth muscle cells that synthesize, store, and secrete renin and are found in the wall of each afferent arteriole of a kidney glomerulus near its point of entry adjacent to a macula densa

Subject: abnormal extraglomerular mesangial cell morphology [MP:0011302]
Value: any structural anomaly of the light-staining cells in the kidney found outside the glomerulus, near the vascular pole and macula densa; lacis cells form the juxtaglomerular apparatus in combination with two other types of cells: the macula densa of the distal convoluted tubule and juxtaglomerular cells of the afferent arteriole

Subject: absent kidney papilla [MP:0011303]
Value: absence of the apex (tip) of a renal pyramid i.e. the location where each medullary pyramid empties urine into a minor calyx

Subject: kidney papillary atrophy [MP:0011304]
Value: acquired diminution of the size of the apex (tip) of a renal pyramid associated with wasting as from death and reabsorbtion of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes

Subject: dilated kidney calyx [MP:0011305]
Value: an expansion in the lumen volume or area of any of the branches of the renal pelvis that surround each renal papilla and collect urine

Subject: absent kidney pelvis [MP:0011306]
Value: absence of the funnel shaped proximal portion of the ureter, normally formed by convergence of the major calices

Subject: kidney medulla cysts [MP:0011307]
Value: abnormal membranous sacs appearing in the inner portion of the kidney which consists of the renal pyramids

Subject: kidney corticomedullary cysts [MP:0011308]
Value: development of abnormal membranous sacs in the corticomedullary junction of the kidney

Subject: abnormal kidney arterial blood vessel morphology [MP:0011309]
Value: any structural anomaly of the network of tubes that supply blood to the renal tissues

Subject: abnormal kidney capillary morphology [MP:0011310]
Value: any structural anomaly of the small branching blood vessels in the kidney that form a network between the arterioles and venules, where the exchange of water, oxygen, carbon dioxide, and other nutrient and waste chemical substances occurs between the blood and the surrounding tissues

Subject: abnormal kidney venous blood vessel morphology [MP:0011311]
Value: any structural anomaly of the network of tubes that return blood from the renal tissues to the systemic circulation

Subject: abnormal kidney afferent arteriole morphology [MP:0011312]
Value: any structural anomaly of the blood vessels that branch from the kidney interlobular artery, convey blood to the glomerular capillaries, and play an important role in the regulation of blood pressure as a part of the tubuloglomerular feedback mechanism

Subject: abnormal kidney efferent arteriole morphology [MP:0011313]
Value: any structural anomaly of the blood vessels that convey blood from the glomerulocapillary network to the capillary bed of the proximal convoluted tubule

Subject: abnormal kidney cortex artery morphology [MP:0011314]
Value: any structural anomaly of the network of tubes that supplies blood to the renal cortex

Subject: abnormal kidney arcuate artery morphology [MP:0011315]
Value: any structural anomaly of the curved arteries at the corticomedullary border of the kidney that arise from the interlobar arteries and give rise to the interlobular arteries

Subject: abnormal kidney interlobular artery morphology [MP:0011316]
Value: any structural anomaly of the branches of the arcuate arteries of the kidney that radiate outward throught the renal columns and supply the glomeruli

Subject: abnormal renal artery morphology [MP:0011317]
Value: any structural anomaly of the pair of major vessels which arise off the side of the abdominal aorta, immediately below the superior mesenteric artery, and supply the kidneys with blood; small branches of the renal artery also supply the suprarenal gland, the ureter and some surrounding tissues

Subject: abnormal right renal artery morphology [MP:0011318]
Value: any structural anomaly of the major vessel which arises off the side of the abdominal aorta, immediately below the superior mesenteric artery, and supplies the right kidney with blood

Subject: abnormal left renal artery morphology [MP:0011319]
Value: any structural anomaly of the major vessel which arises off the side of the abdominal aorta, immediately below the superior mesenteric artery, and supplies the left kidney with blood

Subject: abnormal glomerular capillary morphology [MP:0011320]
Value: any structural anomaly of the small branching blood vessels in the kidney glomerulus that receives blood from the kidney afferent arterioles; these capillaries are under high pressure for filtering within the glomerulus

Subject: abnormal peritubular capillary morphology [MP:0011321]
Value: any structural anomaly of the tiny blood vessels that receive blood from the efferent arterioles of the glomerulus, and interact with superficial cortical nephrons allowing reabsorption and secretion between blood and the inner lumen of the nephron; peritubular capillaries are situated around the tubule and are at low pressure

Subject: abnormal kidney cortex vein morphology [MP:0011322]
Value: any structural anomaly of the network of tubes that receives blood from the renal cortex

Subject: abnormal renal vein morphology [MP:0011323]
Value: any structural anomaly of the pair of major vessels which arise from the renal hilus and return blood from the kidneys, suprarenal gland and the ureter to the inferior vena cava

Subject: abnormal kidney arcuate vein morphology [MP:0011325]
Value: any structural anomaly of the veins that parallel the arcuate arteries, receive blood from the interlobular veins and straight venules, and terminate in the interlobar veins

Subject: abnormal interlobular vein morphology [MP:0011326]
Value: any structural anomaly of the veins that parallel the interlobular arteries, receiving blood from the peritubular capillary plexus and empty into the arcuate veins

Subject: abnormal left renal vein morphology [MP:0011327]
Value: any structural anomaly of the longer of the two renal veins that receives blood from the left kidney; the left renal vein usually receives the left inferior phrenic vein, the left suprarenal vein, the left gonadal vein (left testicular vein in males, left ovarian vein in females) and the left second lumbar vein whereas these veins on the right side drain directly into the inferior vena cava

Subject: abnormal right renal vein morphology [MP:0011328]
Value: any structural anomaly of the shorter of the two renal veins that receives blood from the right kidney; the left renal vein usually receives the left inferior phrenic vein, the left suprarenal vein, the left gonadal vein (left testicular vein in males, left ovarian vein in females) and the left second lumbar vein whereas these veins on the right side drain directly into the inferior vena cava

Subject: abnormal papillary duct morphology [MP:0011331]
Value: any structural anomaly of the largest straight excretory ducts in the kidney medulla and papillae that are a continuation of the collecting tubules, and that open into the area cribosa

Subject: abnormal kidney outer medulla morphology [MP:0011332]
Value: any structural anomaly of the outer medullary region of the adult kidney containing the short Loops of Henle and collecting ducts

Subject: abnormal kidney inner medulla morphology [MP:0011333]
Value: any structural anomaly of the inner medullary region of the adult kidney containing collecting ducts and the long loops of Henle

Subject: abnormal nephrogenic zone morphology [MP:0011334]
Value: any structural anomaly in the region found at the periphery of the developing metanephros within which the metanephric mesenchyme aggregates around the tips of the ureteric tree to form the nephrons; in rodents including mice, this region normally disappears within the first postnatal week when nephrogenesis ceases and only mature nephrons are present; in humans, it is lost by 36 weeks of gestation

Subject: abnormal kidney pelvis smooth muscle morphology [MP:0011335]
Value: any structural anomaly of the smooth muscle tissue surrounding the urothelium of the kidney pelvis

Subject: abnormal kidney pelvis urothelium morphology [MP:0011336]
Value: any structural anomaly of the epithelial lining of the luminal space of the kidney pelvis

Subject: abnormal perihilar interstitium morphology [MP:0011337]
Value: any structural anomaly of the part of the renal interstitium surrounding the pelvis

Subject: abnormal mesangial matrix morphology [MP:0011338]
Value: any structural anomaly of the extracellular matrix secreted by intraglomerular mesangial cells

Subject: abnormal glomerular mesangium morphology [MP:0011339]
Value: any structural anomaly of the inner layer of the glomerulus within the basement membrane surrounding the glomerular capillaries that contain the intraglomerular mesangial cells

Subject: abnormal extraglomerular mesangium morphology [MP:0011340]
Value: any structural anomaly of the tissue comprised of mesangial cells that fill the triangular space between the macula densa and the afferent and efferent arterioles of the juxtaglomerular apparatus

Subject: abnormal loop of Henle descending limb morphology [MP:0011341]
Value: any structural anomaly of the portion of the renal tubule that constitutes the proximal part of the loop of Henle, has low permeability to ions and urea, and is highly permeable to water; it consists of an initial short thick segment lined by low simple cuboidal epithelium and a long thin segment lined by simple squamous epithelium; however, this distinction is not as important physiologically as in the ascending limb, so often the two are treated as one structure

Subject: abnormal loop of Henle ascending limb morphology [MP:0011342]
Value: any structural anomaly of the distal part of the loop of Henle that is impermeable to water and actively pumps sodium out of the filtrate to generate the hypertonic interstitium that drives countercurrent exchange; it consists of an initial very thin segment lined by simple squamous epithelium followed by a distal thick segment lined by simple cuboidal epithelium

Subject: abnormal loop of Henle ascending limb thin segment morphology [MP:0011343]
Value: any structural anomaly of the initial sub-portion of the ascending loop of Henle localized in the juxtamedullary nephron of the kidney; it is lined by simple squamous epithelium, impermeable to water but permeable to ions and other small particles

Subject: abnormal loop of Henle ascending limb thick segment morphology [MP:0011344]
Value: any structural anomaly of the distal sub-portion of the ascending loop of Henle which is lined by simple cuboidal epithelium and enters the renal cortex to empty a hypotonic filtrate into the distal convoluted tubule

Subject: truncated loop of Henle [MP:0011345]
Value: failure of the developing loop of Henle to elongate and extend into the medullary zone of the kidney

Subject: renal tubule atrophy [MP:0011346]
Value: acquired diminution of the size of the loops of Henle, the proximal convoluted tubule or the distal convoluted tubule associated with wasting as from death and reabsorbtion of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes

Subject: abnormal kidney medullary ray morphology [MP:0011347]
Value: any structural anomaly in the center of a renal, cortical lobule, consisting of the ascending or descending limbs of the loop of Henle or of the collecting tubules; medullary rays are regions where parallel arrays of straight tubules travel perpendicular to the capsule and extend from the cortex to the medulla

Subject: abnormal renal glomerulus basement membrane morphology [MP:0011348]
Value: any structural anomaly of the layer of extracellular matrix that lies between the endothelium of the glomerular capillaries and the podocytes of the inner or visceral layer of the Bowman capsule; it is a fusion of the endothelial cell and podocyte basal laminas and acts as a physical barrier and an ion-selective filter

Subject: abnormal renal glomerulus basement membrane thickness [MP:0011349]
Value: increased or decreased width of the layer of extracellular matrix that lies between the endothelium of the glomerular capillaries and the podocytes of the inner or visceral layer of the Bowman capsule

Subject: abnormal proximal convoluted tubule brush border morphology [MP:0011350]
Value: any structural anomaly of the densely packed microvilli that cover the luminal surface of epithelial cells of the proximal convoluted tubule; microvilli increase the luminal surface area of cells, sense the fluid flow in the tubule lumen and convert this information via biochemical responses into reabsorption

Subject: absent proximal convoluted tubule brush border [MP:0011351]
Value: failure to form a brush border of densely packed microvilli on the luminal surface of epithelial cells of the proximal convoluted tubule

Subject: proximal convoluted tubule brush border loss [MP:0011352]
Value: attenuation or degeneration of the microvillus brush border normally present on the luminal surface of epithelial cells of the proximal convoluted tubule; may be associated with renal tubular injury and/or cystic changes

Subject: expanded mesangial matrix [MP:0011353]
Value: increase in the amount of mesangial matrix present in the basement membrane surrounding the glomerular capillaries that also contain the intraglomerular mesangial cells

Subject: absent renal glomerulus [MP:0011354]
Value: complete absence of the tuft formed of capillary loops and mesangium at the beginning of each nephretic tubule in the kidney that normally function as a filtration unit

Subject: abnormal kidney interlobar artery morphology [MP:0011355]
Value: any structural anomaly of the branches of the segmental arteries of the kidney that cross between the renal lobes and give rise to the arculate arteries in the cortex

Subject: renal artery stenosis [MP:0011356]
Value: diffuse constriction or narrowing of one or both renal arteries

Subject: supernumerary renal arteries [MP:0011357]
Value: two or more arteries branch from the abdominal aorta and supply a single kidney

Subject: renal artery aneurysm [MP:0011358]
Value: a protruding sac formed by the dilation of the wall of a renal artery, resulting from a weakening of the vessel wall or heart muscle

Subject: decreased glomerular capillary number [MP:0011359]
Value: reduced number of the small branching blood vessels in the kidney glomerulus that receives blood from the kidney afferent arterioles

Subject: kidney cortex hypoplasia [MP:0011360]
Value: underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, of the outer portion of the kidney, which contains the renal corpuscles, the renal tubules (except for parts of the loop of Henle which descend into the renal medulla), blood vessels and cortical collecting ducts

Subject: pelvic kidney [MP:0011361]
Value: an ectopic kidney located outside the renal fossa and within the pelvic cavity; pelvic kidneys may also, on occasion, occur as fused midline horseshoe kidneys

Subject: ectopic adrenal gland [MP:0011362]
Value: an adrenal gland located outside of its normal position

Subject: renal glomerulus atrophy [MP:0011363]
Value: acquired diminution of the size of the capillary loops of the kidney associated with wasting as from death and reabsorbtion of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes

Subject: abnormal metanephros morphology [MP:0011364]
Value: any structural anomaly of the primordium of the permanent kidney, which develops later than and caudal to the mesonephros, from the mesonephric duct and nephrogenic cord; the metanephros is an endocrine and metabolic organ that filters the blood and excretes the end products of body metabolism in the form of urine

Subject: small metanephros [MP:0011365]
Value: reduced size of the primordium of the permanent kidney, which develops later than and caudal to the mesonephros, from the mesonephric duct and nephrogenic cord

Subject: absent metanephros [MP:0011366]
Value: absence of the primordium of the permanent kidney, which develops later than and caudal to the mesonephros, from the mesonephric duct and nephrogenic cord

Subject: abnormal kidney apoptosis [MP:0011367]
Value: change in the timing or the number of kidney cells undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: increased kidney apoptosis [MP:0011368]
Value: increase in the number of cells of the kidney undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: increased renal glomerulus apoptosis [MP:0011369]
Value: increase in the number of cells of the kidney glomerulus undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: increased mesangial cell apoptosis [MP:0011370]
Value: increase in the number of phagocytic cells in the capillary tuft of the renal glomerulus undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: decreased kidney apoptosis [MP:0011371]
Value: decrease in the number of cells of the kidney undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: decreased renal tubule apoptosis [MP:0011372]
Value: decrease in the number of renal tubule cells undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: decreased mesangial cell apoptosis [MP:0011373]
Value: decrease in the number of phagocytic cells in the capillary tuft of the renal glomerulus undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: decreased podocyte apoptosis [MP:0011374]
Value: decrease in the number of podocytes undergoing programmed cell death; podocyte apoptosis is an early step in the pathophysiological progression to proteinuria and glomerulosclerosis

Subject: decreased renal glomerulus apoptosis [MP:0011375]
Value: decrease in the number of cells of the kidney glomerulus undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: abnormal kidney corticomedullary boundary morphology [MP:0011376]
Value: any structural anomaly of the region demarcating the renal medulla from the surrounding cortex; end-stage renal failure may be associated with loss of the normal corticomedullary boundary

Subject: renal glomerulus fibrosis [MP:0011377]
Value: formation of fibrous tissue in the renal glomerulus as a result of repair or a reactive process

Subject: abnormal kidney outer medulla inner stripe morphology [MP:0011378]
Value: any structural anomaly of the deep, centrally located portion of the renal outer medulla that is traversed by thin descending and thick ascending portions of the loops of Henle

Subject: abnormal kidney outer medulla outer stripe morphology [MP:0011379]
Value: any structural anomaly of the region of the kidney outer medulla that lies just below the cortex; the proximal straight tubules are present in this region

Subject: enlarged brain ventricles [MP:0011380]
Value: increased size of one or more of the four communicating cavities within the brain that are continuous with the central canal of the spinal cord

Subject: abnormal kidney lobe morphology [MP:0011381]
Value: any structural anomaly of the portion of a kidney consisting of a renal medullary pyramid and the renal cortex above it; human kidneys have multilobar (multipyramidal) architecture while mice and rats have unilobar (unipyramidal) kidneys

Subject: abnormal kidney lobule morphology [MP:0011382]
Value: any structural anomaly of the portion of a renal lobe consisting of nephrons grouped around a single medullary ray and draining into a single collecting duct; human kidneys have multilobular, multipapillary architecture while mice and rats have unilobular, unipapillary kidneys

Subject: abnormal kidney capsule morphology [MP:0011383]
Value: any structural anomaly of the tough fibrous layer surrounding the kidney which is covered in a thick layer of perirenal adipose tissue that functions to provide some protection from trauma and damage

Subject: abnormal progesterone level [MP:0011384]
Value: anomaly in the concentration of the antiestrogenic steroid released by the corpus luteum that stimulates the uterus to prepare for pregnancy

Subject: abnormal testosterone level [MP:0011385]
Value: anomaly in the concentration of a potent androgen that promotes development of male secondary sex characteristics and the development of spermatozoa and may regulate sexual desire and help maintain bone and muscle health in both males and females

Subject: increased metanephric mesenchyme apoptosis [MP:0011386]
Value: increase in the number of cells of the metanephric mesenchyme (MM) undergoing programmed cell death; usually due to failure of MM cells to interact with the ureteric bud (UB) tips after UB invasion

Subject: absent metanephric mesenchyme [MP:0011387]
Value: absence of the embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing metanephros; normally, interactions between the ureteric bud and the metanephric mesenchyme lead to the initiation of outgrowth and repetitive branching of the UB that ultimately generates the definitive renal collecting system and induces formation of renal vesicles from the mesenchyme tissue

Subject: absent heart [MP:0011388]
Value: absence of the hollow, muscular organ that maintains the circulation of the blood

Subject: absent optic disk [MP:0011389]
Value: absence of the area in the retina where all of the axons of the ganglion cells exit the retina to form the optic nerve

Subject: abnormal fetal cardiomyocyte physiology [MP:0011390]
Value: any functional anomaly of fetal and neonatal heart cells that undergo proliferation and are not yet terminally differentiated into binucleate or multinucleate cardiac myocytes

Subject: abnormal fetal cardiomyocyte apoptosis [MP:0011391]
Value: change in the timing or the number of fetal cardiomyocytes undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: increased fetal cardiomyocyte apoptosis [MP:0011392]
Value: increase in the number of fetal cardiomyocytes undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: decreased fetal cardiomyocyte apoptosis [MP:0011393]
Value: reduction in the number of fetal cardiomyocytes undergoing programmed cell death

Subject: increased fetal cardiomyocyte proliferation [MP:0011394]
Value: increase in the ability of the differentiating cardiac muscle cell population to undergo expansion by cell division

Subject: decreased fetal cardiomyocyte proliferation [MP:0011395]
Value: reduced ability of the differentiating cardiac muscle cell population to undergo expansion by cell division

Subject: abnormal sleep behavior [MP:0011396]
Value: any anomaly in the actions, reactions, or performance of an organism during a periodic, readily reversible state of reduced awareness and metabolic activity

Subject: endoneurial edema [MP:0011397]
Value: an excessive accumulation of serous fluid in the interstitial connective tissue of a peripheral nerve

Subject: abnormal endoneurial fluid pressure [MP:0011398]
Value: measureable anomalies in the fluid of the ganglia and peripheral nerves that lie outside the brain and spinal cord which may interfere with normal nerve physiology

Subject: increased endoneurial fluid pressure [MP:0011399]
Value: a measureable increase of serous fluid in the interstitial connective tissue of a peripheral nerve which may interefere with normal nerve physiology

Subject: lethality, complete penetrance [MP:0011400]
Value: all individuals of a given genotype in a population die before the end of the normal lifespan but time(s) of death are unspecified

Subject: abnormal vascular smooth muscle development [MP:0011401]
Value: anomaly in the process of forming the nonstriated, involuntary muscle tissue of the blood vessels

Subject: renal cast [MP:0011402]
Value: any of the various casts formed from gelled protein precipitated in the distal convoluted tubules and collecting ducts of nephrons and molded to the tubular or duct lumen which dislodge and pass into the urine; types named for their constituent material include acellular casts (e.g. granular, hyaline, waxy, or fatty casts) and cellular casts (e.g. red or white blood cell casts)

Subject: pyelonephritis [MP:0011403]
Value: a diffuse pyogenic infection of the pelvis and parenchyma of the kidney; an ascending urinary tract infection that has reached the pyelum or pelvis of the kidney usually resulting from noncontagious bacterial infection of the bladder

Subject: pyelitis [MP:0011404]
Value: acute inflammation of the pelvis of the kidney, caused by bacterial infection

Subject: tubulointerstitial nephritis [MP:0011405]
Value: diffuse or local inflammation and edema of the interstitial tissue of the kidney, including the renal tubules; usually secondary to drug sensitization, systemic infection, graft rejection, or autoimmune disease

Subject: abnormal retrotrapezoid nucleus morphology [MP:0011406]
Value: any structural anomaly in the loose collection of neurons that reside in the rostral medulla close to the medullary surface, ventral and immediately caudal of nVII, that are crucial for CO2 sensing in the brain

Subject: absent nephrogenic zone [MP:0011407]
Value: absence of the region found at the periphery of the developing metanephros within which the metanephric mesenchyme aggregates around the tips of the ureteric tree to form the nephrons;in rodents including mice, this region normally persists for a few days postnatally, although it is lost in humans by 36 weeks of gestation

Subject: renal tubule hypertrophy [MP:0011408]
Value: increase in the bulk size of the loop of Henle, the proximal convoluted tubule or the distal convoluted tubule, due to cell enlargement

Subject: increased renal glomerulus basement membrane thickness [MP:0011409]

Subject: gonadal ridge hypoplasia [MP:0011412]

Subject: colorless urine [MP:0011413]

Subject: erythruria [MP:0011414]

Value: any structural anomaly of the kidney region located between the nephrons, ureteric epithelia (ureteric tips, trunk and collecting duct system) and renal vasculature, and composed of renal support cells, including fibroblasts and macrophages, and mesenchymal stroma or interstitial cells; the renal vasculature lies within the renal interstitium but is not a part of it; various conditions can lead to scarring (fibrosis) and congestion of this area, which can cause kidney dysfunction and failure

Subject: mesangial cell hypoplasia [MP:0011428]

Subject: increased urine flow rate [MP:0011431]

Subject: decreased urine magnesium level [MP:0011436]

Subject: absent kidney medulla [MP:0011438]

Subject: decreased kidney cell proliferation [MP:0011441]

Subject: abnormal renal glucose reabsorption [MP:0011447]

Subject: abnormal glomerular capillary endothelium morphology [MP:0011453]

Subject: abnormal catecholamine level [MP:0011479]

Subject: mesangial cell interposition [MP:0011512]

Subject: skin hemorrhage [MP:0011514]

Subject: decreased urine antidiuretic hormone level [MP:0011544]

Subject: abnormal circulating ghrelin level [MP:0011611]

Subject: increased circulating ghrelin level [MP:0011612]

Subject: abnormal nonassociative learning [MP:0011616]

Subject: abnormal sensitization to xenobiotic [MP:0011624]

Subject: decreased mitochondria number [MP:0011629]

Subject: increased mitochondria size [MP:0011630]

Subject: decreased mitochondria size [MP:0011631]

Subject: abnormal aorta collagen fibril morphology [MP:0011640]

Subject: absent oviduct epithelium motile cilium [MP:0011645]

Subject: abnormal sinuatrial valve morphology [MP:0011646]

Subject: absent sinuatrial valve [MP:0011647]

Subject: abnormal corneal stroma collagen fibril morphology [MP:0011650]

Subject: abnormal circulating histidine level [MP:0011651]

Subject: decreased circulating histidine level [MP:0011653]
Value: the amount of the amino acid histidine in the blood is less than expected

Subject: histidinuria [MP:0011654]

Subject: abnormal systemic artery morphology [MP:0011655]

Subject: coronary arterio-venous fistula [MP:0011656]
Value: an abnormal communication between the terminus of a coronary artery, bypassing the myocardial capillary bed and entering any segment of the systemic or pulmonary circulation

Subject: coronary-cameral fistula [MP:0011657]

Subject: interrupted aortic arch, type a [MP:0011658]

Subject: interrupted aortic arch, type b [MP:0011659]

Subject: ectopia cordis [MP:0011660]

Subject: persistent truncus arteriosus type i [MP:0011661]
Value: complete failure of the common arterial trunk opening out of both ventricles to divide into the aorta and pulmonary artery during development; type i is characterized by origin of a single pulmonary trunk from the left lateral aspect of the common trunk, with branching of the left and right pulmonary arteries from the pulmonary trunk

Subject: persistent truncus arteriosus type ii [MP:0011662]

Subject: persistent truncus arteriosus type iii [MP:0011663]
Value: complete failure of the common arterial trunk opening out of both ventricles to divide into the aorta and pulmonary artery during development; in type iii the branch pulmonary arteries originate independently from the common arterial trunk or aortic arch, most often from the left and right lateral aspects of the trunk; this occasionally occurs with origin of one pulmonary artery from the underside of the aortic arch, usually from a ductus arteriosus

Subject: persistent truncus arteriosus type iv [MP:0011664]
Value: complete failure of the common arterial trunk opening out of both ventricles to divide into the aorta and pulmonary artery during development; type i is a form of the lesion with neither pulmonary arterial branch arises from the common trunk, and is more commonly recognized to be a form of pulmonary atresia with ventricular septal defect rather than truncus arteriosus

Subject: d-loop transposition of the great arteries [MP:0011665]

Subject: double outlet right ventricle, ventricular defect committed to aorta [MP:0011666]

Subject: double outlet right ventricle with atrioventricular septal defect [MP:0011667]

Subject: double outlet right ventricle, Taussig bing type [MP:0011668]

Subject: double outlet right ventricle, doubly committed ventricular septal defect [MP:0011669]

Subject: double outlet right ventricle, noncommitted ventricular septal defect [MP:0011670]

Subject: double aortic arch, balanced arches [MP:0011675]
Value: defect in which the aortic arch splits into equally sized large left and right branches, encircling the trachea and esophagus, before becoming one tube to go to the lower body

Subject: aortic arch obstruction [MP:0011676]
Value: any impediment or blockage causing a cessation or reversal of the normal flow of the blood through the aortic arch

Subject: abnormal olfactory sensory neuron physiology [MP:0011677]

Subject: abnormal vomeronasal sensory neuron physiology [MP:0011678]

Subject: abnormal vomeronasal sensory neuron morphology [MP:0011679]

Subject: tricuspid valve hypoplasia [MP:0011680]

Subject: atrium cysts [MP:0011681]

Subject: renal glomerulus cysts [MP:0011682]

Subject: dual inferior vena cava [MP:0011683]

Subject: coronary-cameral fistula to right ventricle [MP:0011684]

Subject: abnormal limb paddle morphology [MP:0011685]

Subject: increased epidermal stem cell number [MP:0011686]

Subject: decreased epidermal stem cell number [MP:0011687]

Subject: absent epidermal stem cells [MP:0011688]

Subject: absent neutrophils [MP:0011689]

Subject: absent basophils [MP:0011690]
Value: absence of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte that in its mature form has an irregularly shaped, pale-staining nucleus that is partially constricted into two lobes, and with cytoplasm that contains coarse, bluish-black granules of variable size; these cells contain vasoactive amines such as histamine and serotonin, which are released on appropriate stimulation

Subject: absent bronchioalveolar stem cells [MP:0011691]
Value: absence of the respiratory stem cells found at the junction of the terminal (conductive) bronchiole and the respiratory bronchiole, which gives rise to alveolar cell types and Clara cells in response to lung injury

Subject: increased chondrocyte number [MP:0011692]
Value: greater number of polymorphic cells that form cartilage

Subject: absent chondrocytes [MP:0011693]
Value: absence of polymorphic cells that form cartilage

Subject: absent eosinophils [MP:0011694]
Value: any structural anomaly of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte with a nucleus that usually has two lobes connected by one or more slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing coarse, round granules that are uniform in size and which can be stained by the dye eosin

Subject: absent hematopoietic stem cells [MP:0011695]
Value: absence of the multipotent, self-renewing stem cells found in the bone marrow, yolk sac and the fetal liver; HSCs give rise to all the types of both the myeloid and lymphoid cell lineages

Subject: absent mast cells [MP:0011696]
Value: any structural anomaly of a cell that is found in almost all tissues containing numerous basophilic granules and capable of releasing large amounts of histamine and heparin upon activation; progenitors leave bone marrow and mature in connective and mucosal tissue; mature mast cells are found in all tissues, except the bloodstream.

Subject: vacuolated lens [MP:0011697]
Value: fluid filled cavities are present in the cytoplasm of the transparent structure of the eye responsible for focusing light

Subject: abnormal brown adipose tissue physiology [MP:0011698]

Subject: abnormal brown adipose tissue thermogenesis [MP:0011699]

Subject: increased cumulus expansion [MP:0011700]

Subject: decreased cumulus expansion [MP:0011701]
Value: reduced ability of the ovarian cumulus cells to secrete an extensive extracellular matrix required for successful fertilization

Subject: abnormal fibroblast proliferation [MP:0011702]

Subject: increased fibroblast proliferation [MP:0011703]

Subject: decreased fibroblast proliferation [MP:0011704]
Value: reduction in the expansion rate of a fibroblast cell population by cell division

Subject: absent fibroblast proliferation [MP:0011705]

Subject: abnormal fibroblast migration [MP:0011706]

Subject: impaired fibroblast cell migration [MP:0011707]

Subject: decreased fibroblast cell migration [MP:0011708]

Subject: increased fibroblast cell migration [MP:0011709]

Subject: enhanced osteoblast differentiation [MP:0011710]

Subject: impaired osteoblast differentiation [MP:0011711]

Subject: arrested osteoblast differentiation [MP:0011712]

Subject: abnormal natural killer cell mediated cytotoxicity [MP:0011719]

Subject: abnormal ossification involved in bone remodeling [MP:0011720]

Subject: abnormal bone mineralization involved in bone maturation [MP:0011721]

Subject: abnormal ossification involved in bone maturation [MP:0011722]

Subject: ectopic neuron [MP:0011723]

Subject: ectopic cortical neuron [MP:0011724]

Subject: neuronal leptomeningeal ectopia [MP:0011725]

Subject: ectopic Cajal-Retzius cell [MP:0011726]

Subject: ectopic ovary [MP:0011727]

Subject: abnormal pineal gland physiology [MP:0011728]

Subject: abnormal pineal gland melatonin secretion [MP:0011729]

Subject: increased myelin sheath thickness [MP:0011730]

Subject: decreased myelin sheath thickness [MP:0011731]

Subject: decreased somite size [MP:0011732]

Subject: fused somites [MP:0011733]

Subject: abnormal urine ammonia level [MP:0011734]

Subject: increased urine ammonia level [MP:0011735]

Subject: decreased urine ammonia level [MP:0011736]

Subject: hypodipsia [MP:0011737]

Subject: anasarca [MP:0011738]

Subject: abnormal Boettcher cell morphology [MP:0011739]

Subject: abnormal urine nitrite level [MP:0011740]

Subject: increased urine nitrite level [MP:0011741]

Subject: decreased urine nitrite level [MP:0011742]

Subject: abnormal Golgi apparatus morphology [MP:0011743]

Subject: abnormal kidney epithelial cell primary cilium physiology [MP:0011744]

Subject: isolation of the left subclavian artery [MP:0011745]

Subject: spleen fibrosis [MP:0011746]

Subject: myelofibrosis [MP:0011747]

Subject: intestinal fibrosis [MP:0011748]

Subject: perivascular fibrosis [MP:0011749]
